63 /* figure out how many bytes a QO_USING_INDEX struct with n entries requires */
64 #define SIZEOF_USING_INDEX(n) \
65  (sizeof(QO_USING_INDEX) + (((n)-1) * sizeof(QO_USING_INDEX_ENTRY)))

67 /* any number that won't overlap PT_MISC_TYPE */
68 #define PREDICATE_TERM -2

70 #define RANK_DEFAULT 0 /* default */
71 #define RANK_NAME RANK_DEFAULT /* name -- use default */
72 #define RANK_VALUE RANK_DEFAULT /* value -- use default */
73 #define RANK_EXPR_LIGHT 1 /* Group 1 */
74 #define RANK_EXPR_MEDIUM 2 /* Group 2 */
75 #define RANK_EXPR_HEAVY 3 /* Group 3 */
76 #define RANK_EXPR_FUNCTION 4 /* agg function, set */
77 #define RANK_QUERY 8 /* subquery */

113 #define EXCHANGE_BUILDER(type,e0,e1) \
114  do { type _tmp = e0; e0 = e1; e1 = _tmp; } while (0)
115 
116 #define TERMCLASS_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(QO_TERMCLASS,e0,e1)
117 #define DOUBLE_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(double,e0,e1)
118 #define PT_NODE_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(PT_NODE *,e0,e1)
119 #define INT_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(int,e0,e1)
120 #define SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(QO_SEGMENT *,e0,e1)
121 #define NODEPTR_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(QO_NODE *,e0,e1)
122 #define EQCLASSPTR_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(QO_EQCLASS *,e0,e1)
123 #define BOOL_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(bool,e0,e1)
124 #define JOIN_TYPE_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(JOIN_TYPE,e0,e1)
125 #define FLAG_EXCHANGE(e0,e1) EXCHANGE_BUILDER(int,e0,e1)
126 
127 #define BISET_EXCHANGE(s0,s1) \
128  do { \
129  BITSET tmp; \
130  BITSET_MOVE(tmp, s0); \
131  BITSET_MOVE(s0, s1); \
132  BITSET_MOVE(s1, tmp); \
133  } while (0)
134 
135 #define PUT_FLAG(cond, flag) \
136  do { \
137  if (cond) { \
138  if (extra_info++) { \
139  fputs(flag, f); \
140  } else { \
141  fputs(" (", f); \
142  fputs(flag, f); \
143  } \
144  } \
145  } while (0)

259 /*
260  * qo_get_optimization_param () - Return the current value of some (global)
261  * optimization parameter
262  * return: int
263  * retval(in): pointer to area to receive info
264  * param(in): what parameter to retrieve
265  * ...(in): parameter-specific parameters
266  */
267 void
268 qo_get_optimization_param (void *retval, QO_PARAM param, ...)
269 {
270  char *buf;
271  va_list args;
272 
273  va_start (args, param);
274 
275  switch (param)
276  {
277  case QO_PARAM_LEVEL:
278  *(int *) retval = prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_OPTIMIZATION_LEVEL);
279  break;
280  case QO_PARAM_COST:
281  buf = (char *) retval;
282  buf[0] = (char) qo_plan_get_cost_fn (va_arg (args, char *));
283  buf[1] = '\0';
284  break;
285  }
286 
287  va_end (args);
288 }
289 
290 /*
291  * qo_need_skip_execution (void) - check execution level and return skip or not
292  *
293  * return: bool
294  */
295 bool
296 qo_need_skip_execution (void)
297 {
298  int level;
299 
300  qo_get_optimization_param (&level, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
301 
302  return level & 0x02;
303 }
304 
305 /*
306  * qo_set_optimization_param () - Return the old value of some (global)
307  * optimization param, and set the global
308  * param to the new value
309  * return: int
310  * retval(in): pointer to area to receive info about old value
311  * param(in): what parameter to retrieve
312  * ...(in): parameter-specific parameters
313  */
314 void
315 qo_set_optimization_param (void *retval, QO_PARAM param, ...)
316 {
317  va_list args;
318  va_start (args, param);
319 
320  switch (param)
321  {
322  case QO_PARAM_LEVEL:
323  if (retval)
324  {
325  *(int *) retval = prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_OPTIMIZATION_LEVEL);
326  }
327  prm_set_integer_value (PRM_ID_OPTIMIZATION_LEVEL, va_arg (args, int));
328  break;
329 
330  case QO_PARAM_COST:
331  {
332  const char *plan_name;
333  int cost_fn;
334 
335  plan_name = va_arg (args, char *);
336  cost_fn = va_arg (args, int);
337  plan_name = qo_plan_set_cost_fn (plan_name, cost_fn);
338  if (retval)
339  {
340  *(const char **) retval = plan_name;
341  }
342  break;
343  }
344  }
345 
346  va_end (args);
347 }
348 
349 /*
350  * qo_optimize_query () - optimize a single select statement, skip nested
351  * selects since embedded selects are optimized first
352  * return: void
353  * parser(in): parser environment
354  * tree(in): select tree to optimize
355  */
356 QO_PLAN *
357 qo_optimize_query (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree)
358 {
359  QO_ENV *env;
360  int level;
361 
362  /*
363  * Give up right away if the optimizer has been turned off in the
364  * user's cubrid.conf file or somewhere else.
365  */
366  qo_get_optimization_param (&level, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
367  if (!OPTIMIZATION_ENABLED (level))
368  {
369  return NULL;
370  }
371 
372  /* if its not a select, we're not interested, also if it is merge we give up. */
373  if (tree->node_type != PT_SELECT)
374  {
375  return NULL;
376  }
377 
378  env = qo_env_init (parser, tree);
379  if (env == NULL)
380  {
381  /* we can't optimize, so bail out */
382  return NULL;
383  }
384 
385  switch (setjmp (env->catch_))
386  {
387  case 0:
388  /*
389  * The return here is ok; we'll take care of freeing the env structure later, when qo_plan_discard is called.
390  * In fact, if we free it now, the plan pointer we're about to return will be worthless.
391  */
392  return qo_optimize_helper (env);
393  case 1:
394  /*
395  * Out of memory during optimization. malloc() has already done an er_set().
396  */
397  break;
398  case 2:
399  /*
400  * Failed some optimizer assertion. QO_ABORT() has already done an er_set().
401  */
402  break;
403  default:
404  /*
405  * No clue.
406  */
407  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FAILED_ASSERTION, 1, "false");
408  break;
409  }
410 
411  /*
412  * If we get here, an error of some sort occurred, and we need to tear down everything and get out.
413  */
414 #if defined(CUBRID_DEBUG)
415  fprintf (stderr, "*** optimizer aborting ***\n");
416 #endif /* CUBRID_DEBUG */
417  qo_env_free (env);
418 
419  return NULL;
420 }
421 
422 /*
423  * qo_optimize_helper () -
424  * return:
425  * env(in):
426  */
427 static QO_PLAN *
428 qo_optimize_helper (QO_ENV * env)
429 {
430  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser;
431  PT_NODE *tree;
432  PT_NODE *spec, *conj, *next;
433  QO_ENV *local_env; /* So we can safely take its address */
434  QO_PLAN *plan;
435  int level;
436  QO_TERM *term;
437  QO_NODE *node, *p_node;
438  BITSET nodeset;
439  int n;
440 
441  parser = QO_ENV_PARSER (env);
442  tree = QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env);
443  local_env = env;
444 
445  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree, build_query_graph, &local_env, build_query_graph_post, &local_env);
446  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree, build_query_graph_function_index, &local_env, NULL, NULL);
447  (void) add_hint (env, tree);
448  add_using_index (env, tree->info.query.q.select.using_index);
449 
450  /* add dep term */
451  {
452  BITSET dependencies;
453  BITSET antecedents;
454 
455  bitset_init (&dependencies, env);
456  bitset_init (&antecedents, env);
457 
458  for (n = 0; n < env->nnodes; n++)
459  {
460  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n);
461  spec = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
462 
463  /*
464  * Set up the dependencies; it's simplest just to assume that a
465  * dependent table depends on everything that precedes it.
466  */
467  if (is_dependent_table (spec))
468  {
469  /*
470  * Find all of the segments (i.e., attributes) referenced in
471  * the derived table expression, and then find the set of
472  * nodes that underly those segments. This node can't be
473  * added to a join plan before all of those nodes have, so we
474  * establish some artificial dependency links that force the
475  * planner to maintain that constraint.
476  */
477 
478  BITSET_CLEAR (dependencies);
479  BITSET_CLEAR (antecedents);
480 
481  qo_expr_segs (env, spec->info.spec.derived_table, &dependencies);
482 
483  if (!bitset_is_empty (&dependencies))
484  {
485  qo_seg_nodes (env, &dependencies, &antecedents);
486  qo_add_dep_term (node, &antecedents, &dependencies, env);
487  }
488  }
489  } /* for (n = 0 ...) */
490 
491  bitset_delset (&dependencies);
492  bitset_delset (&antecedents);
493  }
494 
495  bitset_init (&nodeset, env);
496 
497  /* add term in the ON clause */
498  for (spec = tree->info.query.q.select.from; spec; spec = spec->next)
499  {
500  if (spec->node_type == PT_SPEC && spec->info.spec.on_cond)
501  {
502  for (conj = spec->info.spec.on_cond; conj; conj = conj->next)
503  {
504  next = conj->next;
505  conj->next = NULL;
506 
507  /* The conjuct could be PT_VALUE(0) if an explicit join condition was derived/transformed to the
508  * always-false search condition when type checking, expression evaluation or query rewrite
509  * transformation. We should sustained it for correct join plan. It's different from ordinary WHERE
510  * search condition. If an always-false search condition was found in WHERE clause, they did not call
511  * query optimization and return no result to the user unless the query doesn't have aggregation.
512  */
513 
514  term = qo_add_term (conj, PREDICATE_TERM, env);
515 
516  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN)
517  {
518  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_ON_COND_TERM (term));
519 
520  n = QO_TERM_LOCATION (term);
521  if (QO_NODE_LOCATION (QO_TERM_HEAD (term)) == n - 1 && QO_NODE_LOCATION (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)) == n)
522  {
523  bitset_add (&nodeset, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)));
524  }
525  }
526 
527  conj->next = next;
528  }
529  }
530  }
531 
532  /* add term in the WHERE clause */
533  for (conj = tree->info.query.q.select.where; conj; conj = conj->next)
534  {
535  next = conj->next;
536  conj->next = NULL;
537 
538  term = qo_add_term (conj, PREDICATE_TERM, env);
539  conj->next = next;
540  }
541 
542  for (n = 1; n < env->nnodes; n++)
543  {
544  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n);
545 
546  /* check join-edge for explicit join */
547  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) != PT_JOIN_NONE && QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) != PT_JOIN_CROSS
548  && !BITSET_MEMBER (nodeset, n))
549  {
550  p_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n - 1);
551  (void) qo_add_dummy_join_term (env, p_node, node);
552  /* Is it safe to pass node[n-1] as head node? Yes, because the sequence of QO_NODEs corresponds to the
553  * sequence of PT_SPEC list
554  */
555  }
556  }
557 
558  /* classify terms for outer join */
559  qo_classify_outerjoin_terms (env);
560 
561  bitset_delset (&nodeset);
562 
563  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.list, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env, pt_continue_walk,
564  NULL);
565  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.group_by, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env,
566  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
567  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.having, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env, pt_continue_walk,
568  NULL);
569 
570  /* it's necessary to find segments for nodes in predicates that are evaluated after joins, in order to be available
571  * in intermediary output lists
572  */
573  if (tree->info.query.q.select.connect_by && !tree->info.query.q.select.single_table_opt)
574  {
575  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.start_with, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env,
576  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
577  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.connect_by, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env,
578  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
579  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.query.q.select.after_cb_filter, qo_add_final_segment, &local_env,
580  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
581  }
582 
583  /* finish the rest of the opt structures */
584  qo_discover_edges (env);
585 
586  /* Don't do these things until *after* qo_discover_edges(); that function may rearrange the QO_TERM structures that
587  * were discovered during the earlier phases, and anyone who grabs the idx of one of the terms (or even a pointer to
588  * one) will be pointing to the wrong term after they're rearranged.
589  */
590  qo_assign_eq_classes (env);
591 
592  get_local_subqueries (env, tree);
593  get_rank (env);
594  qo_discover_indexes (env);
595  qo_discover_partitions (env);
596  qo_discover_sort_limit_nodes (env);
597  /* now optimize */
598 
599  plan = qo_planner_search (env);
600 
601  /* need to set est_card for the select in case it is a subquery */
602 
603  /*
604  * Print out any needed post-optimization info. Leave a way to find
605  * out about environment info if we aren't able to produce a plan.
606  * If this happens in the field at least we'll be able to glean some info.
607  */
608  qo_get_optimization_param (&level, QO_PARAM_LEVEL);
609  if (plan && PLAN_DUMP_ENABLED (level) && DETAILED_DUMP (level) && env->plan_dump_enabled)
610  {
611  qo_env_dump (env, query_Plan_dump_fp);
612  }
613  if (plan == NULL)
614  {
615  qo_env_free (env);
616  }
617 
618  return plan;
619 }
620 
621 /*
622  * qo_env_init () - initialize an optimizer environment
623  * return: QO_ENV *
624  * parser(in): parser environment
625  * query(in): A pointer to a PT_NODE structure that describes the query to be optimized
626  */
627 static QO_ENV *
628 qo_env_init (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query)
629 {
630  QO_ENV *env;
631  int i;
632  size_t size;
633 
634  if (query == NULL)
635  {
636  return NULL;
637  }
638 
639  env = qo_env_new (parser, query);
640  if (env == NULL)
641  {
642  return NULL;
643  }
644 
645  if (qo_validate (env))
646  {
647  goto error;
648  }
649 
650  env->segs = NULL;
651  if (env->nsegs > 0)
652  {
653  size = sizeof (QO_SEGMENT) * env->nsegs;
654  env->segs = (QO_SEGMENT *) malloc (size);
655  if (env->segs == NULL)
656  {
657  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
658  goto error;
659  }
660  }
661 
662  env->nodes = NULL;
663  if (env->nnodes > 0)
664  {
665  size = sizeof (QO_NODE) * env->nnodes;
666  env->nodes = (QO_NODE *) malloc (size);
667  if (env->nodes == NULL)
668  {
669  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
670  goto error;
671  }
672  }
673 
674  env->terms = NULL;
675  if (env->nterms > 0)
676  {
677  size = sizeof (QO_TERM) * env->nterms;
678  env->terms = (QO_TERM *) malloc (size);
679  if (env->terms == NULL)
680  {
681  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
682  goto error;
683  }
684  }
685 
686  env->eqclasses = NULL;
687  size = sizeof (QO_EQCLASS) * (MAX (env->nnodes, env->nterms) + env->nsegs);
688  if (size > 0)
689  {
690  env->eqclasses = (QO_EQCLASS *) malloc (size);
691  if (env->eqclasses == NULL)
692  {
693  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
694  goto error;
695  }
696  }
697 
698  env->partitions = NULL;
699  if (env->nnodes > 0)
700  {
701  size = sizeof (QO_PARTITION) * env->nnodes;
702  env->partitions = (QO_PARTITION *) malloc (size);
703  if (env->partitions == NULL)
704  {
705  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
706  goto error;
707  }
708  }
709 
710  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; ++i)
711  {
712  qo_seg_clear (env, i);
713  }
714 
715  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; ++i)
716  {
717  qo_node_clear (env, i);
718  }
719 
720  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; ++i)
721  {
722  qo_term_clear (env, i);
723  }
724 
725  env->Nnodes = env->nnodes;
726  env->Nsegs = env->nsegs;
727  env->Nterms = env->nterms;
728  env->Neqclasses = MAX (env->nnodes, env->nterms) + env->nsegs;
729 
730  env->nnodes = 0;
731  env->nsegs = 0;
732  env->nterms = 0;
733  env->neqclasses = 0;
734 
735  QO_INFINITY = UTIL_infinity ();
736 
737  return env;
738 
739 error:
740  qo_env_free (env);
741  return NULL;
742 }
743 
744 /*
745  * qo_validate () -
746  * return: true iff we reject the query, false otherwise
747  * env(in): A pointer to the environment we are working on
748  *
749  * Note: Determine whether this is a problem that we're willing to
750  * work on. Right now, this means enforcing the constraints
751  * about maximum set sizes. We're not very happy with
752  * set-valued attributes, class attributes, or shared attributes
753  * either, but these are temporary problems and are detected
754  * elsewhere.
755  */
756 static bool
757 qo_validate (QO_ENV * env)
758 {
759 #define OPTIMIZATION_LIMIT 64
760  PT_NODE *tree, *spec, *conj;
761 
762  tree = QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env);
763 
764  /* find out how many nodes and segments will be required for the query graph. */
765  (void) parser_walk_tree (env->parser, tree, graph_size_select, &env, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
766 
767  /* count the number of conjuncts in the ON clause */
768  for (spec = tree->info.query.q.select.from; spec; spec = spec->next)
769  {
770  if (spec->node_type == PT_SPEC && spec->info.spec.on_cond)
771  {
772  for (conj = spec->info.spec.on_cond; conj; conj = conj->next)
773  {
774  if (conj->node_type != PT_EXPR && conj->node_type != PT_VALUE)
775  { /* for outer join */
776  env->bail_out = 1;
777  return true;
778  }
779  env->nterms++;
780  }
781  }
782  }
783 
784  /* count the number of conjuncts in the WHERE clause */
785  for (conj = tree->info.query.q.select.where; conj; conj = conj->next)
786  {
787  if (conj->node_type != PT_EXPR && conj->node_type != PT_VALUE /* is a false conjunct */ )
788  {
789  env->bail_out = 1;
790  return true;
791  }
792  env->nterms++;
793  }
794 
795  if (env->nnodes > OPTIMIZATION_LIMIT)
796  {
797  return true;
798  }
799 
800  return false;
801 
802 }
803 
804 /*
805  * graph_size_select () - This pre walk function will examine the current
806  * select and determine the graph size needed for it
807  * return: PT_NODE *
808  * parser(in): parser environment
809  * tree(in): tree to walk
810  * arg(in):
811  * continue_walk(in):
812  */
813 static PT_NODE *
814 graph_size_select (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
815 {
816  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
817 
818  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
819 
820  /*
821  * skip nested selects, they've already been counted
822  */
823  if ((tree->node_type == PT_SELECT) && (tree != env->pt_tree))
824  {
825  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
826  return tree;
827  }
828 
829  /* if its not an entity_spec, we're not interested */
830  if (tree->node_type != PT_SPEC)
831  {
832  return tree;
833  }
834 
835  (void) graph_size_for_entity (env, tree);
836 
837  /* don't visit leaves of the entity, graph_size_for_entity already did */
838  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
839 
840  return tree;
841 
842 }
843 
844 /*
845  * graph_size_for_entity () - This routine will size the graph for the entity
846  * return: nothing
847  * env(in): optimizer environment
848  * entity(in): entity to build the graph for
849  *
850  * Note: This routine mimics build_graph_for_entity. It is IMPORTANT that
851  * they remain in sync or else we might not allocate enough space for
852  * the graph arrays resulting in memory corruption.
853  */
854 static void
855 graph_size_for_entity (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * entity)
856 {
857  PT_NODE *name, *conj, *next_entity;
858  MOP cls;
859  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *constraints;
860 
861  env->nnodes++;
862 
863  /* create oid segment for the entity */
864  env->nsegs++;
865 
866  for (name = get_referenced_attrs (entity); name != NULL; name = name->next)
867  {
868  env->nsegs++;
869  }
870 
871  /* check if the constraint is a function index info and add a segment for each function index expression */
872  if (entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
873  {
874  cls = sm_find_class (entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.original);
875  if (cls)
876  {
877  constraints = sm_class_constraints (cls);
878  while (constraints != NULL)
879  {
880  if (constraints->func_index_info)
881  {
882  env->nsegs++;
883  }
884  constraints = constraints->next;
885  }
886  }
887  }
888 
889  if (is_dependent_table (entity))
890  {
891  env->nterms += env->nnodes;
892  }
893 
894  /* recurse and size the graph for path entities */
895  for (next_entity = entity->info.spec.path_entities; next_entity != NULL; next_entity = next_entity->next)
896  {
897  (void) graph_size_for_entity (env, next_entity);
898  }
899 
900  /* create a term for each conjunct in the entity's path_conjuncts */
901  for (conj = entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts; conj != NULL; conj = conj->next)
902  {
903  env->nterms++;
904  }
905 
906  /* reserve space for explicit join dummy term */
907  switch (entity->info.spec.join_type)
908  {
909  case PT_JOIN_INNER:
910  /* reserve dummy inner join term */
911  env->nterms++;
912  /* reserve additional always-false sarg */
913  env->nterms++;
914  break;
915  case PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER:
916  case PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER:
917  case PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER:
918  /* reserve dummy outer join term */
919  env->nterms++;
920  break;
921  default:
922  break;
923  }
924 
925 }
926 
927 /*
928  * build_query_graph () - This pre walk function will build the portion of the
929  * query graph for each entity in the entity_list (from list)
930  * return: PT_NODE *
931  * parser(in): parser environment
932  * tree(in): tree to walk
933  * arg(in):
934  * continue_walk(in):
935  */
936 static PT_NODE *
937 build_query_graph (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
938 {
939  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
940 
941  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
942 
943  /*
944  * skip nested selects, they've already been done and are
945  * constant with respect to the current select statement
946  */
947  if ((tree->node_type == PT_SELECT) && (tree != env->pt_tree))
948  {
949  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
950  return tree;
951  }
952 
953  /* if its not an entity_spec, we're not interested */
954  if (tree->node_type != PT_SPEC)
955  {
956  return tree;
957  }
958 
959  (void) build_graph_for_entity (env, tree, QO_BUILD_ENTITY);
960 
961  /* don't visit leaves of the entity, build_graph_for_entity already did */
962  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
963 
964  return tree;
965 }
966 
967 /*
968  * build_query_graph_post () - This post walk function will build the portion
969  * of the query graph for each path-entity in the entity_list (from list)
970  * return:
971  * parser(in): parser environment
972  * tree(in): tree to walk
973  * arg(in):
974  * continue_walk(in):
975  */
976 static PT_NODE *
977 build_query_graph_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
978 {
979  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
980 
981  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
982 
983  /* if its not an entity_spec, we're not interested */
984  if (tree->node_type != PT_SPEC)
985  {
986  return tree;
987  }
988 
989  (void) build_graph_for_entity (env, tree, QO_BUILD_PATH);
990 
991  return tree;
992 }
993 
994 /*
995  * build_query_graph_function_index () - This pre walk function will search the tree for expressions that match
996  * expressions used in function indexes.
997  * For such matched expressions, a corresponding segment is added to the query graph.
998  * return: PT_NODE *
999  * parser(in): parser environment
1000  * tree(in): tree to walk
1001  * arg(in):
1002  * continue_walk(in):
1003  */
1004 static PT_NODE *
1005 build_query_graph_function_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1006 {
1007  PT_NODE *entity = NULL;
1008  UINTPTR spec_id = 0;
1009  int i, k;
1010  MOP cls;
1011  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *constraints;
1012  QO_SEGMENT *seg;
1013  QO_NODE *node = NULL;
1014  QO_SEGMENT *seg_fi;
1015  const char *seg_name;
1016  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
1017 
1018  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1019 
1020  if (pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, tree, false))
1021  {
1022  if (!pt_is_join_expr (tree, &spec_id))
1023  {
1024  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
1025  {
1026  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
1027  entity = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
1028  if (entity->info.spec.id == spec_id)
1029  {
1030  break; /* found the node */
1031  }
1032  }
1033 
1034  if (entity != NULL && entity->info.spec.entity_name
1035  && ((cls = sm_find_class (entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original)) != NULL))
1036  {
1037  constraints = sm_class_constraints (cls);
1038  k = 0;
1039  while (constraints != NULL)
1040  {
1041  if (constraints->func_index_info)
1042  {
1043  char *expr_str = parser_print_function_index_expr (env->parser, tree);
1044 
1045  if (expr_str != NULL
1046  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (expr_str, constraints->func_index_info->expr_str))
1047  {
1048  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; i++)
1049  {
1050  seg_fi = QO_ENV_SEG (env, i);
1051  seg_name = QO_SEG_NAME (seg_fi);
1052  if ((QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (seg_fi) == true)
1053  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (seg_name, constraints->func_index_info->expr_str))
1054  {
1055  /* Also need to check whether the class alias names are matched. */
1056  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (node->class_name, QO_SEG_HEAD (seg_fi)->class_name))
1057  {
1058  /* segment already exists */
1059  break;
1060  }
1061  }
1062  }
1063  if (i == env->nsegs)
1064  {
1065  seg = qo_insert_segment (node, NULL, tree, env, expr_str);
1066  QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (seg) = true;
1067  QO_SEG_NAME (seg) = strdup (constraints->func_index_info->expr_str);
1068  if (QO_SEG_NAME (seg) == NULL)
1069  {
1070  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
1071  (size_t) (strlen (constraints->func_index_info->expr_str) + 1));
1072  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1073  return tree;
1074  }
1075  }
1076  }
1077  }
1078  constraints = constraints->next;
1079  k++;
1080  }
1081  }
1082  }
1083  }
1084  return tree;
1085 }
1086 
1087 /*
1088  * build_graph_for_entity () - This routine will create nodes and segments
1089  * based on the parse tree entity
1090  * return: QO_NODE *
1091  * env(in): optimizer environment
1092  * entity(in): entity to build the graph for
1093  * status(in):
1094  *
1095  * Note: Any changes made to this routine should be reflected in
1096  * graph_size_for_entity. They must remain in sync or else we might not
1097  * allocate enough space for the graph arrays resulting in memory
1098  * corruption.
1099  */
1100 static QO_NODE *
1101 build_graph_for_entity (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * entity, QO_BUILD_STATUS status)
1102 {
1103  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser;
1104  QO_NODE *node = NULL, *next_node;
1105  PT_NODE *name, *next_entity, *attr, *attr_list;
1106  QO_SEGMENT *seg;
1107  parser = QO_ENV_PARSER (env);
1108 
1109  if (!(status & QO_BUILD_ENTITY))
1110  {
1111  int i;
1112  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
1113  {
1114  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
1115  if (QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node) == entity)
1116  {
1117  break; /* found the node */
1118  }
1119  }
1120 
1121  goto build_path;
1122  }
1123 
1124  node = qo_add_node (entity, env);
1125 
1126  attr_list = get_referenced_attrs (entity);
1127 
1128  /*
1129  * Find the PT_NAME corresponding to this entity spec (i.e., the
1130  * PT_NODE that we want backing the oid segment we're about to
1131  * create), if such exists.
1132  */
1133 
1134  for (attr = attr_list; attr && !PT_IS_OID_NAME (attr); attr = attr->next)
1135  {
1136  ;
1137  }
1138 
1139  /*
1140  * 'attr' will be non-null iff the oid "attribute" of the class
1141  * is explicitly used in some way, e.g., in a comparison or a projection.
1142  * If it is non-null, it will be created with the rest of the symbols.
1143  *
1144  * If it is null, we'll make one unless we're dealing with a derived
1145  * table.
1146  */
1147  if (attr == NULL && entity->info.spec.derived_table == NULL && entity->info.spec.entity_name)
1148  {
1149  attr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
1150  if (attr == NULL)
1151  {
1152  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
1153  return NULL;
1154  }
1155 
1156  attr->info.name.resolved = entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.original;
1157  attr->info.name.original = "";
1158  attr->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
1159  attr->info.name.meta_class = PT_OID_ATTR;
1160 
1161  /* create oid segment for the entity */
1162  seg = qo_insert_segment (node, NULL, attr, env, NULL);
1163  QO_SEG_SET_VALUED (seg) = false; /* oid segments aren't set valued */
1164  QO_SEG_CLASS_ATTR (seg) = false; /* oid segments aren't class attrs */
1165  QO_SEG_SHARED_ATTR (seg) = false; /* oid segments aren't shared attrs */
1166  }
1167 
1168  /*
1169  * Create a segment for each symbol in the entities symbol table.
1170  */
1171  for (name = attr_list; name != NULL; name = name->next)
1172  {
1173  seg = qo_insert_segment (node, NULL, name, env, NULL);
1174 
1175  if ((name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SET) || (name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MULTISET)
1176  || (name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE))
1177  {
1178  QO_SEG_SET_VALUED (seg) = true;
1179  }
1180  else
1181  {
1182  QO_SEG_SET_VALUED (seg) = false;
1183  }
1184 
1185  if (name->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
1186  {
1187  QO_SEG_CLASS_ATTR (seg) = true;
1188  }
1189  else
1190  {
1191  QO_SEG_CLASS_ATTR (seg) = false;
1192  }
1193 
1194  /* this needs to check a flag Bill is going to add--CHECK!!!!! */
1195  QO_SEG_SHARED_ATTR (seg) = false;
1196  }
1197 
1198 build_path:
1199 
1200  if (!(status & QO_BUILD_PATH))
1201  {
1202  return node;
1203  }
1204 
1205  /* recurse and build the graph for path entities */
1206  for (next_entity = entity->info.spec.path_entities; next_entity != NULL; next_entity = next_entity->next)
1207  {
1208  next_node = build_graph_for_entity (env, next_entity, (QO_BUILD_STATUS) (QO_BUILD_ENTITY | QO_BUILD_PATH));
1209 
1210  /* for each path entity, fix the join segment */
1211  QO_ASSERT (env, next_node != NULL);
1212 
1213  /* make sure path entity contains the one and only path conjunct */
1214  QO_ASSERT (env, next_entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts != NULL);
1215  QO_ASSERT (env, next_entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts->next == NULL);
1216 
1217  (void) qo_join_segment (node, next_node, next_entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts->info.expr.arg1, env);
1218  }
1219 
1220  /* create a term for the entity's path_conjunct if one exists */
1221  if (entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts != NULL)
1222  {
1223  (void) qo_add_term (entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts, entity->info.spec.meta_class, env);
1224  }
1225 
1226  return node;
1227 }
1228 
1229 /*
1230  * qo_add_node () - This routine adds a node to the optimizer environment
1231  * for the entity
1232  * return: QO_NODE *
1233  * entity(in): entity to add node for
1234  * env(in): optimizer environment
1235  */
1236 static QO_NODE *
1237 qo_add_node (PT_NODE * entity, QO_ENV * env)
1238 {
1239  QO_NODE *node = NULL;
1240  QO_CLASS_INFO *info;
1241  int i, n;
1242  CLASS_STATS *stats;
1243 
1244  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nnodes < env->Nnodes);
1245  QO_ASSERT (env, entity != NULL);
1246  QO_ASSERT (env, entity->node_type == PT_SPEC);
1247 
1248  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, env->nnodes);
1249 
1250  /* fill in node */
1251  QO_NODE_ENV (node) = env;
1252  QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node) = entity;
1253  QO_NODE_NAME (node) = entity->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
1254  QO_NODE_IDX (node) = env->nnodes;
1255  QO_NODE_SORT_LIMIT_CANDIDATE (node) = false;
1256 
1257  env->nnodes++;
1258 
1259  /*
1260  * If derived table there will be no info. Also if derived table
1261  * that is correlated to the current scope level, establish
1262  * dependency links to all nodes that precede it in the scope. This
1263  * is overkill, but it's easier than figuring out the exact
1264  * information, and it's usually the same anyway.
1265  */
1266  if (!PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (entity) && !PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (entity) && (info = qo_get_class_info (env, node)) != NULL)
1267  {
1268  QO_NODE_INFO (node) = info;
1269  for (i = 0, n = info->n; i < n; i++)
1270  {
1271  stats = QO_GET_CLASS_STATS (&info->info[i]);
1272  QO_ASSERT (env, stats != NULL);
1273  if (entity->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS)
1274  {
1275  /* is class OID reference spec for example: 'class x' SELECT class_meth(class x, x.i) FROM x, class x */
1276  QO_NODE_NCARD (node) += 1;
1277  QO_NODE_TCARD (node) += 1;
1278  }
1279  else
1280  {
1281  QO_NODE_NCARD (node) += stats->heap_num_objects;
1282  QO_NODE_TCARD (node) += stats->heap_num_pages;
1283  }
1284  } /* for (i = ... ) */
1285  }
1286  else
1287  {
1288  QO_NODE_NCARD (node) = 5; /* just guess */
1289  QO_NODE_TCARD (node) = 1; /* just guess */
1290 
1291  /* recalculate derived table size */
1292  if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (entity))
1293  {
1294  XASL_NODE *xasl;
1295 
1296  switch (entity->info.spec.derived_table->node_type)
1297  {
1298  case PT_SELECT:
1299  case PT_UNION:
1300  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
1301  case PT_INTERSECTION:
1302  xasl = (XASL_NODE *) entity->info.spec.derived_table->info.query.xasl;
1303  if (xasl)
1304  {
1305  QO_NODE_NCARD (node) = (unsigned long) xasl->cardinality;
1306  QO_NODE_TCARD (node) =
1307  (unsigned long) ((QO_NODE_NCARD (node) * (double) xasl->projected_size) / (double) IO_PAGESIZE);
1308  if (QO_NODE_TCARD (node) == 0)
1309  {
1310  QO_NODE_TCARD (node) = 1;
1311  }
1312  }
1313  break;
1314  default:
1315  break;
1316  }
1317  }
1318  }
1319 
1320  n = QO_NODE_IDX (node);
1321  QO_NODE_SARGABLE (node) = true;
1322 
1323  switch (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node))
1324  {
1325  case PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER:
1326  QO_NODE_SARGABLE (QO_ENV_NODE (env, n - 1)) = false;
1327  break;
1328 
1329  case PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER:
1330  QO_NODE_SARGABLE (node) = false;
1331  break;
1332 
1333 /* currently, not used */
1334 /* case PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER:
1335  QO_NODE_SARGABLE(QO_ENV_NODE(env, n - 1)) = false;
1336  QO_NODE_SARGABLE(node) = false;
1337  break;
1338  */
1339  default:
1340  break;
1341  }
1342 
1343  return node;
1344 }
1345 
1346 /*
1347  * lookup_node () - looks up node in the node array, returns NULL if not found
1348  * return: Ptr to node in node table. If node is found, entity will be set
1349  * to point to the corresponding entity spec in the parse tree.
1350  * attr(in): class to look up
1351  * env(in): optimizer environment
1352  * entity(in): entity spec for the node
1353  */
1354 QO_NODE *
1355 lookup_node (PT_NODE * attr, QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE ** entity)
1356 {
1357  int i;
1358  bool found = false;
1359  PT_NODE *aux = attr;
1360 
1361  if (pt_is_function_index_expr (env->parser, attr, false))
1362  {
1363  /*
1364  * The node should be the same for each argument of expression =>
1365  * once found should be returned
1366  */
1367  QO_NODE *node = NULL;
1368  if (attr->info.expr.op == PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER)
1369  {
1370  PT_NODE *func = attr->info.expr.arg1;
1371  for (aux = func->info.function.arg_list; aux != NULL; aux = aux->next)
1372  {
1373  PT_NODE *save_aux = aux;
1374  aux = pt_function_index_skip_expr (aux);
1375  if (aux->node_type == PT_NAME)
1376  {
1377  node = lookup_node (aux, env, entity);
1378  if (node == NULL)
1379  {
1380  return NULL;
1381  }
1382  else
1383  {
1384  return node;
1385  }
1386  }
1387  aux = save_aux;
1388  }
1389  }
1390  else
1391  {
1392  aux = pt_function_index_skip_expr (attr->info.expr.arg1);
1393  if (aux)
1394  {
1395  if (aux->node_type == PT_NAME)
1396  {
1397  node = lookup_node (aux, env, entity);
1398  if (node == NULL)
1399  {
1400  return NULL;
1401  }
1402  else
1403  {
1404  return node;
1405  }
1406  }
1407  }
1408  aux = pt_function_index_skip_expr (attr->info.expr.arg2);
1409  if (aux)
1410  {
1411  if (aux->node_type == PT_NAME)
1412  {
1413  node = lookup_node (aux, env, entity);
1414  if (node == NULL)
1415  {
1416  return NULL;
1417  }
1418  else
1419  {
1420  return node;
1421  }
1422  }
1423  }
1424  aux = pt_function_index_skip_expr (attr->info.expr.arg3);
1425  if (aux)
1426  {
1427  if (aux->node_type == PT_NAME)
1428  {
1429  node = lookup_node (aux, env, entity);
1430  if (node == NULL)
1431  {
1432  return NULL;
1433  }
1434  else
1435  {
1436  return node;
1437  }
1438  }
1439  }
1440  }
1441  /* node is null at this point */
1442  return node;
1443  }
1444 
1445  QO_ASSERT (env, aux->node_type == PT_NAME);
1446 
1447  for (i = 0; (!found) && (i < env->nnodes); /* no increment step */ )
1448  {
1449  *entity = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (QO_ENV_NODE (env, i));
1450  if ((*entity)->info.spec.id == aux->info.name.spec_id)
1451  {
1452  found = true;
1453  }
1454  else
1455  {
1456  i++;
1457  }
1458  }
1459 
1460  return ((found) ? QO_ENV_NODE (env, i) : NULL);
1461 }
1462 
1463 /*
1464  * qo_insert_segment () - inserts a segment into the optimizer environment
1465  * return: QO_SEGMENT *
1466  * head(in): head of the segment
1467  * tail(in): tail of the segment
1468  * node(in): pt_node that gave rise to this segment
1469  * env(in): optimizer environment
1470  * expr_str(in): function index expression (if needed - NULL for a normal or
1471  * filter index
1472  */
1473 static QO_SEGMENT *
1474 qo_insert_segment (QO_NODE * head, QO_NODE * tail, PT_NODE * node, QO_ENV * env, const char *expr_str)
1475 {
1476  QO_SEGMENT *seg = NULL;
1477 
1478  QO_ASSERT (env, head != NULL);
1479  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nsegs < env->Nsegs);
1480 
1481  seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, env->nsegs);
1482 
1483  /* fill in seg */
1484  QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg) = node;
1485  QO_SEG_HEAD (seg) = head;
1486  QO_SEG_TAIL (seg) = tail;
1487  QO_SEG_IDX (seg) = env->nsegs;
1488  /* add dummy name to segment example: dummy attr from view transfrom select count(*) from v select count(*) from
1489  * (select {v}, 1 from t) v (v, 1) here, '1' is dummy attr set empty string to avoid core crash
1490  */
1491  if (node)
1492  {
1493  QO_SEG_NAME (seg) =
1494  node->info.name.original ? node->info.name.original : pt_append_string (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), NULL, "");
1495  if (PT_IS_OID_NAME (node))
1496  {
1497  /* this is an oid segment */
1498  QO_NODE_OID_SEG (head) = seg;
1499  QO_SEG_INFO (seg) = NULL;
1500  }
1501  else if (!PT_IS_CLASSOID_NAME (node))
1502  {
1503  /* Ignore CLASSOIDs. They are generated by updates on the server and can be treated as any other projected
1504  * column. We don't need to know anything else about this attr since it can not be used as an index or in
1505  * any other interesting way.
1506  */
1507  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME)
1508  {
1509  QO_SEG_INFO (seg) = qo_get_attr_info (env, seg);
1510  }
1511  else
1512  {
1513  QO_SEG_INFO (seg) = qo_get_attr_info_func_index (env, seg, expr_str);
1514  }
1515  }
1516  }
1517 
1518  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_SEGS (head)), QO_SEG_IDX (seg));
1519 
1520  env->nsegs++;
1521 
1522  return seg;
1523 }
1524 
1525 /*
1526  * qo_join_segment () - This routine will look for the segment and set its tail
1527  * to the correct node
1528  * return: QO_SEGMENT *
1529  * head(in): head of join segment
1530  * tail(in): tail of join segment
1531  * name(in): name of join segment
1532  * env(in): optimizer environment
1533  */
1534 static QO_SEGMENT *
1535 qo_join_segment (QO_NODE * head, QO_NODE * tail, PT_NODE * name, QO_ENV * env)
1536 {
1537  QO_SEGMENT *seg = NULL;
1538 
1539  seg = lookup_seg (head, name, env);
1540  QO_ASSERT (env, seg != NULL);
1541 
1542  QO_SEG_TAIL (seg) = tail; /* may be redundant */
1543 
1544  return seg;
1545 }
1546 
1547 /*
1548  * lookup_seg () -
1549  * return: ptr to segment in segment table, or NULL if the segment is not
1550  * in the table
1551  * head(in): head of the segment
1552  * name(in): name of the segment
1553  * env(in): optimizer environment
1554  */
1555 QO_SEGMENT *
1556 lookup_seg (QO_NODE * head, PT_NODE * name, QO_ENV * env)
1557 {
1558  int i;
1559  bool found = false;
1560 
1561  if (pt_is_function_index_expr (env->parser, name, false))
1562  {
1563  int k = -1;
1564  /* we search through the segments that come from a function index. If one of these are matched by the PT_NODE,
1565  * there is no need to search other segments, since they will never match
1566  */
1567  const char *expr_str = parser_print_function_index_expr (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), name);
1568 
1569  if (expr_str != NULL)
1570  {
1571  for (i = 0; (!found) && (i < env->nsegs); i++)
1572  {
1573  if (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i)) == false)
1574  {
1575  continue;
1576  }
1577 
1578  /* match function index expression against the expression in the given query */
1579  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_SEG_NAME (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i)), expr_str))
1580  {
1581  /* Also need to check whether the class alias names are matched. */
1582  if (head != NULL
1583  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (head->class_name, QO_SEG_HEAD (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i))->class_name))
1584  {
1585  found = true;
1586  k = i;
1587  }
1588  }
1589  }
1590  }
1591 
1592  return ((found) ? QO_ENV_SEG (env, k) : NULL);
1593  }
1594 
1595  for (i = 0; (!found) && (i < env->nsegs); /* no increment step */ )
1596  {
1597  if (QO_SEG_HEAD (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i)) == head
1598  && pt_name_equal (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), QO_SEG_PT_NODE (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i)), name))
1599  {
1600  found = true;
1601  }
1602  else
1603  {
1604  i++;
1605  }
1606  }
1607 
1608  return ((found) ? QO_ENV_SEG (env, i) : NULL);
1609 }
1610 
1611 /*
1612  * qo_add_final_segment () -
1613  * return: PT_NODE *
1614  * parser(in): parser environment
1615  * tree(in): tree to walk
1616  * arg(in):
1617  * continue_walk(in):
1618  *
1619  * Note: This walk "pre" function looks up the segment for each
1620  * node in the list. If the node is a PT_NAME node, it can use it to
1621  * find the final segment. If the node is a dot expression, the final
1622  * segment will be the segment associated with the PT_NAME node that is
1623  * arg2 of the dot expression.
1624  */
1625 static PT_NODE *
1626 qo_add_final_segment (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1627 {
1628  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
1629 
1630  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1631 
1632  if (tree->node_type == PT_NAME)
1633  {
1634  (void) set_seg_node (tree, env, &env->final_segs);
1635  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
1636  }
1637  else if ((tree->node_type == PT_DOT_))
1638  {
1639  (void) set_seg_node (tree->info.dot.arg2, env, &env->final_segs);
1640  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
1641  }
1642 
1643  return tree; /* don't alter tree structure */
1644 }
1645 
1646 /*
1647  * qo_add_term () - Creates a new term in the env term table
1648  * return: void
1649  * conjunct(in): term to add
1650  * term_type(in): is the term a path term?
1651  * env(in): optimizer environment
1652  */
1653 static QO_TERM *
1654 qo_add_term (PT_NODE * conjunct, int term_type, QO_ENV * env)
1655 {
1656  QO_TERM *term;
1657  QO_NODE *node;
1658 
1659  QO_ASSERT (env, conjunct->next == NULL);
1660 
1661  /* The conjuct could be PT_VALUE(0); (1) if an outer join condition was derived/transformed to the always-false ON
1662  * condition when type checking, expression evaluation or query rewrite transformation. We should sustained it for
1663  * correct outer join plan. It's different from ordinary WHERE condition. (2) Or is an always-false WHERE condition
1664  */
1665  QO_ASSERT (env, conjunct->node_type == PT_EXPR || conjunct->node_type == PT_VALUE);
1666  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nterms < env->Nterms);
1667 
1668  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, env->nterms);
1669 
1670  /* fill in term */
1671  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_SARG; /* assume sarg until proven otherwise */
1672  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = NO_JOIN;
1673  QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term) = conjunct;
1674  QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) =
1675  (conjunct->node_type == PT_EXPR ? conjunct->info.expr.location : conjunct->info.value.location);
1676  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 0.0;
1677  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = 0;
1678  QO_TERM_FLAG (term) = 0; /* init */
1679  QO_TERM_IDX (term) = env->nterms;
1680 
1681  env->nterms++;
1682 
1683  if (conjunct->node_type == PT_EXPR)
1684  {
1685  (void) qo_analyze_term (term, term_type);
1686  }
1687  else
1688  {
1689  /* conjunct->node_type == PT_VALUE */
1690  if (!pt_false_search_condition (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), conjunct))
1691  {
1692  /* is an always-true WHERE condition */
1693  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0;
1694  }
1695 
1696  if (conjunct->info.value.location == 0)
1697  {
1698  /* is an always-false WHERE condition */
1699  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_OTHER; /* is dummy */
1700  }
1701  else
1702  {
1703  /* Assume 'conjunct->info.value.location' is same to QO_NODE idx */
1704  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, conjunct->info.value.location);
1705  switch (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node))
1706  {
1707  case PT_JOIN_INNER:
1708  /* add always-false arg to each X, Y example: SELECT ... FROM X inner join Y on 0 <> 0; */
1709  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (node) - 1);
1710 
1711  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, env->nterms);
1712 
1713  /* fill in term */
1714  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_SARG;
1715  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = NO_JOIN;
1716  QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term) = conjunct;
1717  QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) = conjunct->info.value.location;
1718  if (!pt_false_search_condition (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), conjunct))
1719  {
1720  /* is an always-true WHERE condition */
1721  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0;
1722  }
1723  else
1724  {
1725  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 0.0;
1726  }
1727  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = 0;
1728  QO_TERM_FLAG (term) = 0; /* init */
1729  QO_TERM_IDX (term) = env->nterms;
1730 
1731  env->nterms++;
1732 
1733  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (node));
1734  break;
1735  case PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER:
1736  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (node));
1737  break;
1738  case PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER:
1739  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (node) - 1);
1740  break;
1741  case PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER: /* not used */
1742  /* I don't know what is to be done for full outer. */
1743  break;
1744  default:
1745  /* this should not happen */
1746  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (node));
1747  break;
1748  }
1749  } /* else */
1750  }
1751 
1752  return term;
1753 }
1754 
1755 /*
1756  * qo_add_dep_term () -
1757  * return: void
1758  * derived_node(in): The node representing the dependent derived table
1759  * depend_nodes(in):
1760  * depend_segs(in):
1761  * env(in): optimizer environment
1762  *
1763  * Note: Creates a new QO_TC_DEP_LINK term in the env term table, plus
1764  * QO_TC_DEP_JOIN terms as necessary. QO_TC_DEP_LINK terms are
1765  * used only to capture dependency information between a node
1766  * representing a dependent derived table and a node on which
1767  * that derived table depends.
1768  */
1769 static void
1770 qo_add_dep_term (QO_NODE * derived_node, BITSET * depend_nodes, BITSET * depend_segs, QO_ENV * env)
1771 {
1772  QO_TERM *term = NULL;
1773  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
1774  int ni, di;
1775 
1776  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nterms < env->Nterms);
1777 
1778  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, env->nterms);
1779 
1780  bitset_assign (&(QO_NODE_DEP_SET (derived_node)), depend_nodes);
1781 
1782  /* fill in term */
1783  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DEP_LINK;
1784  QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term) = NULL;
1785  QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) = 0;
1786  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0;
1787  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = 0;
1788  QO_TERM_FLAG (term) = 0;
1789  QO_TERM_IDX (term) = env->nterms;
1790  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
1791  /*
1792  * This is misleading if |depend_nodes| > 1, but the planner is the
1793  * only party relying on this information, and it understands the
1794  * rules of the game.
1795  */
1796  QO_TERM_HEAD (term) = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_first_member (depend_nodes));
1797  QO_TERM_TAIL (term) = derived_node;
1798 
1799  bitset_assign (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), depend_nodes);
1800  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (derived_node));
1801  bitset_assign (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)), depend_segs);
1802  /*
1803  * Add this term to env->fake_terms so that we're not tempted to sarg
1804  * it if a mergeable join term between these nodes is also present.
1805  * This is part of the fix for PR 7314.
1806  */
1807  bitset_add (&(env->fake_terms), QO_TERM_IDX (term));
1808 
1809  env->nterms++;
1810 
1811  ni = bitset_iterate (depend_nodes, &bi);
1812  while ((di = bitset_next_member (&bi)) != -1)
1813  {
1814  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nterms < env->Nterms);
1815  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, env->nterms);
1816  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DEP_JOIN;
1817  QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term) = NULL;
1818  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0;
1819  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = 0;
1820  QO_TERM_FLAG (term) = 0;
1821  QO_TERM_IDX (term) = env->nterms;
1822  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), ni);
1823  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), di);
1824  QO_TERM_HEAD (term) = QO_ENV_NODE (env, ni);
1825  QO_TERM_TAIL (term) = QO_ENV_NODE (env, di);
1826  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
1827  /*
1828  * Do NOT add these terms to env->fake_terms, because (unlike the
1829  * DEP_LINK terms) there is no restriction on how they can be
1830  * implemented (e.g., if there's a mergeable term available to
1831  * join the two nodes, it's ok to use it).
1832  */
1833  env->nterms++;
1834  }
1835 
1836 }
1837 
1838 /*
1839  * qo_add_dummy_join_term () - Make and add dummy join term if there's no explicit
1840  * join term related with given two nodes
1841  * return: void
1842  * env(in): optimizer environment
1843  * p_node(in):
1844  * on_node(in):
1845  */
1846 static QO_TERM *
1847 qo_add_dummy_join_term (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * p_node, QO_NODE * on_node)
1848 {
1849  QO_TERM *term;
1850 
1851  QO_ASSERT (env, env->nterms < env->Nterms);
1852  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (p_node) >= 0);
1853  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (p_node) + 1 == QO_NODE_IDX (on_node));
1854  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node) > 0);
1855 
1856  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, env->nterms);
1857 
1858  /* fill in term */
1859  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DUMMY_JOIN;
1860  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (p_node));
1861  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), QO_NODE_IDX (on_node));
1862  QO_TERM_HEAD (term) = p_node;
1863  QO_TERM_TAIL (term) = on_node;
1864  QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term) = NULL;
1865  QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) = QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node);
1866  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0;
1867  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = 0;
1868 
1869  switch (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node))
1870  {
1871  case PT_JOIN_INNER:
1872  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
1873  break;
1874  case PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER:
1875  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_LEFT;
1876  break;
1877  case PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER:
1878  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_RIGHT;
1879  break;
1880  case PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER: /* not used */
1881  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_OUTER;
1882  break;
1883  default:
1884  /* this should not happen */
1885  assert (false);
1886  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
1887  break;
1888  }
1889  QO_TERM_FLAG (term) = 0;
1890  QO_TERM_IDX (term) = env->nterms;
1891 
1892  env->nterms++;
1893 
1894  /* record outer join dependecy */
1895  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
1896  {
1897  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) == QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node));
1898 
1899  bitset_union (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (on_node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (p_node)));
1900  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (on_node)), QO_NODE_IDX (p_node));
1901  }
1902 
1903  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term) == 0);
1904 
1905  return term;
1906 }
1907 
1908 /*
1909  * qo_analyze_term () - determine the selectivity and class of the given term
1910  * return: void
1911  * term(in): term to analyze
1912  * term_type(in): predicate, path or selector path term
1913  */
1914 static void
1915 qo_analyze_term (QO_TERM * term, int term_type)
1916 {
1917  QO_ENV *env;
1918  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser;
1919  bool merge_applies;
1920  bool lhs_indexable, rhs_indexable;
1921  PT_NODE *pt_expr, *lhs_expr, *rhs_expr;
1922  QO_NODE *head_node = NULL, *tail_node = NULL;
1923  QO_SEGMENT *head_seg, *tail_seg;
1924  BITSET lhs_segs, rhs_segs, lhs_nodes, rhs_nodes;
1925  BITSET_ITERATOR iter;
1926  PT_OP_TYPE op_type = PT_AND;
1927  int i, n, t;
1928 
1929  env = QO_TERM_ENV (term);
1930 
1931  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) >= 0);
1932 
1933  parser = QO_ENV_PARSER (env);
1934  pt_expr = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term);
1935  merge_applies = true; /* until proven otherwise */
1936  lhs_indexable = rhs_indexable = false; /* until proven as indexable */
1937  lhs_expr = rhs_expr = NULL;
1938 
1939  bitset_init (&lhs_segs, env);
1940  bitset_init (&rhs_segs, env);
1941  bitset_init (&lhs_nodes, env);
1942  bitset_init (&rhs_nodes, env);
1943 
1944  if (pt_expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
1945  {
1946  goto wrapup;
1947  }
1948 
1949  /* only interesting in one predicate term; if 'term' has 'or_next', it was derived from OR term */
1950  /* also cases that are too complicated and unusual to consider here: (cond and/or cond) is true/false (cond and/or
1951  * cond) =/!= (cond and/or cond).
1952  */
1953  if (pt_expr->or_next == NULL && (pt_expr->info.expr.arg1 == NULL || pt_expr->info.expr.arg1->next == NULL)
1954  && (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2 == NULL || pt_expr->info.expr.arg2->next == NULL))
1955  {
1956  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_SINGLE_PRED);
1957 
1958  op_type = pt_expr->info.expr.op;
1959  switch (op_type)
1960  {
1961 
1962  /* operators classified as lhs- and rhs-indexable */
1963  case PT_EQ:
1964  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP);
1965  case PT_LT:
1966  case PT_LE:
1967  case PT_GT:
1968  case PT_GE:
1969  /* temporary guess; RHS could be a indexable segment */
1970  rhs_indexable = true;
1971  /* no break; fall through */
1972 
1973  /* operators classified as rhs-indexable */
1974  case PT_BETWEEN:
1975  case PT_RANGE:
1976  if (op_type == PT_RANGE)
1977  {
1978  assert (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2 != NULL);
1979 
1980  if (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2)
1981  {
1982  PT_NODE *between_and;
1983 
1984  between_and = pt_expr->info.expr.arg2;
1985  if (between_and->or_next)
1986  {
1987  /* is RANGE (r1, r2, ...) */
1988  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_RANGELIST);
1989  }
1990 
1991  for (; between_and; between_and = between_and->or_next)
1992  {
1993  if (between_and->info.expr.op != PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA)
1994  {
1995  break;
1996  }
1997  }
1998 
1999  if (between_and == NULL)
2000  {
2001  /* All ranges are EQ */
2002  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP);
2003  }
2004  }
2005  }
2006  case PT_IS_IN:
2007  case PT_EQ_SOME:
2008  /* temporary guess; LHS could be a indexable segment */
2009  lhs_indexable = true;
2010  /* no break; fall through */
2011 
2012  /* operators classified as not-indexable */
2013  case PT_NOT_BETWEEN:
2014  case PT_IS_NOT_IN:
2015  case PT_GE_SOME:
2016  case PT_GT_SOME:
2017  case PT_LT_SOME:
2018  case PT_LE_SOME:
2019  case PT_EQ_ALL:
2020  case PT_GE_ALL:
2021  case PT_GT_ALL:
2022  case PT_LT_ALL:
2023  case PT_LE_ALL:
2024  case PT_NE:
2025  case PT_SETEQ:
2026  case PT_SETNEQ:
2027  case PT_SUPERSETEQ:
2028  case PT_SUPERSET:
2029  case PT_SUBSET:
2030  case PT_SUBSETEQ:
2031  case PT_NE_SOME:
2032  case PT_NE_ALL:
2033  case PT_LIKE:
2034  case PT_NOT_LIKE:
2035  case PT_RLIKE:
2036  case PT_NOT_RLIKE:
2037  case PT_RLIKE_BINARY:
2038  case PT_NOT_RLIKE_BINARY:
2039  case PT_NULLSAFE_EQ:
2040  /* RHS of the expression */
2041  rhs_expr = pt_expr->info.expr.arg2;
2042  /* get segments from RHS of the expression */
2043  qo_expr_segs (env, rhs_expr, &rhs_segs);
2044  /* no break; fall through */
2045 
2046  case PT_IS_NULL:
2047  case PT_IS_NOT_NULL:
2048  case PT_EXISTS:
2049  case PT_IS:
2050  case PT_IS_NOT:
2051  /* LHS of the expression */
2052  lhs_expr = pt_expr->info.expr.arg1;
2053  /* get segments from LHS of the expression */
2054  qo_expr_segs (env, lhs_expr, &lhs_segs);
2055  /* now break switch statement */
2056  break;
2057 
2058  case PT_OR:
2059  case PT_NOT:
2060  case PT_XOR:
2061  /* get segments from the expression itself */
2062  qo_expr_segs (env, pt_expr, &lhs_segs);
2063  break;
2064 
2065  /* the other operators that can not be used as term; error case */
2066  default:
2067  /* stop processing */
2068  QO_ABORT (env);
2069 
2070  } /* switch (op_type) */
2071  }
2072  else
2073  { /* if (pt_expr->or_next == NULL) */
2074  /* term that consist of more than one predicates; do same as PT_OR */
2075 
2076  qo_expr_segs (env, pt_expr, &lhs_segs);
2077 
2078  } /* if (pt_expr->or_next == NULL) */
2079 
2080  /* get nodes from segments */
2081  qo_seg_nodes (env, &lhs_segs, &lhs_nodes);
2082  qo_seg_nodes (env, &rhs_segs, &rhs_nodes);
2083 
2084  /* do LHS and RHS of the term belong to the different node? */
2085  if (!bitset_intersects (&lhs_nodes, &rhs_nodes))
2086  {
2087  i = 0; /* idx of term->index_seg[] array; it shall be 0 or 1 */
2088 
2089  /* There terms look like they might be candidates for implementation via indexes. Make sure that they really are
2090  * candidates. IMPORTANT: this is not the final say, since we don't know at this point whether indexes actually
2091  * exist or not. We won't know that until a later phase (qo_discover_indexes()). Right now we're just determining
2092  * whether these terms qualify structurally.
2093  */
2094 
2095  /* examine if LHS is indexable or not? */
2096 
2097  /* is LHS a type of name(attribute) of local database */
2098  if (lhs_indexable)
2099  {
2100  if (is_local_name (env, lhs_expr))
2101  {
2102  if (lhs_expr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
2103  {
2104  /* lhs is indexable only if this is an equality comparison */
2105  op_type = pt_expr->info.expr.op;
2106  switch (op_type)
2107  {
2108  case PT_EQ:
2109  case PT_IS_IN:
2110  case PT_EQ_SOME:
2111  case PT_NULLSAFE_EQ:
2112  break;
2113  case PT_RANGE:
2114  if (!QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP))
2115  {
2116  lhs_indexable = false;
2117  }
2118  break;
2119  default:
2120  lhs_indexable = false;
2121  break;
2122  }
2123  }
2124  else
2125  {
2126  lhs_indexable = true;
2127  }
2128  }
2129  else
2130  {
2131  lhs_indexable = false;
2132  }
2133  }
2134  if (lhs_indexable
2135  && (pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, lhs_expr, false)
2136  || (lhs_expr && lhs_expr->info.expr.op == PT_PRIOR
2137  && pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, lhs_expr->info.expr.arg1, false))))
2138  {
2139  /* we should be dealing with a function indexable expression, so we must check if a segment has been
2140  * associated with it
2141  */
2142  n = bitset_first_member (&lhs_segs);
2143  if ((n == -1) || (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (QO_ENV_SEG (env, n)) == false))
2144  {
2145  lhs_indexable = false;
2146  }
2147  }
2148  if (lhs_indexable && rhs_expr->next == NULL)
2149  {
2150 
2151  if (op_type == PT_IS_IN || op_type == PT_EQ_SOME)
2152  {
2153  /* We have to be careful with this case because "i IN (SELECT ...)" has a special meaning: in this case
2154  * the select is treated as UNBOX_AS_TABLE instead of the usual UNBOX_AS_VALUE, and we can't use an index
2155  * even if we want to (because of an XASL deficiency).Because pt_is_pseudo_const() wants to believe that
2156  * subqueries are pseudo-constants, we have to check for that condition outside of pt_is_pseudo_const().
2157  */
2158  switch (rhs_expr->node_type)
2159  {
2160  case PT_SELECT:
2161  case PT_UNION:
2162  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
2163  case PT_INTERSECTION:
2164  lhs_indexable = false;
2165  break;
2166  case PT_NAME:
2167  if (rhs_expr->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER && pt_is_set_type (rhs_expr))
2168  {
2169  lhs_indexable = false;
2170  }
2171  break;
2172  case PT_DOT_:
2173  if (pt_is_set_type (rhs_expr))
2174  {
2175  lhs_indexable = false;
2176  }
2177  break;
2178  case PT_VALUE:
2179  if (op_type == PT_EQ_SOME && rhs_expr->info.value.db_value_is_initialized
2180  && db_value_type_is_collection (&(rhs_expr->info.value.db_value)))
2181  {
2182  /* if we have the = some{} operator check its size */
2183  DB_COLLECTION *db_collectionp = db_get_collection (&(rhs_expr->info.value.db_value));
2184 
2185  if (db_col_size (db_collectionp) == 0)
2186  {
2187  lhs_indexable = false;
2188  }
2189  }
2190  lhs_indexable = lhs_indexable && pt_is_pseudo_const (rhs_expr);
2191  break;
2192  default:
2193  lhs_indexable = lhs_indexable && pt_is_pseudo_const (rhs_expr);
2194  }
2195  }
2196  else
2197  {
2198  /* is LHS attribute and is RHS constant value ? */
2199  lhs_indexable = lhs_indexable && pt_is_pseudo_const (rhs_expr);
2200  }
2201  }
2202 
2203  /* check LHS and RHS for collations that invalidate the term's use in a key range/filter; if one of the expr
2204  * sides contains such a collation then the whole term is not indexable */
2205  if (lhs_indexable || rhs_indexable)
2206  {
2207  int has_nis_coll = 0;
2208 
2209  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, lhs_expr, pt_has_non_idx_sarg_coll_pre, &has_nis_coll, NULL, NULL);
2210  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, rhs_expr, pt_has_non_idx_sarg_coll_pre, &has_nis_coll, NULL, NULL);
2211 
2212  if (has_nis_coll)
2213  {
2214  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_NON_IDX_SARG_COLL);
2215  lhs_indexable = false;
2216  rhs_indexable = false;
2217  }
2218  }
2219 
2220  if (lhs_indexable)
2221  {
2222  n = bitset_first_member (&lhs_segs);
2223  if (n != -1)
2224  {
2225  /* record in the term that it has indexable segment as LHS */
2226  term->index_seg[i++] = QO_ENV_SEG (env, n);
2227  }
2228  }
2229 
2230  /* examine if LHS is indexable or not? */
2231  if (rhs_indexable)
2232  {
2233  if (is_local_name (env, rhs_expr) && pt_is_pseudo_const (lhs_expr))
2234  {
2235  /* is RHS attribute and is LHS constant value ? */
2236  if (rhs_expr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
2237  {
2238  /* lhs is indexable only if this is an equality comparison */
2239  op_type = pt_expr->info.expr.op;
2240  switch (op_type)
2241  {
2242  case PT_EQ:
2243  case PT_IS_IN:
2244  case PT_EQ_SOME:
2245  case PT_NULLSAFE_EQ:
2246  break;
2247  case PT_RANGE:
2248  if (!QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP))
2249  {
2250  rhs_indexable = false;
2251  }
2252  break;
2253  default:
2254  rhs_indexable = false;
2255  break;
2256  }
2257  }
2258  else
2259  {
2260  rhs_indexable = true;
2261  }
2262  }
2263  else
2264  {
2265  rhs_indexable = false;
2266  }
2267  }
2268  if (rhs_indexable
2269  && (pt_is_function_index_expr (term->env->parser, rhs_expr, false)
2270  || (rhs_expr && rhs_expr->info.expr.op == PT_PRIOR
2271  && pt_is_function_index_expr (term->env->parser, rhs_expr->info.expr.arg1, false))))
2272  {
2273  /* we should be dealing with a function indexable expression, so we must check if a segment has been
2274  * associated with it
2275  */
2276  n = bitset_first_member (&rhs_segs);
2277  if ((n == -1) || (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (QO_ENV_SEG (env, n)) == false))
2278  {
2279  rhs_indexable = false;
2280  }
2281  }
2282  if (rhs_indexable)
2283  {
2284  if (!lhs_indexable)
2285  {
2286  op_type = pt_converse_op (op_type);
2287  if (op_type != 0)
2288  {
2289  /* converse 'const op attr' to 'attr op const' */
2290  PT_NODE *tmp;
2291 
2292  tmp = pt_expr->info.expr.arg2;
2293  pt_expr->info.expr.arg2 = pt_expr->info.expr.arg1;
2294  pt_expr->info.expr.arg1 = tmp;
2295  pt_expr->info.expr.op = op_type;
2296  }
2297  else
2298  {
2299  /* must be impossible error. check pt_converse_op() */
2300  QO_ABORT (env);
2301  }
2302  }
2303 
2304  n = bitset_first_member (&rhs_segs);
2305  if (n != -1)
2306  {
2307  /* record in the term that it has indexable segment as RHS */
2308  term->index_seg[i++] = QO_ENV_SEG (env, n);
2309  }
2310  } /* if (rhs_indexable) */
2311 
2312 
2313  QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term) = i; /* cardinality of term->index_seg[] array */
2314 
2315  }
2316  else
2317  { /* if (!bitset_intersects(&lhs_nodes, &rhs_nodes)) */
2318 
2319  merge_applies = false;
2320  QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term) = 0;
2321 
2322  } /* if (!bitset_intersects(&lhs_nodes, &rhs_nodes)) */
2323 
2324 
2325  /* fill in segment and node information of QO_TERM structure */
2326  bitset_assign (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)), &lhs_segs);
2327  bitset_union (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)), &rhs_segs);
2328  bitset_assign (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &lhs_nodes);
2329  bitset_union (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &rhs_nodes);
2330 
2331  /* number of nodes with which this term associated */
2332  n = bitset_cardinality (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)));
2333  /* determine the class of the term */
2334  if (term_type != PREDICATE_TERM)
2335  {
2336  QO_ASSERT (env, n >= 2);
2337 
2338  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_PATH;
2339 
2340  if (n == 2)
2341  {
2342  /* i.e., it's a path term... In this case, it's imperative that we get the head and tail nodes and segs
2343  * right. Fortunately, in this particular case we can rely on the compiler to produce the term in a
2344  * consistent way, with the head on the lhs and the tail on the rhs.
2345  */
2346  head_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_first_member (&lhs_nodes));
2347  tail_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_first_member (&rhs_nodes));
2348 
2349  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (head_node) < QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node));
2350  }
2351  }
2352  else if (n == 0)
2353  {
2354  bool inst_num = false;
2355 
2356  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, pt_expr, pt_check_instnum_pre, NULL, pt_check_instnum_post, &inst_num);
2357  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = inst_num ? QO_TC_TOTALLY_AFTER_JOIN : QO_TC_OTHER;
2358  }
2359  else if (n == 1)
2360  {
2361  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_SARG;
2362 
2363  /* QO_NODE to which this sarg term belongs */
2364  head_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &iter));
2365  }
2366  else if (n == 2)
2367  {
2368  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_JOIN;
2369 
2370  /* Although it may be tempting to say that the head node is the first member of the lhs_nodes and the tail node
2371  * is the first member of the rhs_nodes, that's not always true. For example, a term like "x.a + y.b < 100" can
2372  * get in here, and then *both* head and tail are in lhs_nodes. If you get down into the code guarded by
2373  * 'merge_applies' you can safely make more stringent assumptions, but not before then.
2374  */
2375 
2376  head_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &iter));
2377  tail_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_next_member (&iter));
2378 
2379  if (QO_NODE_IDX (head_node) > QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node))
2380  {
2381  QO_NODE *swap_node = NULL;
2382 
2383  swap_node = head_node;
2384  head_node = tail_node;
2385  tail_node = swap_node;
2386  }
2387  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (head_node) < QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node));
2388  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node) > 0);
2389  }
2390  else
2391  { /* n >= 3 */
2392  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_OTHER;
2393  }
2394 
2395  if (n == 2)
2396  {
2397  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_PATH || QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN);
2398 
2399  /* This is a pretty weak test; it only looks for equality comparisons. */
2400  merge_applies &= expr_is_mergable (pt_expr);
2401 
2402  /* check for dependent edge. do not join with it */
2403  if (BITSET_MEMBER (QO_NODE_DEP_SET (head_node), QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node))
2404  || BITSET_MEMBER (QO_NODE_DEP_SET (tail_node), QO_NODE_IDX (head_node)))
2405  {
2406  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_OTHER;
2407 
2408  merge_applies = false;
2409  }
2410 
2411  /* And there had better be something on both sides of the comparison too. You don't want to be misled by
2412  * something like "x.a + y.b = 100" because that's definitely not mergeable right now. Perhaps if we rewrote it
2413  * like "x.a = 100 - y.b" but that seems to be stretching things a little bit.
2414  */
2415  merge_applies = merge_applies && (!bitset_is_empty (&lhs_segs) && !bitset_is_empty (&rhs_segs));
2416 
2417  if (merge_applies || QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_PATH)
2418  {
2419  head_seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)), &iter));
2420  for (t = bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)), &iter); t != -1; t = bitset_next_member (&iter))
2421  {
2422  tail_seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, t);
2423  if (QO_NODE_IDX (QO_SEG_HEAD (tail_seg)) != QO_NODE_IDX (QO_SEG_HEAD (head_seg)))
2424  {
2425  break; /* found tail */
2426  }
2427  }
2428 
2429  /* Now make sure that the head and tail segs correspond to the proper nodes. */
2430  if (QO_SEG_HEAD (head_seg) != head_node)
2431  {
2432  QO_SEGMENT *swap_seg = NULL;
2433 
2434  swap_seg = head_seg;
2435  head_seg = tail_seg;
2436  tail_seg = swap_seg;
2437  }
2438 
2439  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_SEG_HEAD (head_seg) == head_node);
2440  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_SEG_HEAD (tail_seg) == tail_node);
2441 
2442  /* These are really only interesting for path terms, but it doesn't hurt to set them for others too. */
2443  QO_TERM_SEG (term) = head_seg;
2444  QO_TERM_OID_SEG (term) = tail_seg;
2445 
2446  /* The term might be a merge term (i.e., it uses '=' as the operator), but the expressions might not be
2447  * simple attribute references, and we mustn't try to establish equivalence classes in that case.
2448  */
2449  if (qo_is_equi_join_term (term))
2450  {
2451  qo_equivalence (head_seg, tail_seg);
2452  QO_TERM_NOMINAL_SEG (term) = head_seg;
2453  }
2454  }
2455 
2456  /* always true transitive equi-join term is not suitable as m-join edge. */
2457  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (pt_expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_TRANSITIVE))
2458  {
2459  merge_applies = false;
2460  }
2461 
2462  if (merge_applies)
2463  {
2464  QO_TERM_SET_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE);
2465  }
2466 
2467  /* Now make sure that the two (node) ends of the join get cached in the term structure. */
2468  QO_TERM_HEAD (term) = head_node;
2469  QO_TERM_TAIL (term) = tail_node;
2470 
2471  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_HEAD (term)) < QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)));
2472  }
2473 
2474  if (n == 1)
2475  {
2476  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_SARG);
2477  }
2478 
2479  /* classify TC_JOIN term for outer join and determine its join type */
2480  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN)
2481  {
2482  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (head_node) < QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node));
2483 
2484  /* inner join until proven otherwise */
2485  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
2486 
2487  /* check iff explicit join term */
2488  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
2489  {
2490  QO_NODE *on_node;
2491 
2492  on_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term));
2493  QO_ASSERT (env, on_node != NULL);
2494  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (on_node) > 0);
2495  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node) > 0);
2496 
2497  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) == QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node));
2498 
2499  if (QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node) == QO_NODE_IDX (on_node))
2500  {
2501  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (head_node) < QO_NODE_LOCATION (tail_node));
2502  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (tail_node) > 0);
2503 
2504  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER)
2505  {
2506  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_LEFT;
2507  }
2508  else if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER)
2509  {
2510  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_RIGHT;
2511  }
2512  else if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
2513  { /* not used */
2514  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_OUTER;
2515  }
2516 
2517  /* record explicit join dependecy */
2518  bitset_union (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (on_node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (head_node)));
2519  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (on_node)), QO_NODE_IDX (head_node));
2520  }
2521  else
2522  {
2523  /* is not valid explicit join term */
2524  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_OTHER;
2525 
2526  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = NO_JOIN;
2527 
2528  /* keep out from m-join edge */
2529  QO_TERM_CLEAR_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE);
2530  }
2531  }
2532  else
2533  {
2534  QO_NODE *node;
2535 
2536  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
2537  {
2538  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
2539 
2540  if (QO_NODE_IDX (node) >= QO_NODE_IDX (head_node) && QO_NODE_IDX (node) < QO_NODE_IDX (tail_node))
2541  {
2542  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
2543  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER
2544  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
2545  {
2546  /* record explicit join dependecy */
2547  bitset_union (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)));
2548  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), QO_NODE_IDX (node));
2549  }
2550  }
2551  }
2552  } /* else */
2553  }
2554 
2555 wrapup:
2556 
2557  /* A negative selectivity means that the cardinality of the result depends only on the cardinality of the head, not
2558  * on the product of the cardinalities of the head and the tail as in the usual case.
2559  */
2560  switch (term_type)
2561  {
2562  case PT_PATH_INNER:
2563  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
2564  if (QO_NODE_NCARD (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)) == 0)
2565  {
2566  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 0.0;
2567  }
2568  else
2569  {
2570  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = 1.0 / QO_NODE_NCARD (QO_TERM_TAIL (term));
2571  }
2572  break;
2573 
2574  case PT_PATH_OUTER:
2575  {
2576  QO_TERM *t_term;
2577  QO_NODE *t_node;
2578 
2579  /* Traverse previously generated terms */
2580  for (t = 0; t < env->nterms - 1; t++)
2581  {
2582 
2583  t_term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t);
2584 
2585  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (t_term) == QO_TC_PATH && QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (t_term) == JOIN_LEFT)
2586  {
2587  if (head_node == NULL)
2588  {
2589  break;
2590  }
2591 
2592  if ((QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_HEAD (t_term)) == QO_NODE_IDX (head_node))
2593  || (QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_TAIL (t_term)) == QO_NODE_IDX (head_node)))
2594  {
2595  /* found previously generated head_nodes's path-term */
2596 
2597  /* get tail node */
2598  t_node = QO_TERM_TAIL (t_term);
2599 
2600  /* apply ordered dependency to the tail node */
2601  bitset_union (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (t_node)));
2602  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), QO_NODE_IDX (t_node));
2603  }
2604  }
2605  }
2606  }
2607  /* FALL THROUGH */
2608  case PT_PATH_OUTER_WEASEL:
2609  /* These can't be implemented with index scans regardless because an index scan won't properly implement the
2610  * left-outer semantics of the path...
2611  */
2612  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_LEFT;
2613  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = -1.0;
2614  QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term) = 0;
2615 
2616  /* For term_type is PT_PATH_OUTER_WEASEL, order dependency is needed. i.e. it's a path term. */
2617  if (term_type == PT_PATH_OUTER_WEASEL && head_node != NULL && tail_node != NULL)
2618  {
2619  assert (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_PATH);
2620 
2621  bitset_union (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (head_node)));
2622  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (tail_node)), QO_NODE_IDX (head_node));
2623  }
2624  break;
2625 
2626  case PREDICATE_TERM:
2627  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = qo_expr_selectivity (env, pt_expr);
2628  break;
2629 
2630  default:
2631  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = JOIN_INNER;
2632  QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term) = -1.0;
2633  break;
2634  } /* switch (term_type) */
2635 
2636  bitset_delset (&lhs_segs);
2637  bitset_delset (&rhs_segs);
2638  bitset_delset (&lhs_nodes);
2639  bitset_delset (&rhs_nodes);
2640 }
2641 
2642 /*
2643  * qo_expr_segs () - Returns a bitset encoding all of the join graph segments
2644  * used in the pt_expr
2645  * return: BITSET
2646  * env(in):
2647  * pt_expr(in): pointer to a conjunct
2648  * result(out): BITSET of join segments (OUTPUT PARAMETER)
2649  */
2650 void
2651 qo_expr_segs (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * pt_expr, BITSET * result)
2652 {
2653  PT_NODE *next;
2654 
2655  if (pt_expr == NULL)
2656  {
2657  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FAILED_ASSERTION, 1, "pt_expr != NULL");
2658  return;
2659  }
2660 
2661  /* remember the next link and then break it */
2662  next = pt_expr->next;
2663  pt_expr->next = NULL;
2664 
2665  /* use env to get the bitset to the walk functions */
2666  QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env) = result;
2667 
2668  (void) parser_walk_tree (env->parser, pt_expr, set_seg_expr, &env, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2669 
2670  /* recover the next link */
2671  pt_expr->next = next;
2672 
2673  /* reset the temp pointer so we don't have a dangler */
2674  QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env) = NULL;
2675 }
2676 
2677 /*
2678  * set_seg_expr () -
2679  * return: PT_NODE *
2680  * parser(in): parser environment
2681  * tree(in): tree to walk
2682  * arg(in):
2683  * continue_walk(in):
2684  *
2685  * Note: This walk "pre" function will set a bit in the bitset for
2686  * each segment associated with the PT_NAME node.
2687  */
2688 static PT_NODE *
2689 set_seg_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
2690 {
2691  QO_ENV *env = *(QO_ENV **) arg;
2692 
2693  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
2694 
2695  /*
2696  * Make sure we check all subqueries for embedded references. This
2697  * stuff really ought to all be done in one pass.
2698  */
2699  switch (tree->node_type)
2700  {
2701  case PT_SPEC:
2702  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.spec.derived_table, set_seg_expr, arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2703  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2704  break;
2705 
2706  case PT_NAME:
2707  (void) set_seg_node (tree, env, QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env));
2708  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2709  break;
2710 
2711  case PT_DOT_:
2712  (void) set_seg_node (tree->info.dot.arg2, env, QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env));
2713  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2714  break;
2715 
2716  case PT_EXPR:
2717  if (tree->info.expr.op == PT_SYS_CONNECT_BY_PATH || tree->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ROOT
2718  || tree->info.expr.op == PT_PRIOR)
2719  {
2720  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2721  }
2722  if (pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, tree, false))
2723  {
2724  int count_bits = bitset_cardinality (QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env));
2725  (void) set_seg_node (tree, env, QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env));
2726  if (bitset_cardinality (QO_ENV_TMP_BITSET (env)) - count_bits > 0)
2727  {
2728  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2729  }
2730  }
2731 
2732  break;
2733 
2734  default:
2735  break;
2736  }
2737 
2738  return tree; /* don't alter tree structure */
2739 }
2740 
2741 /*
2742  * set_seg_node () -
2743  * return: nothing
2744  * attr(in): attribute to set the seg for
2745  * env(in): optimizer environment
2746  * bitset(in): bitset in which to set the bit for the segment
2747  */
2748 static void
2749 set_seg_node (PT_NODE * attr, QO_ENV * env, BITSET * bitset)
2750 {
2751  QO_NODE *node;
2752  QO_SEGMENT *seg;
2753  PT_NODE *entity;
2754 
2755  node = lookup_node (attr, env, &entity);
2756 
2757  /* node will be null if this attr resolves to an enclosing scope */
2758  if (node != NULL && (seg = lookup_seg (node, attr, env)) != NULL)
2759  {
2760  /*
2761  * lookup_seg() really shouldn't ever fail here, but it used to
2762  * for shared variables, and it doesn't really hurt anyone just
2763  * to ignore failures here.
2764  */
2765  bitset_add (bitset, QO_SEG_IDX (seg));
2766  }
2767 
2768 }
2769 
2770 /*
2771  * expr_is_mergable () - Test if the pt_expr is an equi-join conjunct
2772  * return: bool
2773  * pt_expr(in):
2774  */
2775 static bool
2776 expr_is_mergable (PT_NODE * pt_expr)
2777 {
2778  if (pt_expr->or_next == NULL)
2779  { /* keep out OR conjunct */
2780  if (!pt_is_query (pt_expr->info.expr.arg1) && !pt_is_query (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2))
2781  {
2782  if (pt_expr->info.expr.op == PT_EQ)
2783  {
2784  return true;
2785  }
2786  else if (pt_expr->info.expr.op == PT_RANGE)
2787  {
2788  PT_NODE *between_and;
2789 
2790  between_and = pt_expr->info.expr.arg2;
2791  if (between_and->or_next == NULL /* has only one range */
2792  && between_and->info.expr.op == PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA)
2793  {
2794  return true;
2795  }
2796  }
2797  }
2798  }
2799 
2800  return false;
2801 }
2802 
2803 /*
2804  * qo_is_equi_join_term () - Test if the term is an equi-join conjunct whose
2805  * left and right sides are simple attribute references
2806  * return: bool
2807  * term(in):
2808  */
2809 static bool
2810 qo_is_equi_join_term (QO_TERM * term)
2811 {
2812  PT_NODE *pt_expr;
2813  PT_NODE *rhs_expr;
2814 
2815  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_SINGLE_PRED) && QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP))
2816  {
2817  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_RANGELIST))
2818  {
2819  /* keep out OR conjunct */
2820  return false;
2821  }
2822 
2823  pt_expr = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term);
2824  if (pt_is_attr (pt_expr->info.expr.arg1))
2825  {
2826  rhs_expr = pt_expr->info.expr.arg2;
2827  if (pt_expr->info.expr.op == PT_RANGE)
2828  {
2829  assert (rhs_expr->info.expr.op == PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA);
2830  assert (rhs_expr->or_next == NULL);
2831  /* has only one range */
