2832  rhs_expr = rhs_expr->info.expr.arg1;
2833  }
2834 
2835  return pt_is_attr (rhs_expr);
2836  }
2837  }
2838 
2839  return false;
2840 }
2841 
2842 /*
2843  * is_dependent_table () - Returns true iff the tree represents a dependent
2844  * derived table for this query
2845  * return: bool
2846  * entity(in): entity spec for a from list entry
2847  */
2848 static bool
2849 is_dependent_table (PT_NODE * entity)
2850 {
2851  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table)
2852  {
2853  /* this test is too pessimistic. The argument must depend on a previous entity spec in the from list.
2854  * >>>> FIXME some day <<<<
2855  */
2856  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SET_EXPR /* is cselect derived table of method */
2857  || entity->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_CSELECT
2858  || entity->info.spec.derived_table->info.query.correlation_level == 1)
2859  {
2860  return true;
2861  }
2862  }
2863 
2864  return false;
2865 }
2866 
2867 /*
2868  * get_term_subqueries () - walks the expression to see whether it contains any
2869  * correlated subqueries. If so, it records the
2870  * identity of the containing term in the subquery
2871  * structure
2872  * return:
2873  * env(in): optimizer environment
2874  * term(in):
2875  */
2876 static void
2877 get_term_subqueries (QO_ENV * env, QO_TERM * term)
2878 {
2879  PT_NODE *pt_expr, *next;
2880  WALK_INFO info;
2881 
2882  if (QO_IS_FAKE_TERM (term))
2883  {
2884  /*
2885  * This is a pseudo-term introduced to keep track of derived
2886  * table dependencies. If the dependent derived table is based
2887  * on a subquery, we need to find that subquery and record it in
2888  * the pseudo-term.
2889  */
2890  pt_expr = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (QO_TERM_TAIL (term));
2891  }
2892  else
2893  {
2894  /*
2895  * This is a normal term, and we need to find all of the
2896  * correlated subqueries contained within it.
2897  */
2898  pt_expr = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term);
2899  }
2900 
2901  /*
2902  * This should only happen for dependent derived tables, either those
2903  * based on a set or when checking out QO_TC_DEP_JOIN terms
2904  * introduced for ddt's that depend on more than one thing.
2905  */
2906  if (pt_expr == NULL)
2907  {
2908  return;
2909  }
2910 
2911  next = pt_expr->next;
2912  pt_expr->next = NULL;
2913 
2914  info.env = env;
2915  info.term = term;
2916 
2917  (void) parser_walk_tree (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), pt_expr, check_subquery_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2918 
2919  pt_expr->next = next;
2920 
2921 }
2922 
2923 /*
2924  * get_opcode_rank () -
2925  * return:
2926  * opcode(in):
2927  */
2928 static int
2929 get_opcode_rank (PT_OP_TYPE opcode)
2930 {
2931  switch (opcode)
2932  {
2933  /* Group 1 -- light */
2934  case PT_COERCIBILITY:
2935  /* is always folded to constant : should not reach this code */
2936  assert (false);
2937  case PT_CHARSET:
2938  case PT_COLLATION:
2939  case PT_AND:
2940  case PT_OR:
2941  case PT_XOR:
2942  case PT_NOT:
2943  case PT_ASSIGN:
2944 
2945  case PT_IS_IN:
2946  case PT_IS_NOT_IN:
2947  case PT_BETWEEN:
2948  case PT_NOT_BETWEEN:
2949 
2950  case PT_EQ:
2951  case PT_EQ_SOME:
2952  case PT_NE_SOME:
2953  case PT_GE_SOME:
2954  case PT_GT_SOME:
2955  case PT_LT_SOME:
2956  case PT_LE_SOME:
2957  case PT_EQ_ALL:
2958  case PT_NE_ALL:
2959  case PT_GE_ALL:
2960  case PT_GT_ALL:
2961  case PT_LT_ALL:
2962  case PT_LE_ALL:
2963 
2964  case PT_NE:
2965  case PT_GE:
2966  case PT_GT:
2967  case PT_LT:
2968  case PT_LE:
2969 
2970  case PT_GT_INF:
2971  case PT_LT_INF:
2972 
2973  case PT_BIT_NOT:
2974  case PT_BIT_AND:
2975  case PT_BIT_OR:
2976  case PT_BIT_XOR:
2977  case PT_BITSHIFT_LEFT:
2978  case PT_BITSHIFT_RIGHT:

3246 /*
3247  * get_expr_fcode_rank () -
3248  * return:
3249  * fcode(in): function code
3250  * Only the functions embedded in an expression (with PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER)
3251  * should be added here.
3252  */
3253 static int
3254 get_expr_fcode_rank (FUNC_TYPE fcode)
3255 {
3256  switch (fcode)
3257  {
3258  case F_ELT:
3259  case F_JSON_OBJECT:
3260  case F_JSON_ARRAY:
3261  case F_JSON_REMOVE:
3262  case F_JSON_ARRAY_APPEND:
3263  case F_JSON_MERGE:
3264  case F_JSON_GET_ALL_PATHS:
3265  case F_JSON_INSERT:
3266  case F_JSON_REPLACE:
3267  case F_JSON_SET:
3268  case F_JSON_KEYS:
3269  return RANK_EXPR_LIGHT;
3270  case F_INSERT_SUBSTRING:
3271  return RANK_EXPR_MEDIUM;
3272  default:
3273  /* each function must fill its rank */
3274  assert (false);
3275  return RANK_EXPR_FUNCTION;
3276  }
3277 }
3278 
3279 /*
3280  * get_operand_rank () -
3281  * return:
3282  * node(in):
3283  */
3284 static int
3285 get_operand_rank (PT_NODE * node)
3286 {
3287  int rank = RANK_DEFAULT;
3288 
3289  if (node)
3290  {
3291  switch (node->node_type)
3292  {
3293  case PT_NAME:
3294  rank = RANK_NAME;
3295  break;
3296 
3297  case PT_VALUE:
3298  rank = RANK_VALUE;
3299  break;
3300 
3301  case PT_EXPR:
3302  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER)
3303  {
3304  PT_NODE *function = node->info.expr.arg1;
3305 
3306  assert (function != NULL);
3307  if (function == NULL)
3308  {
3309  rank = RANK_EXPR_MEDIUM;
3310  }
3311  else
3312  {
3313  rank = get_expr_fcode_rank (function->info.function.function_type);
3314  }
3315  }
3316  else
3317  {
3318  rank = get_opcode_rank (node->info.expr.op);
3319  }
3320  break;
3321 
3322  case PT_FUNCTION:
3323  rank = RANK_EXPR_FUNCTION;
3324  break;
3325 
3326  default:
3327  break;
3328  }
3329  }
3330 
3331  return rank;
3332 }
3333 
3334 /*
3335  * get_term_rank () - walks the expression to see whether it contains any
3336  * rankable things. If so, it records the rank of the
3337  * containing term
3338  * return:
3339  * env(in): optimizer environment
3340  * term(in): term to get
3341  */
3342 static void
3343 get_term_rank (QO_ENV * env, QO_TERM * term)
3344 {
3345  PT_NODE *pt_expr;
3346 
3347  QO_TERM_RANK (term) = bitset_cardinality (&(QO_TERM_SUBQUERIES (term))) * RANK_QUERY;
3348 
3349  if (QO_IS_FAKE_TERM (term))
3350  {
3351  pt_expr = NULL; /* do nothing */
3352  }
3353  else
3354  {
3355  pt_expr = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term);
3356  }
3357 
3358  if (pt_expr == NULL)
3359  {
3360  return;
3361  }
3362 
3363  /* At here, do not traverse OR list */
3364  switch (pt_expr->node_type)
3365  {
3366  case PT_EXPR:
3367  QO_TERM_RANK (term) += get_opcode_rank (pt_expr->info.expr.op);
3368  if (pt_expr->info.expr.arg1)
3369  QO_TERM_RANK (term) += get_operand_rank (pt_expr->info.expr.arg1);
3370  if (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2)
3371  QO_TERM_RANK (term) += get_operand_rank (pt_expr->info.expr.arg2);
3372  if (pt_expr->info.expr.arg3)
3373  QO_TERM_RANK (term) += get_operand_rank (pt_expr->info.expr.arg3);
3374  break;
3375 
3376  default:
3377  break;
3378  }
3379 }
3380 
3381 /*
3382  * check_subquery_pre () - Pre routine to add to some bitset all correlated
3383  * subqueries found in an expression
3384  * return: PT_NODE *
3385  * parser(in): parser environmnet
3386  * node(in): node to check
3387  * arg(in):
3388  * continue_walk(in):
3389  */
3390 static PT_NODE *
3391 check_subquery_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
3392 {
3393  WALK_INFO *info = (WALK_INFO *) arg;
3394 
3395  /*
3396  * Be sure to reenable walking for list tails.
3397  */
3398  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
3399 
3400  if (node->node_type == PT_SELECT || node->node_type == PT_UNION || node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE
3401  || node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION)
3402  {
3403  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK; /* NEVER need to look inside queries */
3404 
3405  if (node->info.query.correlation_level == 1)
3406  {
3407  /*
3408  * Find out the index of this subquery, and record that index
3409  * in the enclosing term's subquery bitset. This is lame,
3410  * but I can't think of a better way to do it. When we
3411  * originally grabbed all of the subqueries we had no idea
3412  * what expression they were in, so we have to discover it
3413  * after the fact. Oh well, this doesn't happen often
3414  * anyway.
3415  */
3416  int i, N;
3417  QO_ENV *env;
3418 
3419  env = info->env;
3420  for (i = 0, N = env->nsubqueries; i < N; i++)
3421  {
3422  if (node == env->subqueries[i].node)
3423  {
3424  bitset_add (&(env->subqueries[i].terms), QO_TERM_IDX (info->term));
3425  bitset_add (&(QO_TERM_SUBQUERIES (info->term)), i);
3426  break;
3427  }
3428  }
3429  }
3430  }
3431 
3432  return node; /* leave node unchanged */
3433 
3434 }
3435 
3436 /*
3437  * is_local_name () -
3438  * return: 1 iff the expression is a name correlated to the current query
3439  * env(in): Optimizer environment
3440  * expr(in): The parse tree for the expression to examine
3441  */
3442 static bool
3443 is_local_name (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * expr)
3444 {
3445  UINTPTR spec = 0;
3446 
3447  if (expr == NULL)
3448  {
3449  return false;
3450  }
3451  else if (expr->node_type == PT_NAME)
3452  {
3453  spec = expr->info.name.spec_id;
3454  }
3455  else if (expr->node_type == PT_DOT_)
3456  {
3457  spec = expr->info.dot.arg2->info.name.spec_id;
3458  }
3459  else if (expr->node_type == PT_EXPR && expr->info.expr.op == PT_PRIOR)
3460  {
3461  return is_local_name (env, expr->info.expr.arg1);
3462  }
3463  else if (pt_is_function_index_expr (env->parser, expr, false))
3464  {
3465  if (expr->info.expr.op == PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER)
3466  {
3467  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
3468  PT_NODE *func = expr->info.expr.arg1;
3469  for (arg = func->info.function.arg_list; arg != NULL; arg = arg->next)
3470  {
3471  PT_NODE *save_arg = arg;
3472  arg = pt_function_index_skip_expr (arg);
3473  if (arg->node_type == PT_NAME)
3474  {
3475  if (is_local_name (env, arg) == false)
3476  {
3477  return false;
3478  }
3479  }
3480  arg = save_arg;
3481  }
3482  }
3483  else
3484  {
3485  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
3486  if (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3487  {
3488  arg = pt_function_index_skip_expr (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3489  if (arg->node_type == PT_NAME)
3490  {
3491  if (is_local_name (env, arg) == false)
3492  {
3493  return false;
3494  }
3495  }
3496  }
3497  if (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3498  {
3499  arg = pt_function_index_skip_expr (expr->info.expr.arg2);
3500  if (arg->node_type == PT_NAME)
3501  {
3502  if (is_local_name (env, arg) == false)
3503  {
3504  return false;
3505  }
3506  }
3507  }
3508  if (expr->info.expr.arg3)
3509  {
3510  arg = pt_function_index_skip_expr (expr->info.expr.arg3);
3511  if (arg->node_type == PT_NAME)
3512  {
3513  if (is_local_name (env, arg) == false)
3514  {
3515  return false;
3516  }
3517  }
3518  }
3519  }
3520  return true;
3521  }
3522  else
3523  {
3524  return false;
3525  }
3526 
3527  return (pt_find_entity (env->parser, env->pt_tree->info.query.q.select.from, spec) != NULL) ? true : false;
3528 }
3529 
3530 /*
3531  * pt_is_pseudo_const () -
3532  * return: true if the expression can serve as a pseudo-constant
3533  * during predicate evaluation. Used primarily to help
3534  * determine whether a predicate can be implemented
3535  * with an index scan
3536  * env(in): The optimizer environment
3537  * expr(in): The parse tree for the expression to examine
3538  */
3539 bool
3540 pt_is_pseudo_const (PT_NODE * expr)
3541 {
3542  if (expr == NULL)
3543  {
3544  return false;
3545  }
3546 
3547  switch (expr->node_type)
3548  {
3549  case PT_VALUE:
3550  case PT_HOST_VAR:
3551  return true;
3552 
3553  case PT_SELECT:
3554  case PT_UNION:
3555  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3556  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3557  return (expr->info.query.correlation_level != 1) ? true : false;
3558 
3559  case PT_NAME:
3560  /*
3561  * It is up to the calling context to ensure that the name is
3562  * actually a pseudo constant, either because it is a correlated
3563  * outer reference, or because it can otherwise be guaranteed to
3564  * be evaluated by the time it is referenced.
3565  */
3566  return true;
3567 
3568  case PT_DOT_:
3569  /*
3570  * It would be nice if we could use expressions that are
3571  * guaranteed to be independent of the attribute, but the current
3572  * XASL implementation can't guarantee that such expressions have
3573  * been evaluated by the time that we need them, so we have to
3574  * play it safe here and not use them.
3575  */
3576  return true;
3577 
3578  case PT_EXPR:
3579  switch (expr->info.expr.op)
3580  {
3581  case PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER:
3582  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3583  case PT_PLUS:
3584  case PT_STRCAT:
3585  case PT_MINUS:
3586  case PT_TIMES:
3587  case PT_DIVIDE:
3588  case PT_BIT_AND:
3589  case PT_BIT_OR:
3590  case PT_BIT_XOR:
3591  case PT_BITSHIFT_LEFT:
3592  case PT_BITSHIFT_RIGHT:
3593  case PT_DIV:
3594  case PT_MOD:
3595  case PT_LEFT:
3596  case PT_RIGHT:
3597  case PT_REPEAT:
3598  case PT_STRCMP:
3599  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3600  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3601  case PT_UNARY_MINUS:
3602  case PT_BIT_NOT:
3603  case PT_BIT_COUNT:
3604  case PT_QPRIOR:
3605  case PT_PRIOR:
3606  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3607  case PT_BETWEEN_AND:
3608  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LE:
3609  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LT:
3610  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LE:
3611  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LT:
3612  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3613  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3614  case PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA:
3615  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LE:
3616  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LT:
3617  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_INF:
3618  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_INF:
3619  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3620  case PT_MODULUS:
3621  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3622  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3623  case PT_SCHEMA:
3624  case PT_DATABASE:
3625  case PT_VERSION:
3626  case PT_PI:
3627  case PT_USER:
3628  case PT_LAST_INSERT_ID:
3629  case PT_ROW_COUNT:
3630  case PT_DEFAULTF:
3631  case PT_LIST_DBS:
3632  case PT_OID_OF_DUPLICATE_KEY:
3633  case PT_SCHEMA_DEF:
3634  return true;
3635  case PT_FLOOR:
3636  case PT_CEIL:
3637  case PT_SIGN:
3638  case PT_ABS:
3639  case PT_CHR:
3640  case PT_EXP:
3641  case PT_SQRT:
3642  case PT_ACOS:
3643  case PT_ASIN:
3644  case PT_ATAN:
3645  case PT_SIN:
3646  case PT_COS:
3647  case PT_TAN:
3648  case PT_COT:
3649  case PT_DEGREES:
3650  case PT_RADIANS:
3651  case PT_LN:
3652  case PT_LOG2:
3653  case PT_LOG10:
3654  case PT_DATEF:
3655  case PT_TIMEF:
3656  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3657  case PT_POWER:
3658  case PT_ROUND:
3659  case PT_TRUNC:
3660  case PT_LOG:
3661  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3662  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3663  case PT_INSTR:
3664  case PT_CONV:
3665  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1) && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3666  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3)) ? true : false;
3667  case PT_POSITION:
3668  case PT_FINDINSET:
3669  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3670  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3671  case PT_SUBSTRING:
3672  case PT_SUBSTRING_INDEX:
3673  case PT_LOCATE:
3674  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1) && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3675  && (expr->info.expr.arg3 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3) : true)) ? true : false;
3676  case PT_CHAR_LENGTH:
3677  case PT_OCTET_LENGTH:
3678  case PT_BIT_LENGTH:
3679  case PT_LOWER:
3680  case PT_UPPER:
3681  case PT_HEX:
3682  case PT_ASCII:
3683  case PT_REVERSE:
3684  case PT_DISK_SIZE:
3685  case PT_SPACE:
3686  case PT_MD5:
3687  case PT_SHA_ONE:
3688  case PT_TO_BASE64:
3689  case PT_FROM_BASE64:
3690  case PT_BIN:
3691  case PT_TZ_OFFSET:
3692  case PT_CRC32:
3693  case PT_CONV_TZ:
3694  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3695  case PT_TRIM:
3696  case PT_LTRIM:
3697  case PT_RTRIM:
3698  case PT_LIKE_LOWER_BOUND:
3699  case PT_LIKE_UPPER_BOUND:
3700  case PT_FROM_UNIXTIME:
3701  case PT_AES_ENCRYPT:
3702  case PT_AES_DECRYPT:
3703  case PT_SHA_TWO:
3704  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3705  && (expr->info.expr.arg2 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2) : true)) ? true : false;
3706 
3707  case PT_LPAD:
3708  case PT_RPAD:
3709  case PT_REPLACE:
3710  case PT_TRANSLATE:
3711  case PT_INDEX_PREFIX:
3712  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1) && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3713  && (expr->info.expr.arg3 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3) : true)) ? true : false;
3714  case PT_ADD_MONTHS:
3715  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3716  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3717  case PT_LAST_DAY:
3718  case PT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP:
3719  if (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3720  {
3721  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3722  }
3723  else
3724  {
3725  return true;
3726  }
3727  case PT_YEARF:
3728  case PT_MONTHF:
3729  case PT_DAYF:
3730  case PT_DAYOFMONTH:
3731  case PT_HOURF:
3732  case PT_MINUTEF:
3733  case PT_SECONDF:
3734  case PT_QUARTERF:
3735  case PT_WEEKDAY:
3736  case PT_DAYOFWEEK:
3737  case PT_DAYOFYEAR:
3738  case PT_TODAYS:
3739  case PT_FROMDAYS:
3740  case PT_TIMETOSEC:
3741  case PT_SECTOTIME:
3742  case PT_TO_ENUMERATION_VALUE:
3743  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3744  case PT_TIMESTAMP:
3745  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3746  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3747  case PT_MONTHS_BETWEEN:
3748  case PT_TIME_FORMAT:
3749  case PT_FORMAT:
3750  case PT_ATAN2:
3751  case PT_ADDDATE:
3752  case PT_DATE_ADD: /* 2 args because the 3rd is constant (unit) */
3753  case PT_SUBDATE:
3754  case PT_DATE_SUB:
3755  case PT_DATE_FORMAT:
3756  case PT_STR_TO_DATE:
3757  case PT_DATEDIFF:
3758  case PT_TIMEDIFF:
3759  case PT_MAKEDATE:
3760  case PT_ADDTIME:
3761  case PT_WEEKF:
3762  case PT_FROM_TZ:
3763  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3764  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3765  case PT_SYS_DATE:
3766  case PT_CURRENT_DATE:
3767  case PT_SYS_TIME:
3768  case PT_CURRENT_TIME:
3769  case PT_SYS_TIMESTAMP:
3770  case PT_CURRENT_TIMESTAMP:
3771  case PT_SYS_DATETIME:
3772  case PT_CURRENT_DATETIME:
3773  case PT_UTC_TIME:
3774  case PT_UTC_DATE:
3775  case PT_LOCAL_TRANSACTION_ID:
3776  case PT_CURRENT_USER:
3777  case PT_EVALUATE_VARIABLE:

3780  return true;
3781  case PT_TO_CHAR:
3782  case PT_TO_DATE:
3783  case PT_TO_TIME:
3784  case PT_TO_TIMESTAMP:
3785  case PT_TO_DATETIME:
3786  case PT_TO_NUMBER:
3787  case PT_TO_DATETIME_TZ:
3788  case PT_TO_TIMESTAMP_TZ:
3789  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3790  && (expr->info.expr.arg2 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2) : true)) ? true : false;
3791  case PT_CURRENT_VALUE:
3792  case PT_NEXT_VALUE:
3793  return true;
3794  case PT_CAST:
3795  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3796  case PT_CASE:
3797  case PT_DECODE:
3798  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3799  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3800  case PT_NULLIF:
3801  case PT_COALESCE:
3802  case PT_NVL:
3803  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3804  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3805  case PT_IF:
3806  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3807  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3)) ? true : false;
3808  case PT_IFNULL:
3809  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3810  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3811 
3812  case PT_ISNULL:
3813  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3814  case PT_CONCAT:
3815  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3816  && (expr->info.expr.arg2 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2) : true)) ? true : false;
3817  case PT_CONCAT_WS:
3818  case PT_FIELD:
3819  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3820  && (expr->info.expr.arg2 ? pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2) : true)
3821  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3)) ? true : false;
3822  case PT_MID:
3823  case PT_NVL2:
3824  case PT_MAKETIME:
3825  case PT_NEW_TIME:
3826  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1) && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)
3827  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg3)) ? true : false;
3828  case PT_EXTRACT:
3829  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3830  case PT_LEAST:
3831  case PT_GREATEST:
3832  return (pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1)
3833  && pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg2)) ? true : false;
3834  case PT_COERCIBILITY:
3835  /* is always folded to constant : should not reach this code */
3836  assert (false);
3837  case PT_COLLATION:
3838  case PT_CHARSET:
3839  case PT_INET_ATON:
3840  case PT_INET_NTOA:
3841  return pt_is_pseudo_const (expr->info.expr.arg1);
3842  default:
3843  return false;
3844  }
3845 
3846  case PT_FUNCTION:
3847  {
3848  /*
3849  * The is the case we encounter for predicates like
3850  *
3851  * x in (a,b,c)
3852  *
3853  * Here the the expression '(a,b,c)' comes in as a multiset
3854  * function call, with PT_NAMEs 'a', 'b', and 'c' as its arglist.
3855  */
3856  PT_NODE *p;
3857 
3858  if (expr->info.function.function_type != F_SET && expr->info.function.function_type != F_MULTISET
3859  && expr->info.function.function_type != F_SEQUENCE)
3860  {
3861  return false;
3862  }
3863  for (p = expr->info.function.arg_list; p; p = p->next)
3864  {
3865  if (!pt_is_pseudo_const (p))
3866  {
3867  return false;
3868  }
3869  }
3870  return true;
3871  }
3872 
3873  default:
3874  return false;
3875  }
3876 }
3877 
3878 /*
3879  * add_local_subquery () - This routine adds an entry to the optimizer
3880  * environment for the subquery
3881  * return: nothing
3882  * env(in): Optimizer environment
3883  * node(in): The parse tree for the subquery being added
3884  */
3885 static void
3886 add_local_subquery (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * node)
3887 {
3888  int i, n;
3889  QO_SUBQUERY *tmp;
3890 
3891  n = env->nsubqueries++;
3892 
3893  /*
3894  * Be careful here: the previously allocated QO_SUBQUERY terms
3895  * contain bitsets that may have self-relative internal pointers, and
3896  * those pointers have to be maintained in the new array. The proper
3897  * way to make sure that they are consistent is to use the bitset_assign()
3898  * macro, not just to do the bitcopy that memcpy() will do.
3899  */
3900  tmp = NULL;
3901  if ((n + 1) > 0)
3902  {
3903  tmp = (QO_SUBQUERY *) malloc (sizeof (QO_SUBQUERY) * (n + 1));
3904  if (tmp == NULL)
3905  {
3906  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (QO_SUBQUERY) * (n + 1));
3907  return;
3908  }
3909  }
3910  else
3911  {
3912  return;
3913  }
3914 
3915  memcpy (tmp, env->subqueries, n * sizeof (QO_SUBQUERY));
3916  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
3917  {
3918  QO_SUBQUERY *subq;
3919  subq = &env->subqueries[i];
3920  BITSET_MOVE (tmp[i].segs, subq->segs);
3921  BITSET_MOVE (tmp[i].nodes, subq->nodes);
3922  BITSET_MOVE (tmp[i].terms, subq->terms);
3923  }
3924  if (env->subqueries)
3925  {
3926  free_and_init (env->subqueries);
3927  }
3928  env->subqueries = tmp;
3929 
3930  tmp = &env->subqueries[n];
3931  tmp->node = node;
3932  bitset_init (&tmp->segs, env);
3933  bitset_init (&tmp->nodes, env);
3934  bitset_init (&tmp->terms, env);
3935  qo_expr_segs (env, node, &tmp->segs);
3936  qo_seg_nodes (env, &tmp->segs, &tmp->nodes);
3937  tmp->idx = n;
3938 }
3939 
3940 
3941 /*
3942  * get_local_subqueries_pre () - Builds vector of locally correlated
3943  * (level 1) queries
3944  * return:
3945  * parser(in):
3946  * node(in):
3947  * arg(in):
3948  * continue_walk(in):
3949  */
3950 static PT_NODE *
3951 get_local_subqueries_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
3952 {
3953  QO_ENV *env;
3954  BITSET segs;
3955 
3956  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
3957 
3958  switch (node->node_type)
3959  {
3960  case PT_SELECT:
3961  case PT_UNION:
3962  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
3963  case PT_INTERSECTION:
3964  /* check for correlated subquery except for SELECT list */
3965  if (node->info.query.correlation_level == 1)
3966  {
3967  env = (QO_ENV *) arg;
3968  bitset_init (&segs, env);
3969  qo_expr_segs (env, node, &segs);
3970  if (bitset_is_empty (&segs))
3971  {
3972  /* reduce_equality_terms() can change a correlated subquery to uncorrelated one */
3973  node->info.query.correlation_level = 0;
3974  }
3975  bitset_delset (&segs);
3976  }
3977  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3978  break;
3979 
3980  default:
3981  break;
3982  }
3983 
3984  return node;
3985 }
3986 
3987 /*
3988  * get_local_subqueries_post () - Builds vector of locally correlated
3989  * (level 1) queries
3990  * return:
3991  * parser(in):
3992  * node(in):
3993  * arg(in):
3994  * continue_walk(in):
3995  */
3996 static PT_NODE *
3997 get_local_subqueries_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
3998 {
3999  QO_ENV *env = (QO_ENV *) arg;
4000 
4001  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
4002 
4003  switch (node->node_type)
4004  {
4005  case PT_SELECT:
4006  case PT_UNION:
4007  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
4008  case PT_INTERSECTION:
4009  if (node->info.query.correlation_level == 1)
4010  {
4011  add_local_subquery (env, node);
4012  }
4013  break;
4014 
4015  default:
4016  break;
4017  }
4018 
4019  return node;
4020 }
4021 
4022 /*
4023  * get_local_subqueries () -
4024  * return: non-zero if something went wrong
4025  * env(in):
4026  * node(in):
4027  *
4028  * Note:
4029  * Gather the correlated level == 1 subqueries.
4030  * EXCLUDE nested queries.
4031  * INCLUDING the node being passed in.
4032  */
4033 static void
4034 get_local_subqueries (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * node)
4035 {
4036  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser;
4037  PT_NODE *tree;
4038  PT_NODE *select_list_ptr;
4039  PT_NODE *next_ptr;
4040  int i;
4041 
4042  parser = QO_ENV_PARSER (env);
4043  tree = QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env);
4044 
4045  next_ptr = tree->next;
4046  tree->next = NULL;
4047  select_list_ptr = tree->info.query.q.select.list;
4048  tree->info.query.q.select.list = NULL;
4049 
4050  parser_walk_leaves (parser, tree, get_local_subqueries_pre, env, get_local_subqueries_post, env);
4051 
4052  /* restore next list pointer */
4053  tree->next = next_ptr;
4054  tree->info.query.q.select.list = select_list_ptr;
4055 
4056  /*
4057  * Now that all of the subqueries have been discovered, make
4058  * *another* pass and associate each with its enclosing QO_TERM, if any.
4059  */
4060  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
4061  {
4062  get_term_subqueries (env, QO_ENV_TERM (env, i));
4063  }
4064 
4065  QO_ASSERT (env, env->subqueries != NULL || env->nsubqueries == 0);
4066 
4067 }

4071  * get_rank () - Gather term's rank
4072  * return:
4073  * env(in):
4074  */
4075 static void
4076 get_rank (QO_ENV * env)
4077 {
4078  int i;
4079 
4080  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
4081  {
4082  get_term_rank (env, QO_ENV_TERM (env, i));
4083  }
4084 }

4086 /*
4087  * get_referenced_attrs () - Returns the list of this entity's attributes that
4088  * are referenced in this query
4089  * return:
4090  * entity(in):
4091  */
4092 static PT_NODE *
4093 get_referenced_attrs (PT_NODE * entity)
4094 {
4095  return (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (entity)
4096  || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (entity)) ? entity->info.spec.as_attr_list : entity->info.spec.referenced_attrs;
4097 }

4099 /*
4100  * add_hint_args () - attach hint informations to QO_NODEs
4101  * return:
4102  * env(in):
4103  * arg_list(in):
4104  * hint(in):
4105  */
4106 static void
4107 add_hint_args (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * arg_list, PT_HINT_ENUM hint)
4108 {
4109  PT_NODE *arg, *entity_spec;
4110  QO_NODE *node;
4111  int i;
4112 
4113  if (arg_list)
4114  {
4115  /* iterate over all nodes */
4116  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4117  {
4118  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4119  entity_spec = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
4120  /* check for spec list */
4121  for (arg = arg_list; arg; arg = arg->next)
4122  {
4123  /* found match */
4124  if (entity_spec->info.spec.id == arg->info.name.spec_id)
4125  {
4126  QO_NODE_HINT (node) = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (QO_NODE_HINT (node) | hint);
4127  break;
4128  }
4129  }
4130  }
4131  }
4132  else
4133  { /* FULLY HINTED */
4134  /* iterate over all nodes */
4135  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4136  {
4137  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4138  QO_NODE_HINT (node) = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (QO_NODE_HINT (node) | hint);
4139  }
4140  }
4141 
4142 }
4143 
4144 /*
4145  * add_hint () -
4146  * return:
4147  * env(in):
4148  * tree(in):
4149  */
4150 static void
4151 add_hint (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * tree)
4152 {
4153  PT_HINT_ENUM hint;
4154  int i, j, k;
4155  QO_NODE *node, *p_node;
4156  PT_NODE *arg, *p_arg, *spec, *p_spec;
4157  int last_ordered_idx = 0;
4158 
4159  hint = tree->info.query.q.select.hint;
4160 
4161  if (hint & PT_HINT_ORDERED)
4162  {
4163  if (tree->info.query.q.select.ordered)
4164  {
4165  /* find last ordered node */
4166  for (arg = tree->info.query.q.select.ordered; arg->next; arg = arg->next)
4167  {
4168  ; /* nop */
4169  }
4170  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4171  {
4172  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4173  spec = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
4174  if (spec->info.spec.id == arg->info.name.spec_id)
4175  {
4176  last_ordered_idx = QO_NODE_IDX (node);
4177  break;
4178  }
4179  }
4180 
4181  /* iterate over all nodes */
4182  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4183  {
4184  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4185  spec = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
4186  /* check for arg list */
4187  p_arg = NULL;
4188  for (arg = tree->info.query.q.select.ordered, j = 0; arg; arg = arg->next, j++)
4189  {
4190  if (spec->info.spec.id == arg->info.name.spec_id)
4191  {
4192  if (p_arg)
4193  { /* skip out the first ordered spec */
4194  /* find prev node */
4195  for (k = 0; k < env->nnodes; k++)
4196  {
4197  p_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, k);
4198  p_spec = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (p_node);
4199  if (p_spec->info.spec.id == p_arg->info.name.spec_id)
4200  {
4201  bitset_assign (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (p_node)));
4202  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), QO_NODE_IDX (p_node));
4203  break;
4204  }
4205  }
4206  }
4207 
4208 #if 1 /* TEMPORARY CODE: DO NOT REMOVE ME !!! */
4209  QO_NODE_HINT (node) = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (QO_NODE_HINT (node) | PT_HINT_ORDERED);
4210 #endif
4211  break; /* exit loop for arg traverse */
4212  }
4213 
4214  p_arg = arg; /* save previous arg */
4215  }
4216 
4217  /* not found in arg list */
4218  if (!arg)
4219  {
4220  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), last_ordered_idx);
4221  }
4222 
4223  } /* for (i = ... ) */
4224 
4225  }
4226  else
4227  { /* FULLY HINTED */
4228  /* iterate over all nodes */
4229  p_node = NULL;
4230  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4231  {
4232  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4233  if (p_node)
4234  { /* skip out the first ordered node */
4235  bitset_assign (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (p_node)));
4236  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), QO_NODE_IDX (p_node));
4237  }
4238 #if 1 /* TEMPORARY CODE: DO NOT REMOVE ME !!! */
4239  QO_NODE_HINT (node) = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (QO_NODE_HINT (node) | PT_HINT_ORDERED);
4240 #endif
4241 
4242  p_node = node; /* save previous node */
4243  } /* for (i = ... ) */
4244  }
4245  }
4246 
4247  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_NL)
4248  {
4249  add_hint_args (env, tree->info.query.q.select.use_nl, PT_HINT_USE_NL);
4250  }
4251 
4252  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_IDX)
4253  {
4254  add_hint_args (env, tree->info.query.q.select.use_idx, PT_HINT_USE_IDX);
4255  }
4256  if (hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS)
4257  {
4258  add_hint_args (env, tree->info.query.q.select.index_ss, PT_HINT_INDEX_SS);
4259  }
4260  if (hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_LS)
4261  {
4262  add_hint_args (env, tree->info.query.q.select.index_ls, PT_HINT_INDEX_LS);
4263  }
4264 
4265 
4266  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_MERGE)
4267  {
4268  add_hint_args (env, tree->info.query.q.select.use_merge, PT_HINT_USE_MERGE);
4269  }
4270 }
4271 
4272 /*
4273  * add_using_index () - attach index names specified in USING INDEX clause to QO_NODEs
4274  * return:
4275  * env(in):
4276  * using_index(in):
4277  */
4278 static void
4279 add_using_index (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * using_index)
4280 {
4281  int i, j, n;
4282  QO_NODE *nodep;
4283  QO_USING_INDEX *uip;
4284  PT_NODE *indexp, *indexp_nokl;
4285  bool is_none, is_ignored;
4286  PT_NODE **idx_ignore_list = NULL;
4287  int idx_ignore_list_capacity = 0;
4288  int idx_ignore_list_size = 0;
4289 
4290  if (!using_index)
4291  {
4292  /* no USING INDEX clause in the query; all QO_NODE_USING_INDEX(node) will contain NULL */
4293  goto cleanup;
4294  }
4295 
4296  /* allocate memory for index ignore list; by default, the capacity of the list is the number of index hints in the
4297  * USING INDEX clause
4298  */
4299  idx_ignore_list_capacity = 0;
4300  for (indexp = using_index; indexp; indexp = indexp->next)
4301  {
4302  idx_ignore_list_capacity++;
4303  }
4304 
4305  idx_ignore_list = (PT_NODE **) malloc (idx_ignore_list_capacity * sizeof (PT_NODE *));
4306  if (idx_ignore_list == NULL)
4307  {
4308  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
4309  idx_ignore_list_capacity * sizeof (PT_NODE *));
4310  goto cleanup;
4311  }
4312 
4313  /* if an index occurs more than once and at least one occurrence has a keylimit, we should ignore the occurrences
4314  * without keylimit; we now build an ignore list containing indexes which should not be attached to the QO_NODE
4315  */
4316  idx_ignore_list_size = 0;
4317  for (indexp_nokl = using_index; indexp_nokl; indexp_nokl = indexp_nokl->next)
4318  {
4319  if (indexp_nokl->info.name.original && indexp_nokl->info.name.resolved && !indexp_nokl->info.name.indx_key_limit)
4320  {
4321  /* it's a normal index without a keylimit; search for same index with keylimit */
4322  for (indexp = using_index; indexp; indexp = indexp->next)
4323  {
4324  if (indexp->info.name.original && indexp->info.name.resolved && indexp->info.name.indx_key_limit
4325  && indexp->etc == indexp_nokl->etc
4326  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (indexp->info.name.original, indexp_nokl->info.name.original)
4327  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (indexp->info.name.resolved, indexp_nokl->info.name.resolved))
4328  {
4329  /* same index found, with keylimit; add to ignore list */
4330  idx_ignore_list[idx_ignore_list_size++] = indexp_nokl;
4331  break;
4332  }
4333  } /* for (indexp ...) */
4334  }
4335  } /* for (indexp_nokl ...) */
4336 
4337  /* for each node */
4338  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
4339  {
4340  nodep = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
4341  is_none = false;
4342 
4343  /* count number of indexes for this node */
4344  n = 0;
4345  for (indexp = using_index; indexp; indexp = indexp->next)
4346  {
4347  /* check for USING INDEX NONE or USING INDEX class.NONE cases */
4348  if (indexp->info.name.original == NULL && indexp->info.name.resolved == NULL)
4349  {
4350  n = 0;
4351  is_none = true;
4352  break; /* USING INDEX NONE case */
4353  }
4354  if (indexp->info.name.original == NULL
4355  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_NODE_NAME (nodep), indexp->info.name.resolved)
4356  && indexp->etc == (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_CLASS_NONE)
4357  {
4358  n = 0; /* USING INDEX class_name.NONE,... case */
4359  is_none = true;
4360  break;
4361  }
4362 
4363  /* check if index is in ignore list (pointer comparison) */
4364  is_ignored = false;
4365  for (j = 0; j < idx_ignore_list_size; j++)
4366  {
4367  if (indexp == idx_ignore_list[j])
4368  {
4369  is_ignored = true;
4370  break;
4371  }
4372  }
4373  if (is_ignored)
4374  {
4375  continue;
4376  }
4377 
4378  /* check index type and count it accordingly */
4379  if (indexp->info.name.original == NULL && indexp->info.name.resolved[0] == '*')
4380  {
4381  n++; /* USING INDEX ALL EXCEPT case */
4382  }
4383  if (indexp->info.name.original && !intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_NODE_NAME (nodep), indexp->info.name.resolved))
4384  {
4385  n++;
4386  }
4387  }
4388  /* if n == 0, it means that either no indexes in USING INDEX clause for this node or USING INDEX NONE case */
4389 
4390  if (n == 0 && !is_none)
4391  {
4392  /* no index for this node in USING INDEX clause, however give it a chance to be assigned an index later */
4393  QO_NODE_USING_INDEX (nodep) = NULL;
4394  continue;
4395  }
4396 
4397  /* allocate QO_USING_INDEX structure */
4398  if (n == 0)
4399  {
4400  uip = (QO_USING_INDEX *) malloc (SIZEOF_USING_INDEX (1));
4401  }
4402  else
4403  {
4404  uip = (QO_USING_INDEX *) malloc (SIZEOF_USING_INDEX (n));
4405  }
4406  QO_NODE_USING_INDEX (nodep) = uip;
4407 
4408  if (uip == NULL)
4409  {
4410  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, SIZEOF_USING_INDEX (n ? n : 1));
4411  goto cleanup;
4412  }
4413 
4414  QO_UI_N (uip) = n;
4415 
4416  /* USING INDEX NONE, or USING INDEX class_name.NONE,... case */
4417  if (is_none)
4418  {
4419  continue;
4420  }
4421 
4422  /* attach indexes to QO_NODE */
4423  n = 0;
4424  for (indexp = using_index; indexp; indexp = indexp->next)
4425  {
4426  /* check for USING INDEX NONE case */
4427  if (indexp->info.name.original == NULL && indexp->info.name.resolved == NULL)
4428  {
4429  break; /* USING INDEX NONE case */
4430  }
4431 
4432  /* check if index is in ignore list (pointer comparison) */
4433  is_ignored = false;
4434  for (j = 0; j < idx_ignore_list_size; j++)
4435  {
4436  if (indexp == idx_ignore_list[j])
4437  {
4438  is_ignored = true;
4439  break;
4440  }
4441  }
4442  if (is_ignored)
4443  {
4444  continue;
4445  }
4446 
4447  /* attach index if necessary */
4448  if (indexp->info.name.original == NULL && indexp->info.name.resolved[0] == '*')
4449  {
4450  /* USING INDEX ALL EXCEPT case */
4451  QO_UI_INDEX (uip, n) = indexp->info.name.resolved;
4452  QO_UI_FORCE (uip, n++) = (int) (UINT64) (indexp->etc);
4453  }
4454  if (indexp->info.name.original && !intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_NODE_NAME (nodep), indexp->info.name.resolved))
4455  {
4456  QO_UI_INDEX (uip, n) = indexp->info.name.original;
4457  QO_UI_KEYLIMIT (uip, n) = indexp->info.name.indx_key_limit;
4458  QO_UI_FORCE (uip, n++) = (int) (UINT64) (indexp->etc);
4459  }
4460  }
4461  }
4462 
4463 cleanup:
4464  /* free memory of index ignore list */
4465  if (idx_ignore_list != NULL)
4466  {
4467  free (idx_ignore_list);
4468  }
4469 }
4470 
4471 /*
4472  * qo_alloc_index () - Allocate a QO_INDEX structure with room for <n>
4473  * QO_INDEX_ENTRY elements. The fields are initialized
4474  * return: QO_CLASS_INFO *
4475  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4476  * n(in): The node whose class info we want
4477  */
4478 static QO_INDEX *
4479 qo_alloc_index (QO_ENV * env, int n)
4480 {
4481  int i;
4482  QO_INDEX *indexp;
4483  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *entryp;
4484 
4485  indexp = (QO_INDEX *) malloc (SIZEOF_INDEX (n));
4486  if (indexp == NULL)
4487  {
4488  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, SIZEOF_INDEX (n));
4489  return NULL;
4490  }
4491 
4492  indexp->n = 0;
4493  indexp->max = n;
4494 
4495  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
4496  {
4497  entryp = QO_INDEX_INDEX (indexp, i);
4498 
4499  entryp->next = NULL;
4500  entryp->class_ = NULL;
4501  entryp->col_num = 0;
4502  entryp->key_type = NULL;
4503  entryp->nsegs = 0;
4504  entryp->seg_idxs = NULL;
4505  entryp->rangelist_seg_idx = -1;
4506  entryp->seg_equal_terms = NULL;
4507  entryp->seg_other_terms = NULL;
4508  bitset_init (&(entryp->terms), env);
4509  entryp->all_unique_index_columns_are_equi_terms = false;
4510  entryp->cover_segments = false;
4511  entryp->is_iss_candidate = false;
4512  entryp->first_sort_column = -1;
4513  entryp->orderby_skip = false;
4514  entryp->groupby_skip = false;
4515  entryp->use_descending = false;
4516  entryp->statistics_attribute_name = NULL;
4517  entryp->key_limit = NULL;
4518  entryp->constraints = NULL;
4519  entryp->ils_prefix_len = 0;
4520  }
4521 
4522  return indexp;
4523 }
4524 
4525 /*
4526  * qo_free_index () - Free the QO_INDEX structure and all elements contained
4527  * within it
4528  * return: nothing
4529  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4530  * indexp(in): A pointer to a previously-allocated index vector
4531  */
4532 static void
4533 qo_free_index (QO_ENV * env, QO_INDEX * indexp)
4534 {
4535  int i, j;
4536  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *entryp;
4537 
4538  if (!indexp)
4539  {
4540  return;
4541  }
4542 
4543  for (i = 0; i < indexp->max; i++)
4544  {
4545  entryp = QO_INDEX_INDEX (indexp, i);
4546  bitset_delset (&(entryp->terms));
4547  for (j = 0; j < entryp->nsegs; j++)
4548  {
4549  bitset_delset (&(entryp->seg_equal_terms[j]));
4550  bitset_delset (&(entryp->seg_other_terms[j]));
4551  }
4552  if (entryp->nsegs)
4553  {
4554  if (entryp->seg_equal_terms)
4555  {
4556  free_and_init (entryp->seg_equal_terms);
4557  }
4558  if (entryp->seg_other_terms)
4559  {
4560  free_and_init (entryp->seg_other_terms);
4561  }
4562  if (entryp->seg_idxs)
4563  {
4564  free_and_init (entryp->seg_idxs);
4565  }
4566 
4567  if (entryp->statistics_attribute_name)
4568  {
4569  free_and_init (entryp->statistics_attribute_name);
4570  }
4571  }
4572  entryp->constraints = NULL;
4573  }
4574 
4575  if (indexp)
4576  {
4577  free_and_init (indexp);
4578  }
4579 }
4580 
4581 /*
4582  * qo_get_class_info () -
4583  * return: QO_CLASS_INFO *
4584  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4585  * node(in): The node whose class info we want
4586  */
4587 static QO_CLASS_INFO *
4588 qo_get_class_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * node)
4589 {
4590  PT_NODE *dom_set;
4591  int n;
4592  QO_CLASS_INFO *info;
4593  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *end;
4594  int i;
4595 
4596  dom_set = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node)->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
4597  n = count_classes (dom_set);
4598  info = (QO_CLASS_INFO *) malloc (SIZEOF_CLASS_INFO (n));
4599  if (info == NULL)
4600  {
4601  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, SIZEOF_CLASS_INFO (n));
4602  return NULL;
4603  }
4604 
4605  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
4606  {
4607  info->info[i].name = NULL;
4608  info->info[i].mop = NULL;
4609  info->info[i].smclass = NULL;
4610  info->info[i].stats = NULL;
4611  info->info[i].self_allocated = 0;
4612  OID_SET_NULL (&info->info[i].oid);
4613  info->info[i].index = NULL;
4614  }
4615 
4616  info->n = n;
4617  end = grok_classes (env, dom_set, &info->info[0]);
4618 
4619  QO_ASSERT (env, end == &info->info[n]);
4620 
4621  return info;
4622 
4623 }
4624 
4625 /*
4626  * qo_free_class_info () - Free the vector and all interally-allocated
4627  * structures
4628  * return: nothing
4629  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4630  * info(in): A pointer to a previously-allocated info vector
4631  */
4632 static void
4633 qo_free_class_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_CLASS_INFO * info)
4634 {
4635  int i;
4636 
4637  if (info == NULL)
4638  {
4639  return;
4640  }
4641 
4642  /*
4643  * The CLASS_STATS structures that are pointed to by the various
4644  * members of info[] will be automatically freed by the garbage
4645  * collector. Make sure that we null out our mop pointer so that the
4646  * garbage collector doesn't mistakenly believe that the class object
4647  * is still in use.
4648  */
4649  for (i = 0; i < info->n; ++i)
4650  {
4651  qo_free_index (env, info->info[i].index);
4652  info->info[i].name = NULL;
4653  info->info[i].mop = NULL;
4654  if (info->info[i].self_allocated)
4655  {
4656  free_and_init (info->info[i].stats);
4657  }
4658  info->info[i].smclass = NULL;
4659  }
4660  if (info)
4661  {
4662  free_and_init (info);
4663  }
4664 }
4665 
4666 /*
4667  * count_classes () - Count the number of object-based classes in the domain set
4668  * return: int
4669  * p(in):
4670  */
4671 static int
4672 count_classes (PT_NODE * p)
4673 {
4674  int n;
4675 
4676  for (n = 0; p; p = p->next)
4677  {
4678  n++;
4679  }
4680 
4681  return n;
4682 }
4683 
4684 /*
4685  * grok_classes () -
4686  * return: QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *
4687  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4688  * p(in): The flat list of entity_specs
4689  * info(in): The next info slot to be initialized
4690  *
4691  * Note: Populate the info array by traversing the given flat list.
4692  * info is assumed to point to a vector of QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY
4693  * structures that is long enough to accept entries for all
4694  * remaining object-based classes. This should be the case if
4695  * the length of the array was determined using count_classes()
4696  * above.
4697  */
4698 static QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *
4699 grok_classes (QO_ENV * env, PT_NODE * p, QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY * info)
4700 {
4701  HFID *hfid;
4702  SM_CLASS *smclass;
4703  int is_class = 0;
4704 
4705  for (; p; p = p->next)
4706  {
4707  info->mop = p->info.name.db_object;
4708  is_class = db_is_class (info->mop);
4709  if (is_class < 0)
4710  {
4711  return NULL;
4712  }
4713  info->normal_class = is_class;
4714  if (info->mop)
4715  {
4716  info->oid = *WS_OID (info->mop);
4717  info->name = sm_get_ch_name (info->mop);
4718  info->smclass = sm_get_class_with_statistics (info->mop);
4719  }
4720  else
4721  {
4722  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser = env->parser;
4723  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "info");
4724  return info;
4725  }
4726 
4727  smclass = info->smclass;
4728  if (smclass == NULL)
4729  {
4730  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser = env->parser;
4731  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "info");
4732  return info;
4733  }
4734 
4735  if (smclass->stats == NULL)
4736  {
4737  info->stats = (CLASS_STATS *) malloc (sizeof (CLASS_STATS));
4738  if (info->stats == NULL)
4739  {
4740  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (CLASS_STATS));
4741  return NULL;
4742  }
4743 
4744  info->self_allocated = 1;
4745  info->stats->n_attrs = 0;
4746  info->stats->attr_stats = NULL;
4747  qo_estimate_statistics (info->mop, info->stats);
4748  }
4749  else if (smclass->stats->heap_num_pages == 0)
4750  {
4751  if (!info->normal_class || ((hfid = sm_get_ch_heap (info->mop)) && !HFID_IS_NULL (hfid)))
4752  {
4753  qo_estimate_statistics (info->mop, smclass->stats);
4754  }
4755  }
4756 
4757  info++;
4758  }
4759 
4760  return info;
4761 }
4762 
4763 /*
4764  * qo_get_attr_info_func_index () - Find the statistics information about
4765  * the function index that underlies this segment
4766  * return: QO_ATTR_INFO *
4767  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4768  * seg(in): A (pointer to) a join graph segment
4769  * expr_str(in):
4770  */
4771 static QO_ATTR_INFO *
4772 qo_get_attr_info_func_index (QO_ENV * env, QO_SEGMENT * seg, const char *expr_str)
4773 {
4774  QO_NODE *nodep;
4775  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *class_info_entryp;
4776  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *consp;
4777  QO_ATTR_INFO *attr_infop = NULL;
4778  QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS *cum_statsp;
4779  BTREE_STATS *bstatsp = NULL;
4780  ATTR_STATS *attr_statsp = NULL;
4781  int n, i, j;
4782  int attr_id;
4783  int n_attrs;
4784  CLASS_STATS *stats;
4785 
4786  nodep = QO_SEG_HEAD (seg);
4787 
4788  if (QO_NODE_INFO (nodep) == NULL || !(QO_NODE_INFO (nodep)->info[0].normal_class))
4789  {
4790  /* if there's no class information or the class is not normal class */
4791  return NULL;
4792  }
4793 
4794  /* number of class information entries */
4795  n = QO_NODE_INFO_N (nodep);
4796  QO_ASSERT (env, n > 0);
4797 
4798  /* pointer to QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY[] array of the node */
4799  class_info_entryp = &QO_NODE_INFO (nodep)->info[0];
4800 
4801  /* allocate QO_ATTR_INFO within the current optimizer environment */
4802  attr_infop = (QO_ATTR_INFO *) malloc (sizeof (QO_ATTR_INFO));
4803  if (attr_infop == NULL)
4804  {
4805  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (QO_ATTR_INFO));
4806  return NULL;
4807  }
4808 
4809  cum_statsp = &attr_infop->cum_stats;
4810  cum_statsp->type = pt_type_enum_to_db (QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg)->type_enum);
4811  cum_statsp->valid_limits = false;
4812  cum_statsp->is_indexed = true;
4813  cum_statsp->leafs = cum_statsp->pages = cum_statsp->height = 0;
4814  cum_statsp->keys = 0;
4815  cum_statsp->key_type = NULL;
4816  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = 0;
4817  cum_statsp->pkeys = NULL;
4818 
4819  /* set the statistics from the class information(QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY) */
4820  for (i = 0; i < n; class_info_entryp++, i++)
4821  {
4822  stats = QO_GET_CLASS_STATS (class_info_entryp);
4823  QO_ASSERT (env, stats != NULL);
4824  if (stats->attr_stats == NULL)
4825  {
4826  /* the attribute statistics of the class were not set */
4827  cum_statsp->is_indexed = false;
4828  continue;
4829  /* We'll consider the segment to be indexed only if all of the attributes it represents are indexed. The
4830  * current optimization strategy makes it inconvenient to try to construct "mixed" (segment and index) scans
4831  * of a node that represents more than one node.
4832  */
4833  }
4834 
4835  for (consp = class_info_entryp->smclass->constraints; consp; consp = consp->next)
4836  {
4837  /* search the attribute from the class information */
4838  attr_statsp = stats->attr_stats;
4839  n_attrs = stats->n_attrs;
4840 
4841  if (consp->func_index_info && consp->func_index_info->col_id == 0
4842  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (expr_str, consp->func_index_info->expr_str))
4843  {
4844  attr_id = consp->attributes[0]->id;
4845 
4846  for (j = 0; j < n_attrs; j++, attr_statsp++)
4847  {
4848  if (attr_statsp->id == attr_id)
4849  {
4850  break;
4851  }
4852  }
4853  if (j == n_attrs)
4854  {
4855  /* attribute not found, what happens to the class attribute? */
4856  cum_statsp->is_indexed = false;
4857  continue;
4858  }
4859 
4860  bstatsp = attr_statsp->bt_stats;
4861  for (j = 0; j < attr_statsp->n_btstats; j++, bstatsp++)
4862  {
4863  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (&bstatsp->btid, &consp->index_btid) && bstatsp->has_function == 1)
4864  {
4865  break;
4866  }
4867  }
4868 
4869  if (cum_statsp->valid_limits == false)
4870  {
4871  /* first time */
4872  cum_statsp->valid_limits = true;
4873  }
4874 
4875  cum_statsp->leafs += bstatsp->leafs;
4876  cum_statsp->pages += bstatsp->pages;
4877  cum_statsp->height = MAX (cum_statsp->height, bstatsp->height);
4878 
4879  if (cum_statsp->pkeys_size == 0 || /* the first found */
4880  cum_statsp->keys < bstatsp->keys)
4881  {
4882  cum_statsp->keys = bstatsp->keys;
4883  cum_statsp->key_type = bstatsp->key_type;
4884  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = bstatsp->pkeys_size;
4885  /* alloc pkeys[] within the current optimizer environment */
4886  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
4887  {
4888  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
4889  }
4890  cum_statsp->pkeys = (int *) malloc (SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
4891  if (cum_statsp->pkeys == NULL)
4892  {
4893  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
4894  SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
4895  qo_free_attr_info (env, attr_infop);
4896  return NULL;
4897  }
4898 
4899  assert (cum_statsp->pkeys_size <= BTREE_STATS_PKEYS_NUM);
4900  for (i = 0; i < cum_statsp->pkeys_size; i++)
4901  {
4902  cum_statsp->pkeys[i] = bstatsp->pkeys[i];
4903  }
4904  }
4905  }
4906  }
4907  }
4908 
4909  return attr_infop;
4910 }
4911 
4912 /*
4913  * qo_get_attr_info () - Find the ATTR_STATS information about each actual
4914  * attribute that underlies this segment
4915  * return: QO_ATTR_INFO *
4916  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
4917  * seg(in): A (pointer to) a join graph segment
4918  */
4919 static QO_ATTR_INFO *
4920 qo_get_attr_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_SEGMENT * seg)
4921 {
4922  QO_NODE *nodep;
4923  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *class_info_entryp;
4924  QO_ATTR_INFO *attr_infop;
4925  int attr_id;
4926  QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS *cum_statsp;
4927  ATTR_STATS *attr_statsp;
4928  BTREE_STATS *bt_statsp;
4929  int n_attrs;
4930  const char *name;
4931  int n, i, j;
4932  int n_func_indexes;
4933  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *consp;
4934  CLASS_STATS *stats;
4935  bool is_reserved_name = false;
4936 
4937  if ((QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg))->info.name.meta_class == PT_RESERVED)
4938  {
4939  is_reserved_name = true;
4940  }
4941 
4942  /* actual attribute name of the given segment */
4943  name = QO_SEG_NAME (seg);
4944  /* QO_NODE of the given segment */
4945  nodep = QO_SEG_HEAD (seg);
4946 
4947  if (QO_NODE_INFO (nodep) == NULL || !(QO_NODE_INFO (nodep)->info[0].normal_class))
4948  {
4949  /* if there's no class information or the class is not normal class */
4950  return NULL;
4951  }
4952 
4953  /* number of class information entries */
4954  n = QO_NODE_INFO_N (nodep);
4955  QO_ASSERT (env, n > 0);
4956 
4957  /* pointer to QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY[] array of the node */
4958  class_info_entryp = &QO_NODE_INFO (nodep)->info[0];
4959 
4960  /* allocate QO_ATTR_INFO within the current optimizer environment */
4961  attr_infop = (QO_ATTR_INFO *) malloc (sizeof (QO_ATTR_INFO));
4962  if (attr_infop == NULL)
4963  {
4964  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (QO_ATTR_INFO));
4965  return NULL;
4966  }
4967 
4968  /* initialize QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS structure of QO_ATTR_INFO */
4969  cum_statsp = &attr_infop->cum_stats;
4970  if (is_reserved_name)
4971  {
4972  cum_statsp->type = pt_Reserved_name_table[(QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg))->info.name.reserved_id].type;
4973  cum_statsp->valid_limits = false;
4974  cum_statsp->is_indexed = true;
4975  cum_statsp->leafs = cum_statsp->pages = cum_statsp->height = 0;
4976  cum_statsp->keys = 0;
4977  cum_statsp->key_type = NULL;
4978  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = 0;
4979  cum_statsp->pkeys = NULL;
4980 
4981  return attr_infop;
4982  }
4983 
4984  /* not a reserved name */
4985  cum_statsp->type = sm_att_type_id (class_info_entryp->mop, name);
4986  cum_statsp->valid_limits = false;
4987  cum_statsp->is_indexed = true;
4988  cum_statsp->leafs = cum_statsp->pages = cum_statsp->height = 0;
4989  cum_statsp->keys = 0;
4990  cum_statsp->key_type = NULL;
4991  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = 0;
4992  cum_statsp->pkeys = NULL;
4993 
4994  /* set the statistics from the class information(QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY) */
4995  for (i = 0; i < n; class_info_entryp++, i++)
4996  {
4997  attr_id = sm_att_id (class_info_entryp->mop, name);
4998 
4999  /* pointer to ATTR_STATS of CLASS_STATS of QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY */
5000  stats = QO_GET_CLASS_STATS (class_info_entryp);
5001  QO_ASSERT (env, stats != NULL);
5002  if (stats->attr_stats == NULL)
5003  {
5004  /* the attribute statistics of the class were not set */
5005  cum_statsp->is_indexed = false;
5006  continue;
5007  /* We'll consider the segment to be indexed only if all of the attributes it represents are indexed. The
5008  * current optimization strategy makes it inconvenient to try to construct "mixed" (segment and index) scans
5009  * of a node that represents more than one node.
5010  */
5011  }
5012 
5013  /* The stats vector isn't kept in id order because of the effects of schema updates (attribute deletion, most
5014  * notably). We need to search it to find the stats record we're interested in. Worse, there doesn't even need to
5015  * be an entry for this particular attribute in the vector. If we're dealing with a class that was created after
5016  * the last statistics update, it won't have any information associated with it, or if we're dealing with certain
5017  * kinds of attributes they simply won't be recorded. In these cases we just make the best guess we can.
5018  */
5019 
5020  /* search the attribute from the class information */
5021  attr_statsp = stats->attr_stats;
5022  n_attrs = stats->n_attrs;
5023  for (j = 0; j < n_attrs; j++, attr_statsp++)
5024  {
5025  if (attr_statsp->id == attr_id)
5026  {
5027  break;
5028  }
5029  }
5030  if (j == n_attrs)
5031  {
5032  /* attribute not found, what happens to the class attribute? */
5033  cum_statsp->is_indexed = false;
5034  continue;
5035  }
5036 
5037  if (cum_statsp->valid_limits == false)
5038  {
5039  /* first time */
5040  cum_statsp->type = attr_statsp->type;
5041  cum_statsp->valid_limits = true;
5042  }
5043 
5044  n_func_indexes = 0;
5045  for (j = 0; j < attr_statsp->n_btstats; j++)
5046  {
5047  if (attr_statsp->bt_stats[j].has_function == 1)
5048  {
5049  n_func_indexes++;
5050  }
5051  }
5052 
5053  if (attr_statsp->n_btstats - n_func_indexes <= 0 || !attr_statsp->bt_stats)
5054  {
5055  /* the attribute does not have any index */
5056  cum_statsp->is_indexed = false;
5057  continue;
5058  /* We'll consider the segment to be indexed only if all of the attributes it represents are indexed. The
5059  * current optimization strategy makes it inconvenient to try to construct "mixed" (segment and index) scans
5060  * of a node that represents more than one node.
5061  */
5062  }
5063 
5064  /* Because we cannot know which index will be selected for this attribute when there're more than one indexes on
5065  * this attribute, use the statistics of the MIN keys index.
5066  */
5067  bt_statsp = &attr_statsp->bt_stats[0];
5068  for (j = 1; j < attr_statsp->n_btstats; j++)
5069  {
5070  if (bt_statsp->keys > attr_statsp->bt_stats[j].keys)
5071  {
5072  bt_statsp = &attr_statsp->bt_stats[j];
5073  }
5074  }
5075 
5076  if (QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (nodep)->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL)
5077  {
5078  /* class hierarchy spec for example: select ... from all p */
5079 
5080  /* check index uniqueness */
5081  for (consp = sm_class_constraints (class_info_entryp->mop); consp; consp = consp->next)
5082  {
5083  if (SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE_FAMILY (consp->type) && BTID_IS_EQUAL (&bt_statsp->btid, &consp->index_btid))
5084  {
5085  break;
5086  }
5087  }
5088 
5089  if (consp) /* is unique index */
5090  {
5091  /* is class hierarchy index: set unique index statistics */
5092  cum_statsp->leafs = bt_statsp->leafs;
5093  cum_statsp->pages = bt_statsp->pages;
5094  cum_statsp->height = bt_statsp->height;
5095  cum_statsp->keys = bt_statsp->keys;
5096  cum_statsp->key_type = bt_statsp->key_type;
5097  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = bt_statsp->pkeys_size;
5098  /* alloc pkeys[] within the current optimizer environment */
5099  if (cum_statsp->pkeys != NULL)
5100  {
5101  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys); /* free alloced */
5102  }
5103  cum_statsp->pkeys = (int *) malloc (SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5104  if (cum_statsp->pkeys == NULL)
5105  {
5106  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5107  SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5108  qo_free_attr_info (env, attr_infop);
5109  return NULL;
5110  }
5111 
5112  assert (cum_statsp->pkeys_size <= BTREE_STATS_PKEYS_NUM);
5113  for (j = 0; j < cum_statsp->pkeys_size; j++)
5114  {
5115  cum_statsp->pkeys[j] = bt_statsp->pkeys[j];
5116  }
5117 
5118  /* immediately return the allocated QO_ATTR_INFO */
5119  return attr_infop;
5120  }
5121  }
5122 
5123  /* keep cumulative totals of index statistics */
5124  cum_statsp->leafs += bt_statsp->leafs;
5125  cum_statsp->pages += bt_statsp->pages;
5126  /* Assume that the key distributions overlap here, so that the number of distinct keys in all of the attributes
5127  * equal to the maximum number of distinct keys in any one of the attributes. This is probably not far from the
5128  * truth; it is almost certainly a better guess than assuming that all key ranges are distinct.
5129  */
5130  cum_statsp->height = MAX (cum_statsp->height, bt_statsp->height);
5131  if (cum_statsp->pkeys_size == 0 || /* the first found */
5132  cum_statsp->keys < bt_statsp->keys)
5133  {
5134  cum_statsp->keys = bt_statsp->keys;
5135  cum_statsp->key_type = bt_statsp->key_type;
5136  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = bt_statsp->pkeys_size;
5137  /* alloc pkeys[] within the current optimizer environment */
5138  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
5139  {
5140  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
5141  }
5142  cum_statsp->pkeys = (int *) malloc (SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5143  if (cum_statsp->pkeys == NULL)
5144  {
5145  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5146  SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5147  qo_free_attr_info (env, attr_infop);
5148  return NULL;
5149  }
5150 
5151  assert (cum_statsp->pkeys_size <= BTREE_STATS_PKEYS_NUM);
5152  for (j = 0; j < cum_statsp->pkeys_size; j++)
5153  {
5154  cum_statsp->pkeys[j] = bt_statsp->pkeys[j];
5155  }
5156  }
5157 
5158  } /* for (i = 0; i < n; ...) */
5159 
5160  /* return the allocated QO_ATTR_INFO */
5161  return attr_infop;
5162 }
5163 
5164 /*
5165  * qo_free_attr_info () - Free the vector and any internally allocated
5166  * structures
5167  * return: nothing
5168  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
5169  * info(in): A pointer to a previously allocated info vector
5170  */
5171 static void
5172 qo_free_attr_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_ATTR_INFO * info)
5173 {
5174  QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS *cum_statsp;
5175 
5176  if (info)
5177  {
5178  cum_statsp = &info->cum_stats;
5179  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
5180  {
5181  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
5182  }
5183  free_and_init (info);
5184  }
5185 }
5186 
5187 /*
5188  * qo_get_index_info () - Get index statistical information
5189  * return:
5190  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
5191  * node(in): A join graph node
5192  */
5193 static void
5194 qo_get_index_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * node)
5195 {
5196  QO_NODE_INDEX *node_indexp;
5197  QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY *ni_entryp;
5198  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *index_entryp;
5199  QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS *cum_statsp;
5200  QO_SEGMENT *segp;
5201  QO_NODE *seg_node;
5202  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *class_info_entryp = NULL;
5203  const char *name;
5204  int attr_id, n_attrs;
5205  ATTR_STATS *attr_statsp;
5206  BTREE_STATS *bt_statsp;
5207  int i, j, k;
5208  CLASS_STATS *stats;
5209 
5210  /* pointer to QO_NODE_INDEX structure of QO_NODE */
5211  node_indexp = QO_NODE_INDEXES (node);
5212 
5213  /* for each index list(linked list of QO_INDEX_ENTRY) rooted at the node (all elements of QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY[]
5214  * array) */
5215  for (i = 0, ni_entryp = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, 0); i < QO_NI_N (node_indexp); i++, ni_entryp++)
5216  {
5217  cum_statsp = &(ni_entryp)->cum_stats;
5218  cum_statsp->is_indexed = true;
5219 
5220  /* The linked list of QO_INDEX_ENTRY was built by 'qo_find_node_index()' function. It is the list of compatible
5221  * indexes under class hierarchy.
5222  */
5223  /* for each index entry(QO_INDEX_ENTRY) on the list, acquire the statistics and cumulate them */
5224  for (j = 0, index_entryp = (ni_entryp)->head; index_entryp != NULL; j++, index_entryp = index_entryp->next)
5225  {
5226  /* The index information is associated with the first attribute of index keys in the case of multi-column
5227  * index and 'seg_idx[]' array of QO_INDEX_ENTRY structure was built by 'qo_find_index_seg_and_term()'
5228  * function to keep the order of index key attributes. So, 'seg_idx[0]' is the right segment denoting the
5229  * attribute that contains the index statistics that we want to get. If seg_idx[0] is null (-1), then the
5230  * name of the first attribute is taken from index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name
5231  */
5232  segp = NULL;
5233  for (k = 0; k < index_entryp->nsegs; k++)
5234  {
5235  if (index_entryp->seg_idxs[k] != -1)
5236  {
5237  segp = QO_ENV_SEG (env, (index_entryp->seg_idxs[k]));
5238 
5239  if (segp != NULL)
5240  {
5241  break;
5242  }
5243  }
5244  }
5245 
5246  if (segp == NULL)
5247  {
5248  index_entryp->key_type = NULL;
5249  continue;
5250  }
5251 
5252  /* QO_NODE of the given segment */
5253  seg_node = QO_SEG_HEAD (segp);
5254 
5255  if (k == 0)
5256  {
5257  /* actual attribute name of the given segment */
5258  name = QO_SEG_NAME (segp);
5259  }
5260  else
5261  {
5262  /* actual attribute name of the given segment */
5263  name = index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name;
5264  }
5265 
5266  /* pointer to QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY[] array of the node */
5267  class_info_entryp = &QO_NODE_INFO (seg_node)->info[j];
5268 
5269  /* pointer to ATTR_STATS of CLASS_STATS of QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY */
5270  stats = QO_GET_CLASS_STATS (class_info_entryp);
5271  QO_ASSERT (env, stats != NULL);
5272 
5273  /* search the attribute from the class information */
5274  attr_statsp = stats->attr_stats;
5275  n_attrs = stats->n_attrs;
5276 
5277  if (!index_entryp->is_func_index)
5278  {
5279  attr_id = sm_att_id (class_info_entryp->mop, name);
5280  }
5281  else
5282  {
5283  /* function index with the function expression as the first attribute */
5284  attr_id = index_entryp->constraints->attributes[0]->id;
5285  }
5286 
5287  for (k = 0; k < n_attrs; k++, attr_statsp++)
5288  {
5289  if (attr_statsp->id == attr_id)
5290  {
5291  break;
5292  }
5293  }
5294 
5295  index_entryp->key_type = NULL;
5296  if (k >= n_attrs) /* not found */
5297  {
5298  attr_statsp = NULL;
5299  continue;
5300  }
5301 
5302  if (cum_statsp->valid_limits == false)
5303  {
5304  /* first time */
5305  cum_statsp->type = attr_statsp->type;
5306  cum_statsp->valid_limits = true;
5307  }
5308 
5309  /* find the index that we are interesting within BTREE_STATS[] array */
5310  bt_statsp = attr_statsp->bt_stats;
5311  for (k = 0; k < attr_statsp->n_btstats; k++, bt_statsp++)
5312  {
5313  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (&bt_statsp->btid, &(index_entryp->constraints->index_btid)))
5314  {
5315  if (!index_entryp->is_func_index || bt_statsp->has_function == 1)
5316  {
5317  index_entryp->key_type = bt_statsp->key_type;
5318  break;
5319  }
5320  }
5321  } /* for (k = 0, ...) */
5322 
5323  if (k == attr_statsp->n_btstats)
5324  {
5325  /* cannot find index in this attribute. what happens? */
5326  continue;
5327  }
5328 
5329  if (QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node)->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL)
5330  {
5331  /* class hierarchy spec for example: select ... from all p */
5332 
5333  /* check index uniqueness */
5334  if (SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE_FAMILY (index_entryp->constraints->type))
5335  {
5336  /* is class hierarchy index: set unique index statistics */
5337  cum_statsp->leafs = bt_statsp->leafs;
5338  cum_statsp->pages = bt_statsp->pages;
5339  cum_statsp->height = bt_statsp->height;
5340  cum_statsp->keys = bt_statsp->keys;
5341  cum_statsp->key_type = bt_statsp->key_type;
5342  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = bt_statsp->pkeys_size;
5343  /* alloc pkeys[] within the current optimizer environment */
5344  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
5345  {
5346  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
5347  }
5348  cum_statsp->pkeys = (int *) malloc (SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5349  if (cum_statsp->pkeys == NULL)
5350  {
5351  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5352  SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5353  return; /* give up */
5354  }
5355 
5356  assert (cum_statsp->pkeys_size <= BTREE_STATS_PKEYS_NUM);
5357  for (k = 0; k < cum_statsp->pkeys_size; k++)
5358  {
5359  cum_statsp->pkeys[k] = bt_statsp->pkeys[k];
5360  }
5361 
5362  /* immediately finish getting index statistics */
5363  break; /* for (j = 0, ... ) */
5364  }
5365  }
5366 
5367  /* keep cumulative totals of index statistics */
5368  cum_statsp->leafs += bt_statsp->leafs;
5369  cum_statsp->pages += bt_statsp->pages;
5370  /* Assume that the key distributions overlap here, so that the number of distinct keys in all of the
5371  * attributes equal to the maximum number of distinct keys in any one of the attributes. This is probably not
5372  * far from the truth; it is almost certainly a better guess than assuming that all key ranges are distinct.
5373  */
5374  cum_statsp->height = MAX (cum_statsp->height, bt_statsp->height);
5375  if (cum_statsp->pkeys_size == 0 || /* the first found */
5376  cum_statsp->keys < bt_statsp->keys)
5377  {
5378  cum_statsp->keys = bt_statsp->keys;
5379  cum_statsp->key_type = bt_statsp->key_type;
5380  cum_statsp->pkeys_size = bt_statsp->pkeys_size;
5381  /* alloc pkeys[] within the current optimizer environment */
5382  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
5383  {
5384  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
5385  }
5386  cum_statsp->pkeys = (int *) malloc (SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5387  if (cum_statsp->pkeys == NULL)
5388  {
5389  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5390  SIZEOF_ATTR_CUM_STATS_PKEYS (cum_statsp->pkeys_size));
5391  return; /* give up */
5392  }
5393 
5394  assert (cum_statsp->pkeys_size <= BTREE_STATS_PKEYS_NUM);
5395  for (k = 0; k < cum_statsp->pkeys_size; k++)
5396  {
5397  cum_statsp->pkeys[k] = bt_statsp->pkeys[k];
5398  }
5399  }
5400  } /* for (j = 0, ... ) */
5401  } /* for (i = 0, ...) */
5402 }
5403 
5404 /*
5405  * qo_free_node_index_info () - Free the vector and any internally allocated
5406  * structures
5407  * return: nothing
5408  * env(in): The current optimizer environment
5409  * node_indexp(in): A pointer to QO_NODE_INDEX structure of QO_NODE
5410  */
5411 static void
5412 qo_free_node_index_info (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE_INDEX * node_indexp)
5413 {
5414  QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY *ni_entryp;
5415  QO_ATTR_CUM_STATS *cum_statsp;
5416  int i;
5417 
5418  if (node_indexp)
5419  {
5420  /* for each index list(linked list of QO_INDEX_ENTRY) rooted at the node (all elements of QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY[]
5421  * array) */
5422  for (i = 0, ni_entryp = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, 0); i < QO_NI_N (node_indexp); i++, ni_entryp++)
5423  {
5424  cum_statsp = &(ni_entryp)->cum_stats;
5425  if (cum_statsp->pkeys)
5426  {
5427  free_and_init (cum_statsp->pkeys);
5428  }
5429  }
5430 
5431  free_and_init (node_indexp);
5432  }
5433 }
5434 
5435 /*
5436  * qo_data_compare () -
5437  * return: 1, 0, -1
5438  * data1(in):
5439  * data2(in):
5440  * type(in):
5441  *
5442  * Note: This is a simplified function that works with DB_DATA
5443  * instead of DB_VALUE, which is the same function of 'qst_data_compare()'.
5444  */
5445 static int
5446 qo_data_compare (DB_DATA * data1, DB_DATA * data2, DB_TYPE type)
5447 {
5448  int result;
5449 
5450  switch (type)
5451  {
5452  case DB_TYPE_INTEGER:
5453  result = (data1->i < data2->i) ? -1 : ((data1->i > data2->i) ? 1 : 0);
5454  break;
5455  case DB_TYPE_SHORT:
5456  result = ((data1->sh < data2->sh) ? -1 : ((data1->sh > data2->sh) ? 1 : 0));
5457  break;
5458  case DB_TYPE_BIGINT:
5459  result = ((data1->bigint < data2->bigint) ? -1 : ((data1->bigint > data2->bigint) ? 1 : 0));
5460  break;
5461  case DB_TYPE_FLOAT:
5462  result = (data1->f < data2->f) ? -1 : ((data1->f > data2->f) ? 1 : 0);
5463  break;
5464  case DB_TYPE_DOUBLE:
5465  result = (data1->d < data2->d) ? -1 : ((data1->d > data2->d) ? 1 : 0);
5466  break;
5467  case DB_TYPE_DATE:
5468  result = ((data1->date < data2->date) ? -1 : ((data1->date > data2->date) ? 1 : 0));
5469  break;
5470  case DB_TYPE_TIME:
5471  result = ((data1->time < data2->time) ? -1 : ((data1->time > data2->time) ? 1 : 0));
5472  break;
5473 
5474  case DB_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
5475  case DB_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
5476  result = ((data1->utime < data2->utime) ? -1 : ((data1->utime > data2->utime) ? 1 : 0));
5477  break;
5478  case DB_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
5479  result = ((data1->timestamptz.timestamp < data2->timestamptz.timestamp)
5480  ? -1 : ((data1->timestamptz.timestamp > data2->timestamptz.timestamp) ? 1 : 0));
5481  break;
5482  case DB_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
5483  case DB_TYPE_DATETIME:
5484  if (data1->datetime.date < data2->datetime.date)
5485  {
5486  result = -1;
5487  }
5488  else if (data1->datetime.date > data2->datetime.date)
5489  {
5490  result = 1;
5491  }
5492  else if (data1->datetime.time < data2->datetime.time)
5493  {
5494  result = -1;
5495  }
5496  else if (data1->datetime.time > data2->datetime.time)
5497  {
5498  result = 1;
5499  }
5500  else
5501  {
5502  result = 0;
5503  }
5504  break;
5505  case DB_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
5506  if (data1->datetimetz.datetime.date < data2->datetimetz.datetime.date)
5507  {
5508  result = -1;
5509  }
5510  else if (data1->datetimetz.datetime.date > data2->datetimetz.datetime.date)
5511  {
5512  result = 1;
5513  }
5514  else if (data1->datetimetz.datetime.time < data2->datetimetz.datetime.time)
5515  {
5516  result = -1;
5517  }
5518  else if (data1->datetimetz.datetime.time > data2->datetimetz.datetime.time)
5519  {
5520  result = 1;
5521  }
5522  else
5523  {
5524  result = 0;
5525  }
5526  break;
5527  case DB_TYPE_MONETARY:
5528  result = ((data1->money.amount < data2->money.amount)
5529  ? -1 : ((data1->money.amount > data2->money.amount) ? 1 : 0));
5530  break;
5531  default:
5532  /* not numeric type */
5533  result = 0;
5534  break;
5535  }
5536 
5537  return result;
5538 }
5539 
5540 /*
5541  * qo_estimate_statistics () - Make a wild-ass guess at the appropriate
5542  * statistics for this class. The statistics
5543  * manager doesn't know anything about this class,
5544  * so we're on our own.
5545  * return: nothing
5546  * class_mop(in): The mop of the class whose statistics need to be
5547  fabricated
5548  * statblock(in): The CLASS_STATS structure to be populated
5549  */
5550 static void
5551 qo_estimate_statistics (MOP class_mop, CLASS_STATS * statblock)
5552 {
5553  /*
5554  * It would be nice if we could the get the actual number of pages
5555  * allocated for the class; at least then we could make some sort of
5556  * realistic guess at the upper bound of the number of objects (we
5557  * can already figure out the "average" size of an object).
5558  *
5559  * Really, the statistics manager ought to be doing this on its own.
5560  */
5561 
5562  statblock->heap_num_pages = NOMINAL_HEAP_SIZE (class_mop);
5563  statblock->heap_num_objects = (statblock->heap_num_pages * DB_PAGESIZE) / NOMINAL_OBJECT_SIZE (class_mop);
5564 
5565 }
5566 
5567 /*
5568  * qo_env_new () -
5569  * return:
5570  * parser(in):
5571  * query(in):
5572  */
5573 static QO_ENV *
5574 qo_env_new (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query)
5575 {
5576  QO_ENV *env;
5577  PT_NODE *spec;
5578 
5579  env = (QO_ENV *) malloc (sizeof (QO_ENV));
5580  if (env == NULL)
5581  {
5582  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (QO_ENV));
5583  return NULL;
5584  }
5585 
5586  env->parser = parser;
5587  env->pt_tree = query;
5588  env->nsegs = 0;
5589  env->nnodes = 0;
5590  env->nedges = 0;
5591  env->neqclasses = 0;
5592  env->nterms = 0;
5593  env->nsubqueries = 0;
5594  env->npartitions = 0;
5595  env->final_plan = NULL;
5596  env->segs = NULL;
5597  env->nodes = NULL;
5598  env->eqclasses = NULL;
5599  env->terms = NULL;
5600  env->subqueries = NULL;
5601  env->partitions = NULL;
5602  bitset_init (&(env->final_segs), env);
5603  env->tmp_bitset = NULL;
5604  env->bail_out = 0;
5605  env->planner = NULL;
5606  env->dump_enable = prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_QO_DUMP);
5607  bitset_init (&(env->fake_terms), env);
5608  bitset_init (&QO_ENV_SORT_LIMIT_NODES (env), env);
5609  db_make_null (&QO_ENV_LIMIT_VALUE (env));
5610 
5611  assert (query->node_type == PT_SELECT);
5612  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (query, PT_SELECT_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA)
5613  || PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (query, PT_SELECT_FULL_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA) || query->is_system_generated_stmt
5614  || ((spec = query->info.query.q.select.from) != NULL && spec->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SHOWSTMT))
5615  {
5616  env->plan_dump_enabled = false;
5617  }
5618  else
5619  {
5620  env->plan_dump_enabled = true;
5621  }
5622  env->multi_range_opt_candidate = false;
5623 
5624  return env;
5625 }
