5666 /*
5667  * qo_env_free () -
5668  * return:
5669  * env(in):
5670  */
5671 void
5672 qo_env_free (QO_ENV * env)
5673 {
5674  if (env)
5675  {
5676  int i;
5677 
5678  /*
5679  * Be sure to use Nnodes, Nterms, and Nsegs as the loop limits in
5680  * the code below, because those are the sizes of the allocated
5681  * arrays; nnodes, nterms, and nsegs are the extents of those
5682  * arrays that were actually used, but the entries past those
5683  * extents need to be cleaned up too.
5684  */
5685 
5686  if (env->segs)
5687  {
5688  for (i = 0; i < env->Nsegs; ++i)
5689  {
5690  qo_seg_free (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i));
5691  }
5692  free_and_init (env->segs);
5693  }
5694 
5695  if (env->nodes)
5696  {
5697  for (i = 0; i < env->Nnodes; ++i)
5698  {
5699  qo_node_free (QO_ENV_NODE (env, i));
5700  }
5701  free_and_init (env->nodes);
5702  }
5703 
5704  if (env->eqclasses)
5705  {
5706  for (i = 0; i < env->neqclasses; ++i)
5707  {
5708  qo_eqclass_free (QO_ENV_EQCLASS (env, i));
5709  }
5710  free_and_init (env->eqclasses);
5711  }
5712 
5713  if (env->terms)
5714  {
5715  for (i = 0; i < env->Nterms; ++i)
5716  {
5717  qo_term_free (QO_ENV_TERM (env, i));
5718  }
5719  free_and_init (env->terms);
5720  }
5721 
5722  if (env->partitions)
5723  {
5724  for (i = 0; i < env->npartitions; ++i)
5725  {
5726  qo_partition_free (QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, i));
5727  }
5728  free_and_init (env->partitions);
5729  }
5730 
5731  if (env->subqueries)
5732  {
5733  for (i = 0; i < env->nsubqueries; ++i)
5734  {
5735  qo_subquery_free (&env->subqueries[i]);
5736  }
5737  free_and_init (env->subqueries);
5738  }
5739 
5740  bitset_delset (&(env->final_segs));
5741  bitset_delset (&(env->fake_terms));
5742  bitset_delset (&QO_ENV_SORT_LIMIT_NODES (env));
5743  pr_clear_value (&QO_ENV_LIMIT_VALUE (env));
5744 
5745  if (env->planner)
5746  {
5747  qo_planner_free (env->planner);
5748  }
5749 
5750  free_and_init (env);
5751  }
5752 }
5753 
5754 /*
5755  * qo_exchange () -
5756  * return:
5757  * t0(in):
5758  * t1(in):
5759  */
5760 static void
5761 qo_exchange (QO_TERM * t0, QO_TERM * t1)
5762 {
5763 
5764  /*
5765  * 'env' attribute is the same in both, don't bother with it.
5766  */
5767  TERMCLASS_EXCHANGE (t0->term_class, t1->term_class);
5768  BISET_EXCHANGE (t0->nodes, t1->nodes);
5769  BISET_EXCHANGE (t0->segments, t1->segments);
5770  DOUBLE_EXCHANGE (t0->selectivity, t1->selectivity);
5771  INT_EXCHANGE (t0->rank, t1->rank);
5772  PT_NODE_EXCHANGE (t0->pt_expr, t1->pt_expr);
5773  INT_EXCHANGE (t0->location, t1->location);
5774  BISET_EXCHANGE (t0->subqueries, t1->subqueries);
5775  JOIN_TYPE_EXCHANGE (t0->join_type, t1->join_type);
5776  INT_EXCHANGE (t0->can_use_index, t1->can_use_index);
5777  SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->index_seg[0], t1->index_seg[0]);
5778  SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->index_seg[1], t1->index_seg[1]);
5779  SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->seg, t1->seg);
5780  SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->oid_seg, t1->oid_seg);
5781  NODEPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->head, t1->head);
5782  NODEPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->tail, t1->tail);
5783  EQCLASSPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->eqclass, t1->eqclass);
5784  SEGMENTPTR_EXCHANGE (t0->nominal_seg, t1->nominal_seg);
5785  FLAG_EXCHANGE (t0->flag, t1->flag);
5786  /*
5787  * DON'T exchange the 'idx' values!
5788  */
5789 }
5790 
5791 /*
5792  * qo_discover_edges () -
5793  * return:
5794  * env(in):
5795  */
5796 static void
5797 qo_discover_edges (QO_ENV * env)
5798 {
5799  int i, j, n;
5800  QO_TERM *term, *edge, *edge2;
5801  QO_NODE *node;
5802  PT_NODE *pt_expr;
5803  int t;
5804  BITSET_ITERATOR iter;
5805  BITSET direct_nodes;
5806  int t1, t2;
5807  QO_TERM *term1, *term2;
5808 
5809  bitset_init (&direct_nodes, env);
5810 
5811  i = 0;
5812  n = env->nterms;
5813 
5814  while (i < n)
5815  {
5816  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
5817  if (QO_IS_EDGE_TERM (term))
5818  {
5819  env->nedges++;
5820  i++;
5821  }
5822  else
5823  {
5824  if (i < --n)
5825  {
5826  /*
5827  * Exchange the terms at the two boundaries. This moves
5828  * a known non-edge up to just below the section of other
5829  * non-edge terms, and moves a term of unknown "edgeness"
5830  * down to just above the section of known edges. Leave
5831  * the bottom boundary alone, but move the upper boundary
5832  * down one notch.
5833  */
5834  qo_exchange (QO_ENV_TERM (env, i), QO_ENV_TERM (env, n));
5835  }
5836  }
5837  }
5838 
5839  /* sort join-term on selectivity as descending order */
5840  for (t1 = 0; t1 < i - 1; t1++)
5841  {
5842  term1 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t1);
5843  for (t2 = t1 + 1; t2 < i; t2++)
5844  {
5845  term2 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t2);
5846  if (QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term1) < QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term2))
5847  {
5848  qo_exchange (term1, term2);
5849  }
5850  }
5851  }
5852  /* sort sarg-term on selectivity as descending order */
5853  for (t1 = i; t1 < env->nterms - 1; t1++)
5854  {
5855  term1 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t1);
5856  for (t2 = t1 + 1; t2 < env->nterms; t2++)
5857  {
5858  term2 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t2);
5859  if (QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term1) < QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term2))
5860  {
5861  qo_exchange (term1, term2);
5862  }
5863  }
5864  }
5865 
5866  for (n = env->nterms; i < n; i++)
5867  {
5868  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
5869  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_SARG)
5870  {
5871  QO_ASSERT (env, bitset_cardinality (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term))) == 1);
5872  qo_node_add_sarg (QO_ENV_NODE (env, bitset_first_member (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)))), term);
5873  }
5874  }
5875 
5876  /*
5877  * Check some invariants. If something has gone wrong during the
5878  * discovery phase to violate these invariants, it will mean certain
5879  * death for later phases, so we need to discover it now while it's
5880  * convenient.
5881  */
5882  for (i = 0, n = env->nedges; i < n; i++)
5883  {
5884  edge = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
5885  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_HEAD (edge) != NULL);
5886  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_TAIL (edge) != NULL);
5887 
5888  if (QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (edge) != JOIN_INNER && QO_TERM_CLASS (edge) != QO_TC_JOIN)
5889  {
5890  for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
5891  {
5892  edge2 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, j);
5893  if (i != j && bitset_is_equivalent (&(QO_TERM_NODES (edge)), &(QO_TERM_NODES (edge2))))
5894  {
5895  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (edge2) = QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (edge);
5896  }
5897  }
5898  }
5899 
5900  pt_expr = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (edge);
5901 
5902  /* check for always true transitive join term */
5903  if (pt_expr && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (pt_expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_TRANSITIVE))
5904  {
5905  BITSET_CLEAR (direct_nodes);
5906 
5907  for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
5908  {
5909  edge2 = QO_ENV_TERM (env, j);
5910  if (bitset_intersects (&(QO_TERM_NODES (edge2)), &(QO_TERM_NODES (edge))))
5911  {
5912  bitset_union (&direct_nodes, &(QO_TERM_NODES (edge2)));
5913  }
5914  } /* for (j = 0; ...) */
5915 
5916  /* check for direct connected nodes */
5917  for (t = bitset_iterate (&direct_nodes, &iter); t != -1; t = bitset_next_member (&iter))
5918  {
5919  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, t);
5920  if (!QO_NODE_SARGABLE (node))
5921  {
5922  break; /* give up */
5923  }
5924  }
5925 
5926  /* found dummy join edge. it is used for planning only */
5927  if (t == -1)
5928  {
5929  QO_TERM_CLASS (edge) = QO_TC_DUMMY_JOIN;
5930 
5931  /* keep out from m-join edge */
5932  QO_TERM_CLEAR_FLAG (edge, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE);
5933  }
5934  }
5935  }
5936 
5937  bitset_delset (&direct_nodes);
5938 }
5939 
5940 /*
5941  * qo_classify_outerjoin_terms () -
5942  * return:
5943  * env(in):
5944  *
5945  * Note:
5946  * Term Classify Matrix
5947  * --+-----+---------------------+----------+---------------+------------------
5948  * NO|Major|Minor |nidx_self |dep_set | Classify
5949  * --+-----+---------------------+----------+---------------+------------------
5950  * O1|ON |TC_sarg(on_conn) |!Right |!Outer(ex R_on)|TC_sarg(ow TC_dj)
5951  * O2|ON |TC_join |term_tail=|=on_node |TC_join(ow O3)
5952  * O3|ON |TC_other(n>0,on_conn)|- |!Outer(ex R_on)|TC_other(ow TC_dj)
5953  * O4|ON |TC_other(n==0) |- |- |TC_dj
5954  * W1|WHERE|TC_sarg |!Left |!Right |TC_sarg(ow TC_aj)
5955  * W2|WHERE|TC_join |!Outer |!Right |TC_join(ow TC_aj)
5956  * W3|WHERE|TC_other(n>0) |!Outer |!Right |TC_other(ow TC_aj)
5957  * W4|WHERE|TC_other(n==0) |- |- |TC_aj
5958  * --+-----+---------------------+----------+---------------+------------------
5959  */
5960 static void
5961 qo_classify_outerjoin_terms (QO_ENV * env)
5962 {
5963  bool is_null_padded;
5964  int n, i, t;
5965  BITSET_ITERATOR iter;
5966  QO_NODE *node, *on_node;
5967  QO_TERM *term;
5968  int nidx_self; /* node index of term */
5969  BITSET dep_set, prev_dep_set;
5970 
5971  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
5972  {
5973  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
5974  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) >= 0);
5975 
5976  if (QO_OUTER_JOIN_TERM (term))
5977  {
5978  break;
5979  }
5980  }
5981 
5982  if (i >= env->nterms)
5983  {
5984  return; /* not found outer join term; do nothing */
5985  }
5986 
5987  bitset_init (&dep_set, env);
5988  bitset_init (&prev_dep_set, env);
5989 
5990  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
5991  {
5992  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
5993  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) >= 0);
5994 
5995  on_node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term));
5996  QO_ASSERT (env, on_node != NULL);
5997 
5998  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
5999  {
6000  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (on_node) > 0);
6001  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node) > 0);
6002  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) != PT_JOIN_NONE);
6003 
6004  /* is explicit join ON cond */
6005  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) == QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node));
6006 
6007  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_INNER)
6008  {
6009  continue; /* is inner join; no need to classify */
6010  }
6011 
6012  /* is explicit outer-joined ON cond */
6013  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
6014  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER
6015  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER);
6016  }
6017  else
6018  {
6019  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (on_node) == 0);
6020  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node) == 0);
6021  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_NONE);
6022  }
6023 
6024  nidx_self = -1; /* init */
6025  for (t = bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &iter); t != -1; t = bitset_next_member (&iter))
6026  {
6027  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, t);
6028 
6029  nidx_self = MAX (nidx_self, QO_NODE_IDX (node));
6030  }
6031  QO_ASSERT (env, nidx_self < env->nnodes);
6032 
6033  /* nidx_self is -1 iff term nodes is empty */
6034 
6035  /* STEP 1: check nidx_self */
6036  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_SARG)
6037  {
6038  QO_ASSERT (env, nidx_self >= 0);
6039 
6040  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, nidx_self);
6041 
6042  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6043  {
6044  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER
6045  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
6046  {
6047  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DURING_JOIN;
6048  }
6049  }
6050  else
6051  {
6052  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
6053  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
6054  {
6055  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN;
6056  }
6057  }
6058  }
6059  else if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN)
6060  {
6061  QO_ASSERT (env, nidx_self >= 0);
6062 
6063  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, nidx_self);
6064 
6065  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6066  {
6067  /* is already checked at qo_analyze_term () */
6068  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)) == QO_NODE_IDX (on_node));
6069  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_HEAD (term)) < QO_NODE_IDX (QO_TERM_TAIL (term)));
6070  }
6071  else
6072  {
6073  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
6074  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER
6075  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
6076  {
6077  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN;
6078 
6079  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = NO_JOIN;
6080 
6081  /* keep out from m-join edge */
6082  QO_TERM_CLEAR_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE);
6083  }
6084  }
6085  }
6086  else if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_OTHER)
6087  {
6088  if (nidx_self >= 0)
6089  {
6090  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, nidx_self);
6091 
6092  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6093  {
6094  ; /* no restriction on nidx_self; go ahead */
6095  }
6096  else
6097  {
6098  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
6099  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER
6100  || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
6101  {
6102  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN;
6103  }
6104  }
6105  }
6106  else
6107  {
6108  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6109  {
6110  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DURING_JOIN;
6111  }
6112  else
6113  {
6114  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN;
6115  }
6116  }
6117  }
6118 
6119  if (!
6120  (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_SARG || QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN
6121  || QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_OTHER))
6122  {
6123  continue; /* no need to classify */
6124  }
6125 
6126  /* traverse outer-dep nodeset */
6127 
6128  QO_ASSERT (env, nidx_self >= 0);
6129 
6130  is_null_padded = false; /* init */
6131 
6132  BITSET_CLEAR (dep_set);
6133 
6134  bitset_add (&dep_set, nidx_self);
6135 
6136  do
6137  {
6138  bitset_assign (&prev_dep_set, &dep_set);
6139 
6140  for (n = 0; n < env->nnodes; n++)
6141  {
6142  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n);
6143 
6144  if (bitset_intersects (&dep_set, &(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node))))
6145  {
6146  bitset_add (&dep_set, QO_NODE_IDX (node));
6147  }
6148  }
6149  }
6150  while (!bitset_is_equivalent (&prev_dep_set, &dep_set));
6151 
6152  /* STEP 2: check iff term nodes are connected with ON cond */
6153  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6154  {
6155  if (!BITSET_MEMBER (dep_set, QO_NODE_IDX (on_node)))
6156  {
6157  is_null_padded = true;
6158  }
6159  }
6160 
6161  /* STEP 3: check outer-dep nodeset join type */
6162  bitset_remove (&dep_set, nidx_self); /* remove me */
6163  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6164  {
6165  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_TERM_LOCATION (term) == QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node));
6166 
6167  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (on_node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER)
6168  {
6169  bitset_remove (&dep_set, QO_NODE_IDX (on_node)); /* remove ON */
6170  }
6171  }
6172 
6173  for (t = bitset_iterate (&dep_set, &iter); t != -1 && !is_null_padded; t = bitset_next_member (&iter))
6174  {
6175  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, t);
6176 
6177  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6178  {
6179  if (QO_NODE_LOCATION (node) > QO_NODE_LOCATION (on_node))
6180  {
6181  continue; /* out of ON cond scope */
6182  }
6183 
6184  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER)
6185  {
6186  is_null_padded = true;
6187  }
6188  }
6189 
6190  if (QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER || QO_NODE_PT_JOIN_TYPE (node) == PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER)
6191  {
6192  is_null_padded = true;
6193  }
6194  }
6195 
6196  if (!is_null_padded)
6197  {
6198  continue; /* go ahead */
6199  }
6200 
6201  /* at here, found non-sargable node in outer-dep nodeset */
6202 
6203  if (QO_ON_COND_TERM (term))
6204  {
6205  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_DURING_JOIN;
6206  }
6207  else
6208  {
6209  QO_TERM_CLASS (term) = QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN;
6210  }
6211 
6212  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) != QO_TC_JOIN)
6213  {
6214  QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) = NO_JOIN;
6215 
6216  /* keep out from m-join edge */
6217  QO_TERM_CLEAR_FLAG (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE);
6218  }
6219 
6220  } /* for (i = 0; ...) */
6221 
6222  bitset_delset (&prev_dep_set);
6223  bitset_delset (&dep_set);
6224 }
6225 
6226 /*
6227  * qo_find_index_terms () - Find the terms which contain the passed segments
6228  * and terms which contain just the passed segments
6229  * return:
6230  * env(in): The environment used
6231  * segsp(in): Passed BITSET of interested segments
6232  * index_entry(in):
6233  */
6234 static void
6235 qo_find_index_terms (QO_ENV * env, BITSET * segsp, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry)
6236 {
6237  int t;
6238  QO_TERM *qo_termp;
6239 
6240  assert (index_entry != NULL);
6241 
6242  BITSET_CLEAR (index_entry->terms);
6243 
6244  /* traverse all terms */
6245  for (t = 0; t < env->nterms; t++)
6246  {
6247  /* get the pointer to QO_TERM structure */
6248  qo_termp = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t);
6249 
6250  /* Fake terms (e.g., dependency links) won't have pt_expr's associated with them. They can't be implemented as
6251  * indexed sargs, either, so don't worry about them here.
6252  */
6253  if (!QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (qo_termp))
6254  {
6255  continue;
6256  }
6257  /* 'qo_analyze_term()' function verifies that all indexable terms are expression so that they have 'pt_expr'
6258  * field of type PT_EXPR. */
6259 
6260  /* if the segments that give rise to the term are in the given segment set */
6261  if (bitset_intersects (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (qo_termp)), segsp))
6262  {
6263  /* collect this term */
6264  bitset_add (&(index_entry->terms), t);
6265  }
6266  } /* for (t = 0; t < env->nterms; t++) */
6267 
6268 }
6269 
6270 /*
6271  * qo_find_index_seg_terms () - Find the terms which contain the passed segment.
6272  * Only indexable and SARG terms are included
6273  * return:
6274  * env(in): The environment used
6275  * index_entry(in/out): Index entry
6276  * idx(in): Passed idx of an interested segment
6277  */
6278 static void
6279 qo_find_index_seg_terms (QO_ENV * env, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry, int idx)
6280 {
6281  int t;
6282  QO_TERM *qo_termp;
6283 
6284  /* traverse all terms */
6285  for (t = 0; t < env->nterms; t++)
6286  {
6287  /* get the pointer to QO_TERM structure */
6288  qo_termp = QO_ENV_TERM (env, t);
6289 
6290  /* ignore this term if it is not marked as indexable by 'qo_analyze_term()' */
6291  if (!qo_termp->can_use_index)
6292  {
6293  continue;
6294  }
6295 
6296  /* Fake terms (e.g., dependency links) won't have pt_expr's associated with them. They can't be implemented as
6297  * indexed sargs, either, so don't worry about them here.
6298  */
6299  if (!QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (qo_termp))
6300  {
6301  continue;
6302  }
6303  /* 'qo_analyze_term()' function verifies that all indexable terms are expression so that they have 'pt_expr'
6304  * field of type PT_EXPR.
6305  */
6306 
6307  /* if the term is sarg and the given segment is involed in the expression that gives rise to the term */
6308  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (qo_termp) == QO_TC_SARG && BITSET_MEMBER (QO_TERM_SEGS (qo_termp), index_entry->seg_idxs[idx]))
6309  {
6310  /* check for range list term; RANGE (r1, r2, ...) */
6311  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (qo_termp, QO_TERM_RANGELIST))
6312  {
6313  if (index_entry->rangelist_seg_idx != -1)
6314  {
6315  continue; /* already found. give up */
6316  }
6317 
6318  /* is the first time */
6319  index_entry->rangelist_seg_idx = idx;
6320  }
6321 
6322  /* collect this term */
6323  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (qo_termp, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP))
6324  {
6325  bitset_add (&(index_entry->seg_equal_terms[idx]), t);
6326  }
6327  else
6328  {
6329  bitset_add (&(index_entry->seg_other_terms[idx]), t);
6330  }
6331  }
6332 
6333  } /* for (t = 0; ... */
6334 
6335 }
6336 
6337 /*
6338  * is_equivalent_indexes () - Compare the two index entries
6339  * return: True/False
6340  * index1(in): First index entry
6341  * index2(in): Second index entry
6342  *
6343  * Note: Return true if they are equivalent
6344  * and false otherwise. In order to be equivalent, the index entries
6345  * must contain the same segments specified in the same order
6346  */
6347 static int
6348 is_equivalent_indexes (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index1, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index2)
6349 {
6350  int i, equivalent;
6351 
6352  /*
6353  * If the number of segments is different, then the indexes can't
6354  * be equivalent (cheap test).
6355  */
6356  if (index1->nsegs != index2->nsegs)
6357  {
6358  return false;
6359  }
6360 
6361  /*
6362  * Now compare the two indexes element by element
6363  */
6364  equivalent = true;
6365  for (i = 0; i < index1->nsegs; i++)
6366  {
6367  if ((index1->seg_idxs[i]) != (index2->seg_idxs[i]))
6368  {
6369  equivalent = false;
6370  break;
6371  }
6372  }
6373 
6374  return equivalent;
6375 }
6376 
6377 /*
6378  * qo_find_matching_index () -
6379  * return: int (index of matching index entry, or -1)
6380  * index_entry(in): Index entry to match
6381  * class_indexes(in): Array of index entries to search
6382  *
6383  * Note:
6384  * Given a index entry, search the index array looking for a match.
6385  * The array index of the matching entry is returned (if found).
6386  * A -1 is returned if a matching entry is not found.
6387  *
6388  * Indexes which are already a part of a heirarchical compatible index
6389  * list are not considered (these are identifialbe since their next
6390  * pointer is non-NULL).
6391  */
6392 static int
6393 qo_find_matching_index (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry, QO_INDEX * class_indexes)
6394 {
6395  int i;
6396 
6397  for (i = 0; i < class_indexes->n; i++)
6398  {
6399  /*
6400  * A matching index is found if the index node is not already a member
6401  * of a heirarchical compatible index list (i.e. next pointer is NULL)
6402  * and if it matches the passes <index_entry>.
6403  */
6404  if (QO_INDEX_INDEX (class_indexes, i)->next == NULL
6405  && is_equivalent_indexes (index_entry, QO_INDEX_INDEX (class_indexes, i)))
6406  {
6407  break;
6408  }
6409  }
6410 
6411  /*
6412  * If a match is found, return its index, otherwise return -1
6413  */
6414  if (i < class_indexes->n)
6415  {
6416  return i;
6417  }
6418  else
6419  {
6420  return -1;
6421  }
6422 }
6423 
6424 /*
6425  * is_index_compatible () -
6426  * return: int (True/False)
6427  * class_info(in): Class info structure
6428  * n(in): Index into class info structure. This determines the level
6429  * in the class hierarchy that we're currently concerned with
6430  * index_entry(in): Index entry to match against
6431  *
6432  * Note:
6433  * This is a recursive function which is used to verify that a
6434  * given index entry is compatible across the class hierarchy.
6435  * An index entry is compatible if there exists an index definition
6436  * on the same sequence of attributes at each level in the class
6437  * hierarchy. If the index entry is compatible, the entry will be
6438  * marked as such throughout the hierarchy.
6439  */
6440 static QO_INDEX_ENTRY *
6441 is_index_compatible (QO_CLASS_INFO * class_info, int n, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry)
6442 {
6443  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *class_entry;
6444  QO_INDEX *class_indexes;
6445  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *index;
6446  int i;
6447 
6448  if (n >= class_info->n)
6449  {
6450  return NULL;
6451  }
6452 
6453  class_entry = &(class_info->info[n]);
6454  class_indexes = class_entry->index;
6455 
6456  i = qo_find_matching_index (index_entry, class_indexes);
6457  if (i < 0)
6458  {
6459  return NULL;
6460  }
6461 
6462  index = QO_INDEX_INDEX (class_indexes, i);
6463  if (n == (class_info->n - 1))
6464  {
6465  index->next = NULL;
6466  return index;
6467  }
6468  else
6469  {
6470  index->next = is_index_compatible (class_info, n + 1, index);
6471  if (index->next == NULL)
6472  {
6473  return NULL;
6474  }
6475  else
6476  {
6477  return index;
6478  }
6479  }
6480 
6481 /* return NULL;*/
6482 }
6483 
6484 /*
6485  * qo_find_index_segs () -
6486  * return:
6487  * env(in):
6488  * consp(in):
6489  * nodep(in):
6490  * seg_idx(in):
6491  * seg_idx_num(in):
6492  * nseg_idxp(in):
6493  * segs(in):
6494  */
6495 static bool
6496 qo_find_index_segs (QO_ENV * env, SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT * consp, QO_NODE * nodep, int *seg_idx, int seg_idx_num,
6497  int *nseg_idxp, BITSET * segs)
6498 {
6499  QO_SEGMENT *segp;
6500  SM_ATTRIBUTE *attrp;
6501  BITSET working;
6502  BITSET_ITERATOR iter;
6503  int i, iseg;
6504  bool matched;
6505  int count_matched_index_attributes = 0;
6506 
6507  /* working set; indexed segments */
6508  bitset_init (&working, env);
6509  bitset_assign (&working, &(QO_NODE_SEGS (nodep)));
6510 
6511  /* for each attribute of this constraint */
6512  for (i = 0; *nseg_idxp < seg_idx_num; i++)
6513  {
6514 
6515  if (consp->func_index_info && i == consp->func_index_info->col_id)
6516  {
6517  matched = false;
6518  for (iseg = bitset_iterate (&working, &iter); iseg != -1; iseg = bitset_next_member (&iter))
6519  {
6520  segp = QO_ENV_SEG (env, iseg);
6521  if (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (segp) == true
6522  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_SEG_NAME (segp), consp->func_index_info->expr_str))
6523  {
6524  bitset_add (segs, iseg); /* add the segment to the index segment set */
6525  bitset_remove (&working, iseg); /* remove the segment from the working set */
6526  seg_idx[*nseg_idxp] = iseg; /* remember the order of the index segments */
6527  (*nseg_idxp)++; /* number of index segments, 'seg_idx[]' */
6528  /* If we're handling with a multi-column index, then only equality expressions are allowed except for
6529  * the last matching segment.
6530  */
6531  bitset_delset (&working);
6532  matched = true;
6533  count_matched_index_attributes++;
6534  break;
6535  }
6536  }
6537  if (!matched)
6538  {
6539  seg_idx[*nseg_idxp] = -1; /* not found matched segment */
6540  (*nseg_idxp)++; /* number of index segments, 'seg_idx[]' */
6541  } /* if (!matched) */
6542  }
6543 
6544  if (*nseg_idxp == seg_idx_num)
6545  {
6546  break;
6547  }
6548  attrp = consp->attributes[i];
6549 
6550  matched = false;
6551  /* for each indexed segments of this node, compare the name of the segment with the one of the attribute */
6552  for (iseg = bitset_iterate (&working, &iter); iseg != -1; iseg = bitset_next_member (&iter))
6553  {
6554 
6555  segp = QO_ENV_SEG (env, iseg);
6556 
6557  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (QO_SEG_NAME (segp), attrp->header.name))
6558  {
6559 
6560  bitset_add (segs, iseg); /* add the segment to the index segment set */
6561  bitset_remove (&working, iseg); /* remove the segment from the working set */
6562  seg_idx[*nseg_idxp] = iseg; /* remember the order of the index segments */
6563  (*nseg_idxp)++; /* number of index segments, 'seg_idx[]' */
6564  /* If we're handling with a multi-column index, then only equality expressions are allowed except for the
6565  * last matching segment.
6566  */
6567  matched = true;
6568  count_matched_index_attributes++;
6569  break;
6570  } /* if (!intl_identifier_casecmp...) */
6571 
6572  } /* for (iseg = bitset_iterate(&working, &iter); ...) */
6573 
6574  if (!matched)
6575  {
6576  seg_idx[*nseg_idxp] = -1; /* not found matched segment */
6577  (*nseg_idxp)++; /* number of index segments, 'seg_idx[]' */
6578  } /* if (!matched) */
6579 
6580  } /* for (i = 0; consp->attributes[i]; i++) */
6581 
6582  bitset_delset (&working);
6583 
6584  return count_matched_index_attributes > 0;
6585  /* this index is feasible to use if at least one attribute of index is specified(matched) */
6586 }
6587 
6588 /*
6589  * qo_is_coverage_index () - check if the index cover all query segments
6590  * return: bool
6591  * env(in): The environment
6592  * nodep(in): The node
6593  * index_entry(in): The index entry
6594  */
6595 static bool
6596 qo_is_coverage_index (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * nodep, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry)
6597 {
6598  int i, j, seg_idx;
6599  QO_SEGMENT *seg;
6600  bool found;
6601  QO_CLASS_INFO *class_infop = NULL;
6602  QO_NODE *seg_nodep = NULL;
6603  QO_TERM *qo_termp;
6604  PT_NODE *pt_node;
6605 
6606  if (env == NULL || nodep == NULL || index_entry == NULL)
6607  {
6608  return false;
6609  }
6610 
6611  /*
6612  * If NO_COVERING_IDX hint is given, we do not generate a plan for
6613  * covering index scan.
6614  */
6615  QO_ASSERT (env, QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env)->node_type == PT_SELECT);
6616  if (QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env)->node_type == PT_SELECT
6617  && (QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env)->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_NO_COVERING_IDX))
6618  {
6619  return false;
6620  }
6621 
6622  for (i = 0; i < index_entry->nsegs; i++)
6623  {
6624  seg_idx = (index_entry->seg_idxs[i]);
6625  if (seg_idx == -1)
6626  {
6627  continue;
6628  }
6629 
6630  /* We do not use covering index if there is a path expression */
6631  seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, seg_idx);
6632  pt_node = QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg);
6633  if (pt_node->node_type == PT_DOT_ || (pt_node->node_type == PT_NAME && pt_node->info.name.resolved == NULL))
6634  {
6635  return false;
6636  }
6637  }
6638 
6639  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; i++)
6640  {
6641  seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, i);
6642 
6643  if (seg == NULL)
6644  {
6645  continue;
6646  }
6647 
6648  if (QO_SEG_IS_OID_SEG (seg))
6649  {
6650  found = false;
6651  for (j = 0; j < env->nterms; j++)
6652  {
6653  qo_termp = QO_ENV_TERM (env, j);
6654  if (BITSET_MEMBER (QO_TERM_SEGS (qo_termp), i))
6655  {
6656  found = true;
6657  break;
6658  }
6659  }
6660 
6661  if (found == false)
6662  {
6663  continue;
6664  }
6665  }
6666 
6667  /* the segment should belong to the given node */
6668  seg_nodep = QO_SEG_HEAD (seg);
6669  if (seg_nodep == NULL || seg_nodep != nodep)
6670  {
6671  continue;
6672  }
6673 
6674  class_infop = QO_NODE_INFO (seg_nodep);
6675  if (class_infop == NULL || !(class_infop->info[0].normal_class))
6676  {
6677  return false;
6678  }
6679  QO_ASSERT (env, class_infop->n > 0);
6680 
6681  found = false;
6682  for (j = 0; j < class_infop->n; j++)
6683  {
6684  if (class_infop->info[j].mop == index_entry->class_->mop)
6685  {
6686  found = true;
6687  break;
6688  }
6689  }
6690  if (!found)
6691  {
6692  continue;
6693  }
6694 
6695  found = false;
6696  for (j = 0; j < index_entry->col_num; j++)
6697  {
6698  if (index_entry->seg_idxs[j] == QO_SEG_IDX (seg))
6699  {
6700  /* if the segment created in respect to the function index info is covered, we do not use index covering */
6701  if (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (seg))
6702  {
6703  return false;
6704  }
6705  found = true;
6706  break;
6707  }
6708  }
6709  if (!found)
6710  {
6711  return false;
6712  }
6713  }
6714 
6715  return true;
6716 }
6717 
6718 /*
6719  * qo_get_ils_prefix_length () - get prefix length of loose scan
6720  * returns: prefix length or -1 if loose scan not possible
6721  * env(in): environment
6722  * nodep(in): graph node
6723  * index_entry(in): index structure
6724  */
6725 static int
6726 qo_get_ils_prefix_length (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * nodep, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry)
6727 {
6728  PT_NODE *tree;
6729  int prefix_len = 0, i;
6730 
6731  /* check for nulls */
6732  if (env == NULL || nodep == NULL || index_entry == NULL)
6733  {
6734  return 0;
6735  }
6736 
6737  /* loose scan has no point on single column index */
6738  if (!QO_ENTRY_MULTI_COL (index_entry))
6739  {
6740  return 0;
6741  }
6742  assert (index_entry->nsegs > 1);
6743 
6744  tree = env->pt_tree;
6745  QO_ASSERT (env, tree != NULL);
6746 
6747  if (tree->node_type != PT_SELECT)
6748  {
6749  return 0; /* not applicable */
6750  }
6751 
6752  /* check hint */
6753  if (tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_NO_INDEX_LS)
6754  {
6755  return 0; /* disable loose index scan */
6756  }
6757  else if ((tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_LS) && (QO_NODE_HINT (nodep) & PT_HINT_INDEX_LS))
6758  { /* enable loose index scan */
6759  if (tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_NO_INDEX_SS || !(tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS)
6760  || !(QO_NODE_HINT (nodep) & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS))
6761  { /* skip scan is disabled */
6762  ; /* go ahead */
6763  }
6764  else
6765  { /* skip scan is enabled */
6766  return 0;
6767  }
6768  }
6769  else
6770  {
6771  return 0; /* no hint */
6772  }
6773 
6774  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (tree, PT_SELECT_INFO_DISABLE_LOOSE_SCAN))
6775  {
6776  return 0; /* not applicable */
6777  }
6778 
6779  if (index_entry->cover_segments
6780  && (tree->info.query.all_distinct == PT_DISTINCT || PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (tree, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_AGG)))
6781  {
6782  /* this is a select, index is covering all segments and it's either a DISTINCT query or GROUP BY query with
6783  * DISTINCT functions
6784  */
6785 
6786  /* see if only a prefix of the index is used */
6787  for (i = index_entry->nsegs - 1; i >= 0; i--)
6788  {
6789  if (index_entry->seg_idxs[i] != -1)
6790  {
6791  prefix_len = i + 1;
6792  break;
6793  }
6794  }
6795  }
6796  else
6797  {
6798  /* not applicable */
6799  return 0;
6800  }
6801 
6802  /* no need to continue if no prefix detected */
6803  if (prefix_len == -1 || prefix_len == index_entry->col_num)
6804  {
6805  return 0;
6806  }
6807 
6808  if (!pt_is_single_tuple (env->parser, env->pt_tree))
6809  {
6810  /* if not a single tuple query, then we either have a GROUP BY clause or we don't have any kind of aggregation;
6811  * in these cases, pure NULL keys qualify iff no terms are used
6812  */
6813  if (bitset_cardinality (&index_entry->terms) <= 0)
6814  {
6815  /* no terms specified, so NULL keys can't be skipped; disable ILS */
6816  return 0;
6817  }
6818  }
6819 
6820  /* all done */
6821  return prefix_len;
6822 }
6823 
6824 /*
6825  * qo_is_iss_index () - check if we can use the Index Skip Scan optimization
6826  * return: bool
6827  * env(in): The environment
6828  * nodep(in): The node
6829  * index_entry(in): The index entry
6830  *
6831  * Notes: The Index Skip Scan optimization applies when there is no term
6832  * involving the first index column, but there are other terms that
6833  * refer to the second, third etc columns, and the first column has
6834  * few distinct values: in this case, multiple index scans (one for
6835  * each value of the first column) can be faster than an index scan.
6836  */
6837 static bool
6838 qo_is_iss_index (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * nodep, QO_INDEX_ENTRY * index_entry)
6839 {
6840  int i;
6841  PT_NODE *tree;
6842  bool first_col_present = false, second_col_present = false;
6843 
6844  if (env == NULL || nodep == NULL || index_entry == NULL)
6845  {
6846  return false;
6847  }
6848 
6849  /* Index skip scan (ISS) candidates: - have no range or key filter terms for the first column of the index; - DO have
6850  * range or key filter terms for at least the second column of the index (maybe even for further columns, but we are
6851  * only interested in the second column right now); - obviously are multi-column indexes - not a filter index - not
6852  * with HQ
6853  */
6854 
6855  /* ISS has no meaning on single column indexes */
6856  if (!QO_ENTRY_MULTI_COL (index_entry))
6857  {
6858  return false;
6859  }
6860  assert (index_entry->nsegs > 1);
6861 
6862  tree = env->pt_tree;
6863  QO_ASSERT (env, tree != NULL);
6864 
6865  if (tree->node_type != PT_SELECT)
6866  {
6867  return false;
6868  }
6869 
6870  /* CONNECT BY messes with the terms, so just refuse any index skip scan in this case */
6871  if (tree->info.query.q.select.connect_by)
6872  {
6873  return false;
6874  }
6875 
6876  /* check hint */
6877  if (tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_NO_INDEX_SS || !(tree->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS)
6878  || !(QO_NODE_HINT (nodep) & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS))
6879  {
6880  return false;
6881  }
6882 
6883  assert (index_entry->constraints != NULL);
6884 
6885  /* do not allow filter ISS with filter index */
6886  if (index_entry->constraints->filter_predicate != NULL)
6887  {
6888  return false;
6889  }
6890 
6891  /* do not allow filter ISS with function index */
6892  for (i = 0; i < index_entry->nsegs; i++)
6893  {
6894  if ((index_entry->seg_idxs[i] != -1) && (QO_SEG_FUNC_INDEX (QO_ENV_SEG (env, index_entry->seg_idxs[i]))))
6895  {
6896  return false;
6897  }
6898  }
6899 
6900  /* First segment index should be missing */
6901  first_col_present = false;
6902  if (index_entry->seg_idxs[0] != -1)
6903  {
6904  /* it's not enough to have a reference to a segment in seg_idxs[], we must make sure there is an indexable term
6905  * that uses it: this means either an equal term, or an "other" term that is real (i.e. it is not a full range
6906  * scan term "invented" by pt_check_orderby to help with generating index covering.
6907  */
6908 
6909  if (bitset_cardinality (&(index_entry->seg_equal_terms[0])) > 0
6910  || bitset_cardinality (&(index_entry->seg_other_terms[0])) > 0)
6911  {
6912  first_col_present = true;
6913  }
6914  }
6915 
6916  if (first_col_present)
6917  {
6918  return false;
6919  }
6920 
6921  second_col_present = false;
6922  if (index_entry->seg_idxs[1] != -1)
6923  {
6924  /* it's not enough to have a reference to a segment in seg_idxs[], we must make sure there is an indexable term
6925  * that uses it: this means either an equal term, or an "other" term that is real (i.e. it is not a full range
6926  * scan term "invented" by pt_check_orderby to help with generating index covering.
6927  */
6928 
6929  if (bitset_cardinality (&(index_entry->seg_equal_terms[1])) > 0
6930  || bitset_cardinality (&(index_entry->seg_other_terms[1])) > 0)
6931  {
6932  second_col_present = true;
6933  }
6934  }
6935 
6936  if (!second_col_present)
6937  {
6938  return false;
6939  }
6940 
6941  /* The first col is missing, and the second col is present and has terms that can be used in a range search. Go ahead
6942  * and approve the index as a candidate for index skip scanning. We still have a long way ahead of us (use statistics
6943  * to decide whether index skip scan is the best approach) but we've made the first step.
6944  */
6945  return true;
6946 }
6947 
6948 static bool
6949 qo_is_usable_index (SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT * constraint, QO_NODE * nodep)
6950 {
6951  if (!SM_IS_CONSTRAINT_INDEX_FAMILY (constraint->type))
6952  {
6953  // not an index
6954  return false;
6955  }
6956 
6957  if (constraint->index_status != SM_NORMAL_INDEX && constraint->index_status != SM_ONLINE_INDEX_BUILDING_DONE)
6958  {
6959  // building or invisible
6960  return false;
6961  }
6962 
6963  if (constraint->filter_predicate != NULL && QO_NODE_USING_INDEX (nodep) == NULL)
6964  {
6965  return false;
6966  }
6967 
6968  return true;
6969 }
6970 
6971 /*
6972  * qo_find_node_indexes () -
6973  * return:
6974  * env(in): The environment to be updated
6975  * nodep(in): The node to be updated
6976  *
6977  * Note: Scan the class constraints associated with the node. If
6978  * a match is found between a class constraint and the
6979  * segments, then add an QO_INDEX to the node. A match
6980  * occurs when the class constraint attribute are a subset
6981  * of the segments. We currently consider SM_CONSTRAINT_INDEX
6982  * and SM_CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE constraint types.
6983  */
6984 static void
6985 qo_find_node_indexes (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * nodep)
6986 {
6987  int i, j, n, col_num;
6988  QO_CLASS_INFO *class_infop;
6989  QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY *class_entryp;
6990  QO_USING_INDEX *uip;
6991  QO_INDEX *indexp;
6992  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *index_entryp;
6993  QO_NODE_INDEX *node_indexp;
6994  QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY *ni_entryp;
6995  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *constraints, *consp;
6996  int *seg_idx, seg_idx_arr[NELEMENTS], nseg_idx;
6997  bool found, is_hint_use, is_hint_ignore, is_hint_force, is_hint_all_except;
6998  BITSET index_segs, index_terms;
6999  bool special_index_scan = false;
7000 
7001  /* information of classes underlying this node */
7002  class_infop = QO_NODE_INFO (nodep);
7003 
7004  if (class_infop->n <= 0)
7005  {
7006  return; /* no classes, nothing to do process */
7007  }
7008 
7009  if (PT_SPEC_SPECIAL_INDEX_SCAN (QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (nodep)))
7010  {
7011  if (QO_NODE_USING_INDEX (nodep) == NULL)
7012  {
7013  assert (0);
7014  return;
7015  }
7016  special_index_scan = true;
7017  }
7018 
7019  /* for each class in the hierarchy, search the class constraint cache looking for applicable indexes(UNIQUE and INDEX
7020  * constraint)
7021  */
7022  for (i = 0; i < class_infop->n; i++)
7023  {
7024 
7025  /* class information entry */
7026  class_entryp = &(class_infop->info[i]);
7027 
7028  if (qo_is_non_mvcc_class_with_index (class_entryp))
7029  {
7030  /* Do not use index of db_serial/db_has_apply_info for scanning. Current index scanning is optimized for
7031  * MVCC, while db_serial and db_ha_apply_info have MVCC disabled.
7032  */
7033  constraints = NULL;
7034  }
7035  else
7036  {
7037  /* get constraints of the class */
7038  constraints = sm_class_constraints (class_entryp->mop);
7039  }
7040 
7041  /* count the number of INDEX and UNIQUE constraints contained in this class */
7042  n = 0;
7043  for (consp = constraints; consp; consp = consp->next)
7044  {
7045  if (qo_is_usable_index (consp, nodep))
7046  {
7047  n++;
7048  }
7049  }
7050 
7051  /* allocate room for the constraint indexes */
7052  /* we don't have apriori knowledge about which constraints will be applied, so allocate room for all of them */
7053  /* qo_alloc_index(env, n) will allocate QO_INDEX structure and QO_INDEX_ENTRY structure array */
7054  indexp = class_entryp->index = qo_alloc_index (env, n);
7055  if (indexp == NULL)
7056  {
7057  return;
7058  }
7059 
7060  indexp->n = 0;
7061 
7062  /* for each constraint of the class */
7063  for (consp = constraints; consp; consp = consp->next)
7064  {
7065  if (!qo_is_usable_index (consp, nodep))
7066  {
7067  continue; // skip it
7068  }
7069 
7070  uip = QO_NODE_USING_INDEX (nodep);
7071  j = -1;
7072  if (uip)
7073  {
7074  if (QO_UI_N (uip) == 0)
7075  {
7076  /* USING INDEX NONE case, skip */
7077  continue;
7078  }
7079 
7080  /* search USING INDEX list */
7081  found = false;
7082  is_hint_use = is_hint_force = is_hint_ignore = false;
7083  is_hint_all_except = false;
7084 
7085  /* gather information */
7086  for (j = 0; j < QO_UI_N (uip); j++)
7087  {
7088  switch (QO_UI_FORCE (uip, j))
7089  {
7090  case PT_IDX_HINT_USE:
7091  is_hint_use = true;
7092  break;
7093  case PT_IDX_HINT_FORCE:
7094  is_hint_force = true;
7095  break;
7096  case PT_IDX_HINT_IGNORE:
7097  is_hint_ignore = true;
7098  break;
7099  case PT_IDX_HINT_ALL_EXCEPT:
7100  is_hint_all_except = true;
7101  break;
7102  }
7103  }
7104 
7105  /* search for index in using_index clause */
7106  for (j = 0; j < QO_UI_N (uip); j++)
7107  {
7108  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (consp->name, QO_UI_INDEX (uip, j)))
7109  {
7110  found = true;
7111  break;
7112  }
7113  }
7114 
7115  if (QO_UI_FORCE (uip, 0) == PT_IDX_HINT_ALL_EXCEPT)
7116  {
7117  /* USING INDEX ALL EXCEPT case */
7118  if (found)
7119  {
7120  /* this constraint(index) is specified in USING INDEX ALL EXCEPT clause; do not use it */
7121  continue;
7122  }
7123  if (consp->filter_predicate != NULL)
7124  {
7125  /* don't use filter indexes unless specified */
7126  continue;
7127  }
7128  j = -1;
7129  }
7130  else if (is_hint_force || is_hint_use)
7131  {
7132  /* if any indexes are forced or used, use them */
7133  if (!found || QO_UI_FORCE (uip, j) == PT_IDX_HINT_IGNORE)
7134  {
7135  continue;
7136  }
7137  }
7138  else
7139  {
7140  /* no indexes are used or forced, only ignored */
7141  if (found)
7142  {
7143  /* found as ignored; don't use */
7144  continue;
7145  }
7146  if (consp->filter_predicate != NULL)
7147  {
7148  /* don't use filter indexes unless specified */
7149  continue;
7150  }
7151  j = -1;
7152  }
7153  }
7154 
7155  bitset_init (&index_segs, env);
7156  bitset_init (&index_terms, env);
7157  nseg_idx = 0;
7158 
7159  /* count the number of columns on this constraint */
7160  for (col_num = 0; consp->attributes[col_num]; col_num++)
7161  {
7162  ;
7163  }
7164  if (consp->func_index_info)
7165  {
7166  col_num = consp->func_index_info->attr_index_start + 1;
7167  }
7168 
7169  if (col_num <= NELEMENTS)
7170  {
7171  seg_idx = seg_idx_arr;
7172  }
7173  else
7174  {
7175  /* allocate seg_idx */
7176  seg_idx = (int *) malloc (sizeof (int) * col_num);
7177  if (seg_idx == NULL)
7178  {
7179  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (int) * col_num);
7180  /* cannot allocate seg_idx, use seg_idx_arr instead. */
7181  seg_idx = seg_idx_arr;
7182  col_num = NELEMENTS;
7183  }
7184  }
7185 
7186  /* find indexed segments into 'seg_idx[]' */
7187  found = qo_find_index_segs (env, consp, nodep, seg_idx, col_num, &nseg_idx, &index_segs);
7188  /* 'seg_idx[nseg_idx]' array contains index no.(idx) of the segments which are found and applicable to this
7189  * index(constraint) as search key in the order of the index key attribute. For example, if the index
7190  * consists of attributes 'b' and 'a', and the given segments of the node are 'a(1)', 'b(2)' and 'c(3)', then
7191  * the result of 'seg_idx[]' will be '{ 2, 1, -1 }'. The value -1 in 'seg_idx[] array means that no segment
7192  * is specified.
7193  */
7194  /* If key information is required, no index segments will be found, but index scan has to be forced. */
7195  if (found == true || special_index_scan == true)
7196  {
7197  /* if applicable index was found, add it to the node */
7198 
7199  /* fill in QO_INDEX_ENTRY structure */
7200  index_entryp = QO_INDEX_INDEX (indexp, indexp->n);
7201  index_entryp->nsegs = nseg_idx;
7202  index_entryp->seg_idxs = NULL;
7203  index_entryp->rangelist_seg_idx = -1;
7204  index_entryp->seg_equal_terms = NULL;
7205  index_entryp->seg_other_terms = NULL;
7206  if (index_entryp->nsegs > 0)
7207  {
7208  size_t size;
7209 
7210  size = sizeof (int) * index_entryp->nsegs;
7211  index_entryp->seg_idxs = (int *) malloc (size);
7212  if (index_entryp->seg_idxs == NULL)
7213  {
7214  if (seg_idx != seg_idx_arr)
7215  {
7216  free_and_init (seg_idx);
7217  }
7218  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
7219  return;
7220  }
7221 
7222  size = sizeof (BITSET) * index_entryp->nsegs;
7223  index_entryp->seg_equal_terms = (BITSET *) malloc (size);
7224  if (index_entryp->seg_equal_terms == NULL)
7225  {
7226  free_and_init (index_entryp->seg_idxs);
7227  if (seg_idx != seg_idx_arr)
7228  {
7229  free_and_init (seg_idx);
7230  }
7231  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
7232  return;
7233  }
7234  index_entryp->seg_other_terms = (BITSET *) malloc (size);
7235  if (index_entryp->seg_other_terms == NULL)
7236  {
7237  free_and_init (index_entryp->seg_equal_terms);
7238  free_and_init (index_entryp->seg_idxs);
7239  if (seg_idx != seg_idx_arr)
7240  {
7241  free_and_init (seg_idx);
7242  }
7243  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, size);
7244  return;
7245  }
7246  }
7247  index_entryp->class_ = class_entryp;
7248  /* j == -1 iff no USING INDEX or USING INDEX ALL EXCEPT */
7249  index_entryp->force = (j == -1) ? 0 : QO_UI_FORCE (uip, j);
7250  index_entryp->col_num = col_num;
7251  index_entryp->key_type = NULL;
7252  index_entryp->constraints = consp;
7253 
7254  /* set key limits */
7255  index_entryp->key_limit = (j == -1) ? NULL : QO_UI_KEYLIMIT (uip, j);
7256 
7257  /* assign seg_idx[] and seg_terms[] */
7258  for (j = 0; j < index_entryp->nsegs; j++)
7259  {
7260  bitset_init (&(index_entryp->seg_equal_terms[j]), env);
7261  bitset_init (&(index_entryp->seg_other_terms[j]), env);
7262  index_entryp->seg_idxs[j] = seg_idx[j];
7263  if (index_entryp->seg_idxs[j] != -1)
7264  {
7265  qo_find_index_seg_terms (env, index_entryp, j);
7266  }
7267  }
7268  qo_find_index_terms (env, &index_segs, index_entryp);
7269 
7270  index_entryp->cover_segments = qo_is_coverage_index (env, nodep, index_entryp);
7271 
7272  index_entryp->is_iss_candidate = qo_is_iss_index (env, nodep, index_entryp);
7273 
7274  /* disable loose scan if skip scan is possible */
7275  if (index_entryp->is_iss_candidate == true)
7276  {
7277  index_entryp->ils_prefix_len = 0;
7278  }
7279  else
7280  {
7281  index_entryp->ils_prefix_len = qo_get_ils_prefix_length (env, nodep, index_entryp);
7282  }
7283 
7284  index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name = NULL;
7285  index_entryp->is_func_index = false;
7286 
7287  if (index_entryp->col_num > 0)
7288  {
7289  const char *temp_name = NULL;
7290 
7291  if (consp->func_index_info && consp->func_index_info->col_id == 0)
7292  {
7293  index_entryp->is_func_index = true;
7294  }
7295  if (!index_entryp->is_func_index && consp->attributes && consp->attributes[0])
7296  {
7297  temp_name = consp->attributes[0]->header.name;
7298  if (temp_name)
7299  {
7300  size_t len = strlen (temp_name) + 1;
7301  index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name = (char *) malloc (sizeof (char) * len);
7302  if (index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name == NULL)
7303  {
7304  if (seg_idx != seg_idx_arr)
7305  {
7306  free_and_init (seg_idx);
7307  }
7308  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
7309  sizeof (char) * len);
7310  return;
7311  }
7312  strcpy (index_entryp->statistics_attribute_name, temp_name);
7313  }
7314  }
7315  }
7316 
7317  (indexp->n)++;
7318 
7319  }
7320 
7321  bitset_delset (&(index_segs));
7322  bitset_delset (&(index_terms));
7323  if (seg_idx != seg_idx_arr)
7324  {
7325  free_and_init (seg_idx);
7326  }
7327 
7328  } /* for (consp = constraintp; consp; consp = consp->next) */
7329 
7330  } /* for (i = 0; i < class_infop->n; i++) */
7331  /* class_infop->n >= 1 */
7332 
7333  /* find and mark indexes which are compatible across class hierarchy */
7334 
7335  indexp = class_infop->info[0].index;
7336 
7337  /* allocate room for the compatible heirarchical indexex */
7338  /* We'll go ahead and allocate room for each index in the top level class. This is the worst case situation and it
7339  * simplifies the code a bit.
7340  */
7341  /* Malloc and Init a QO_INDEX struct with n entries. */
7342  node_indexp = QO_NODE_INDEXES (nodep) = (QO_NODE_INDEX *) malloc (SIZEOF_NODE_INDEX (indexp->n));
7343 
7344  if (node_indexp == NULL)
7345  {
7346  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, SIZEOF_NODE_INDEX (indexp->n));
7347  return;
7348  }
7349 
7350  memset (node_indexp, 0, SIZEOF_NODE_INDEX (indexp->n));
7351 
7352  QO_NI_N (node_indexp) = 0;
7353 
7354  /* if we don`t have any indexes to process, we're through if there is only one, then make sure that the head pointer
7355  * points to it if there are more than one, we also need to construct a linked list of compatible indexes by
7356  * recursively searching down the hierarchy
7357  */
7358  for (i = 0; i < indexp->n; i++)
7359  {
7360  index_entryp = QO_INDEX_INDEX (indexp, i);
7361  /* get compatible(equivalent) index of the next class 'index_entryp->next' points to it */
7362  index_entryp->next = is_index_compatible (class_infop, 1, index_entryp);
7363 
7364  if ((index_entryp->next != NULL) || (class_infop->n == 1))
7365  {
7366  /* fill in QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY structure */
7367  ni_entryp = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, QO_NI_N (node_indexp));
7368  /* number of classes on the list */
7369  (ni_entryp)->n = class_infop->n;
7370  /* link QO_INDEX_ENTRY struture to QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY strucure */
7371  (ni_entryp)->head = index_entryp;
7372  QO_NI_N (node_indexp)++;
7373  }
7374  } /* for (i = 0; i < indexp->n; i++) */
7375 
7376 }
7377 
7378 /*
7379  * qo_discover_indexes () -
7380  * return: nothing
7381  * env(in): The environment to be updated
7382  *
7383  * Note: Study each term to finish determination of whether it can use
7384  * an index. qo_analyze_term() already determined whether each
7385  * term qualifies structurally, and qo_get_class_info() has
7386  * determined all of the indexes that are available, so all we
7387  * have to do here is combine those two pieces of information.
7388  */
7389 static void
7390 qo_discover_indexes (QO_ENV * env)
7391 {
7392  int i, j, k, b, n, s;
7393  bool found;
7394  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
7395  QO_NODE_INDEX *node_indexp;
7396  QO_NODE_INDEX_ENTRY *ni_entryp;
7397  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *index_entryp;
7398  QO_TERM *termp;
7399  QO_NODE *nodep;
7400  QO_SEGMENT *segp;
7401 
7402  /* iterate over all nodes and find indexes for each node */
7403  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; i++)
7404  {
7405 
7406  nodep = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
7407  if (nodep->info)
7408  {
7409  /* find indexed segments that belong to this node and get indexes that apply to indexed segments. Note that a
7410  * scan for record information or page informations should follow, there is no need to check for index (a
7411  * sequential scan is needed).
7412  */
7413  if (!PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET (QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (nodep),
7414  (PT_SPEC_FLAG_RECORD_INFO_SCAN | PT_SPEC_FLAG_PAGE_INFO_SCAN)))
7415  {
7416  qo_find_node_indexes (env, nodep);
7417  /* collect statistic information on discovered indexes */
7418  qo_get_index_info (env, nodep);
7419  }
7420  else
7421  {
7422  QO_NODE_INDEXES (nodep) = NULL;
7423  }
7424  }
7425  else
7426  {
7427  /* If the 'info' of node is NULL, then this is probably a derived table. Without the info, we don't have
7428  * class information to work with so we really can't do much so just skip the node.
7429  */
7430  QO_NODE_INDEXES (nodep) = NULL; /* this node will not use a index */
7431  }
7432 
7433  } /* for (n = 0; n < env->nnodes; n++) */
7434 
7435  /* for each terms, look indexed segements and filter out the segments which don't actually contain any indexes */
7436  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
7437  {
7438 
7439  termp = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
7440 
7441  /* before, 'index_seg[]' has all possible indexed segments, that is assigned at 'qo_analyze_term()' */
7442  /* for all 'term.index_seg[]', examine if it really has index or not */
7443  k = 0;
7444  for (j = 0; j < termp->can_use_index; j++)
7445  {
7446 
7447  segp = termp->index_seg[j];
7448 
7449  found = false; /* init */
7450  /* for each nodes, do traverse */
7451  for (b = bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_NODES (termp)), &bi); b != -1 && !found; b = bitset_next_member (&bi))
7452  {
7453 
7454  nodep = QO_ENV_NODE (env, b);
7455 
7456  /* pointer to QO_NODE_INDEX structure of QO_NODE */
7457  node_indexp = QO_NODE_INDEXES (nodep);
7458  if (node_indexp == NULL)
7459  {
7460  /* node has not any index skip and go ahead */
7461  continue;
7462  }
7463 
7464  /* for each index list rooted at the node */
7465  for (n = 0, ni_entryp = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, 0); n < QO_NI_N (node_indexp) && !found;
7466  n++, ni_entryp++)
7467  {
7468 
7469  index_entryp = (ni_entryp)->head;
7470 
7471  /* for each segments constrained by the index */
7472  for (s = 0; s < index_entryp->nsegs && !found; s++)
7473  {
7474  if (QO_SEG_IDX (segp) == (index_entryp->seg_idxs[s]))
7475  {
7476  /* found specified seg stop traverse */
7477  found = true;
7478 
7479  /* record term at segment structure */
7480  bitset_add (&(QO_SEG_INDEX_TERMS (segp)), QO_TERM_IDX (termp));
7481  /* indexed segment in 'index_seg[]' array */
7482  termp->index_seg[k++] = termp->index_seg[j];
7483  }
7484  } /* for (s = 0 ... ) */
7485 
7486  } /* for (n = 0 ... ) */
7487 
7488  } /* for (b = ... ) */
7489 
7490  } /* for (j = 0 ... ) */
7491 
7492  termp->can_use_index = k; /* dimension of 'index_seg[]' */
7493  /* clear unused, discarded 'index_seg[]' entries */
7494  while (k < j)
7495  {
7496  termp->index_seg[k++] = NULL;
7497  }
7498 
7499  } /* for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++) */
7500 
7501 }
7502 
7503 /*
7504  * qo_discover_partitions () -
7505  * return:
7506  * env(in):
7507  */
7508 static void
7509 qo_discover_partitions (QO_ENV * env)
7510 {
7511  int N = env->nnodes; /* The number of nodes in the join graph */
7512  int E = env->nedges; /* The number of edges (in the strict sense) */
7513  int P = 0; /* The number of partitions */
7514  int e, n, p;
7515 
7516  int *buddy; /* buddy[i] is the index of another node in the same partition as i */
7517  int *partition; /* partition[i] is the index of the partition to which node i belongs */
7518  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
7519  int hi, ti, r;
7520  QO_TERM *term;
7521  QO_PARTITION *part;
7522  int M_offset, join_info_size;
7523  int rel_idx;
7524 
7525  buddy = NULL;
7526  if (N > 0)
7527  {
7528  buddy = (int *) malloc (sizeof (int) * (2 * N));
7529  if (buddy == NULL)
7530  {
7531  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (int) * (2 * N));
7532  return;
7533  }
7534  }
7535  else
7536  {
7537  return;
7538  }
7539 
7540  partition = buddy + N;
7541 
7542  /*
7543  * This code assumes that there will be no ALLOCATE failures; if
7544  * there are, the buddy array will be lost.
7545  */
7546 
7547  for (n = 0; n < N; ++n)
7548  {
7549  buddy[n] = -1;
7550  partition[n] = -1;
7551  }
7552 
7553  for (e = 0; e < E; ++e)
7554  {
7555  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, e);
7556 
7557  /*
7558  * Identify one of the nodes in this term, and run to the top of
7559  * the tree in which it resides.
7560  */
7561  hi = bitset_iterate (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)), &bi);
7562  while (hi != -1 && buddy[hi] != -1)
7563  {
7564  hi = buddy[hi];
7565  }
7566 
7567  /*
7568  * Now buddy up all of the other nodes encompassed by this term.
7569  */
7570  while ((ti = bitset_next_member (&bi)) != -1)
7571  {
7572  /*
7573  * Run to the top of the tree in which node[ti] resides.
7574  */
7575  while (buddy[ti] != -1)
7576  {
7577  ti = buddy[ti];
7578  }
7579  /*
7580  * Join the two trees together.
7581  */
7582  if (hi != ti)
7583  {
7584  buddy[hi] = ti;
7585  }
7586  }
7587  }
7588 
7589  /*
7590  * Now assign the actual partitions.
7591  */
7592  for (n = 0; n < N; ++n)
7593  {
7594  if (partition[n] == -1)
7595  {
7596  r = n;
7597  /*
7598  * Find the root of the tree to which node[n] belongs.
7599  */
7600  while (buddy[r] != -1)
7601  {
7602  r = buddy[r];
7603  }
7604  /*
7605  * If a partition hasn't already been assigned for this tree,
7606  * assign one now.
7607  */
7608  if (partition[r] == -1)
7609  {
7610  QO_PARTITION *part = QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, P);
7611  QO_NODE *node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, r);
7612  qo_partition_init (env, part, P);
7613  bitset_add (&(QO_PARTITION_NODES (part)), r);
7614  bitset_union (&(QO_PARTITION_DEPENDENCIES (part)), &(QO_NODE_DEP_SET (node)));
7615  QO_NODE_PARTITION (node) = part;
7616  partition[r] = P;
7617  P++;
7618  }
7619  /*
7620  * Now add node[n] to that partition.
7621  */
7622  if (n != r)
7623  {
7624  QO_PARTITION *part = QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, partition[r]);
7625  QO_NODE *node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n);
7626  partition[n] = partition[r];
7627  bitset_add (&(QO_PARTITION_NODES (part)), n);
7628  bitset_union (&(QO_PARTITION_DEPENDENCIES (part)), &(QO_NODE_DEP_SET (node)));
7629  QO_NODE_PARTITION (node) = part;
7630  }
7631  }
7632  }
7633 
7634  /*
7635  * Now go build the edge sets that correspond to each partition,
7636  * i.e., the set of edges that connect the nodes in each partition.
7637  */
7638  M_offset = 0; /* init */
7639  for (p = 0; p < P; ++p)
7640  {
7641  part = QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, p);
7642 
7643  for (e = 0; e < E; ++e)
7644  {
7645  QO_TERM *edge = QO_ENV_TERM (env, e);
7646 
7647  if (bitset_subset (&(QO_PARTITION_NODES (part)), &(QO_TERM_NODES (edge)))
7648  && !bitset_is_empty (&(QO_TERM_NODES (edge))))
7649  {
7650  bitset_add (&(QO_PARTITION_EDGES (part)), e);
7651  }
7652  }
7653  /* alloc size check 2: for signed max int. 2**30 is positive, 2**31 is negative LOG2_SIZEOF_POINTER:
7654  * log2(sizeof(QO_INFO *))
7655  */
7656  if (bitset_cardinality (&(QO_PARTITION_NODES (part))) > _WORDSIZE - 2 - LOG2_SIZEOF_POINTER)
7657  {
7658  if (buddy)
7659  {
7660  free_and_init (buddy);
7661  }
7662  QO_ABORT (env);
7663  }
7664 
7665  /* set the starting point the join_info vector that correspond to each partition. */
7666  if (p > 0)
7667  {
7668  QO_PARTITION_M_OFFSET (part) = M_offset;
7669  }
7670  join_info_size = QO_JOIN_INFO_SIZE (part);
7671  if (INT_MAX - M_offset * sizeof (QO_INFO *) < join_info_size * sizeof (QO_INFO *))
7672  {
7673  if (buddy)
7674  {
7675  free_and_init (buddy);
7676  }
7677  QO_ABORT (env);
7678  }
7679  M_offset += join_info_size;
7680 
7681  /* set the relative id of nodes in the partition */
7682  rel_idx = 0; /* init */
7683  for (hi = bitset_iterate (&(QO_PARTITION_NODES (part)), &bi); hi != -1; hi = bitset_next_member (&bi))
7684  {
7685  QO_NODE_REL_IDX (QO_ENV_NODE (env, hi)) = rel_idx;
7686  rel_idx++;
7687  }
7688  }
7689 
7690  env->npartitions = P;
7691 
7692  if (buddy)
7693  {
7694  free_and_init (buddy);
7695  }
7696 }
7697 
7698 /*
7699  * qo_assign_eq_classes () -
7700  * return:
7701  * env(in):
7702  */
7703 static void
7704 qo_assign_eq_classes (QO_ENV * env)
7705 {
7706  int i;
7707  QO_EQCLASS **eq_map;
7708  BITSET segs;
7709 
7710  bitset_init (&segs, env);
7711 
7712  eq_map = NULL;
7713  if (env->nsegs > 0)
7714  {
7715  eq_map = (QO_EQCLASS **) malloc (sizeof (QO_EQCLASS *) * env->nsegs);
7716  if (eq_map == NULL)
7717  {
7718  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (QO_EQCLASS *) * env->nsegs);
7719  return;
7720  }
7721  }
7722 
7723  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; ++i)
7724  {
7725  eq_map[i] = NULL;
7726  }
7727 
7728  for (i = 0; i < env->nedges; i++)
7729  {
7730  QO_TERM *term;
7731 
7732  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
7733  if (QO_TERM_NOMINAL_SEG (term))
7734  {
7735  bitset_union (&segs, &(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)));
7736  }
7737  }
7738 
7739  /*
7740  * Now examine each segment and see if it should be assigned to an
7741  * equivalence class.
7742  */
7743  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; ++i)
7744  {
7745  if (!BITSET_MEMBER (segs, i))
7746  {
7747  continue;
7748  }
7749 
7750  if (eq_map[i] == NULL)
7751  {
7752  QO_SEGMENT *root, *seg;
7753  seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, i);
7754 
7755  /*
7756  * Find the root of the tree in which this segment resides.
7757  */
7758  for (root = seg; QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (root); root = QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (root))
7759  {
7760  ;
7761  }
7762  /*
7763  * Assign a new EqClass to that root if one hasn't already
7764  * been assigned.
7765  */
7766  if (eq_map[QO_SEG_IDX (root)] == NULL)
7767  {
7768  qo_eqclass_add ((eq_map[QO_SEG_IDX (root)] = qo_eqclass_new (env)), root);
7769  }
7770  /*
7771  * Now add the original segment to the same equivalence
7772  * class.
7773  */
7774  if (root != seg)
7775  {
7776  qo_eqclass_add (eq_map[QO_SEG_IDX (root)], seg);
7777  }
7778  eq_map[i] = eq_map[QO_SEG_IDX (root)];
7779  }
7780  }
7781 
7782  bitset_delset (&segs);
7783  if (eq_map)
7784  {
7785  free_and_init (eq_map);
7786  }
7787 
7788  /*
7789  * Now squirrel away the eqclass info for each term so that we don't
7790  * have to keep recomputing it when searching the plan space. Note
7791  * that this not really meaningful unless all of the segments in the
7792  * term are in the same equivalence class as the first one. However,
7793  * since we're only supposed to use this information when examining
7794  * join or path terms, and since that condition holds for those
7795  * terms, this should be ok.
7796  */
7797  for (i = 0; i < env->nedges; i++)
7798  {
7799  QO_TERM *term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
7800  QO_SEGMENT *seg = QO_TERM_NOMINAL_SEG (term);
7801 
7802  if (seg)
7803  {
7804  QO_TERM_EQCLASS (term) = QO_SEG_EQCLASS (seg);
7805  }
7806  else if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE))
7807  {
7808  QO_TERM_EQCLASS (term) = qo_eqclass_new (env);
7809  QO_EQCLASS_TERM (QO_TERM_EQCLASS (term)) = term;
7810  }
7811  else
7812  {
7813  QO_TERM_EQCLASS (term) = QO_UNORDERED;
7814  }
7815  }
7816 }
7817 
7818 /*
7819  * qo_env_dump () -
7820  * return:
7821  * env(in):
7822  * f(in):
7823  */
7824 static void
7825 qo_env_dump (QO_ENV * env, FILE * f)
7826 {
7827  int i;
7828 
7829  if (env->pt_tree->node_type == PT_SELECT && env->pt_tree->info.query.is_subquery == PT_IS_CTE_NON_REC_SUBQUERY)
7830  {
7831  fprintf (f, "Non recursive part of CTE:\n");
7832  }
7833  else if (env->pt_tree->node_type == PT_SELECT && env->pt_tree->info.query.is_subquery == PT_IS_CTE_REC_SUBQUERY)
7834  {
7835  fprintf (f, "Recursive part of CTE:\n");
7836  }
7837 
7838  if (f == NULL)
7839  {
7840  f = stdout;
7841  }
7842 
7843  if (env->nsegs)
7844  {
7845  fprintf (f, "Join graph segments (f indicates final):\n");
7846  for (i = 0; i < env->nsegs; ++i)
7847  {
7848  QO_SEGMENT *seg = QO_ENV_SEG (env, i);
7849  int extra_info = 0;
7850 
7851  fprintf (f, "seg[%d]: ", i);
7852  qo_seg_fprint (seg, f);
7853 
7854  PUT_FLAG (BITSET_MEMBER (env->final_segs, i), "f");
7855  /*
7856  * Put extra flags here.
7857  */
7858  fputs (extra_info ? ")\n" : "\n", f);
7859  }
7860  }
7861 
7862  if (env->nnodes)
7863  {
7864  fprintf (f, "Join graph nodes:\n");
7865  for (i = 0; i < env->nnodes; ++i)
7866  {
7867  QO_NODE *node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
7868  fprintf (f, "node[%d]: ", i);
7869  qo_node_dump (node, f);
7870  fputs ("\n", f);
7871  }
7872  }
7873 
7874  if (env->neqclasses)
7875  {
7876  fprintf (f, "Join graph equivalence classes:\n");
7877  for (i = 0; i < env->neqclasses; ++i)
7878  {
7879  fprintf (f, "eqclass[%d]: ", i);
7880  qo_eqclass_dump (QO_ENV_EQCLASS (env, i), f);
7881  fputs ("\n", f);
7882  }
7883  }
7884 
7885  /*
7886  * Notice that we blow off printing the edge structures themselves,
7887  * and just print the term that gives rise to the edge. Also notice
7888  * the way edges and terms are separated: we don't reset the counter
7889  * for non-edge terms.
7890  */
7891  if (env->nedges)
7892  {
7893  fputs ("Join graph edges:\n", f);
7894  for (i = 0; i < env->nedges; ++i)
7895  {
7896  fprintf (f, "term[%d]: ", i);
7897  qo_term_dump (QO_ENV_TERM (env, i), f);
7898  fputs ("\n", f);
7899  }
7900  }
7901 
7902  if (env->nterms - env->nedges)
7903  {
7904  fputs ("Join graph terms:\n", f);
7905  for (i = env->nedges; i < env->nterms; ++i)
7906  {
7907  fprintf (f, "term[%d]: ", i);
7908  qo_term_dump (QO_ENV_TERM (env, i), f);
7909  fputs ("\n", f);
7910  }
7911  }
7912 
7913  if (env->nsubqueries)
7914  {
7915  fputs ("Join graph subqueries:\n", f);
7916  for (i = 0; i < env->nsubqueries; ++i)
7917  {
7918  fprintf (f, "subquery[%d]: ", i);
7919  qo_subquery_dump (env, &env->subqueries[i], f);
7920  fputs ("\n", f);
7921  }
7922  }
7923 
7924  if (env->npartitions > 1)
7925  {
7926  fputs ("Join graph partitions:\n", f);
7927  for (i = 0; i < env->npartitions; ++i)
7928  {
7929  fprintf (f, "partition[%d]: ", i);
7930  qo_partition_dump (QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, i), f);
7931  fputs ("\n", f);
7932  }
7933  }
7934 
7935  fflush (f);
7936 }

7997 /*
7998  * qo_node_add_sarg () -
7999  * return:
8000  * node(in):
8001  * sarg(in):
8002  */
8003 static void
8004 qo_node_add_sarg (QO_NODE * node, QO_TERM * sarg)
8005 {
8006  double sel_limit;
8007 
8008  bitset_add (&(QO_NODE_SARGS (node)), QO_TERM_IDX (sarg));
8009  QO_NODE_SELECTIVITY (node) *= QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (sarg);
8010  sel_limit = (QO_NODE_NCARD (node) == 0) ? 0 : (1.0 / (double) QO_NODE_NCARD (node));
8011  if (QO_NODE_SELECTIVITY (node) < sel_limit)
8012  {
8013  QO_NODE_SELECTIVITY (node) = sel_limit;
8014  }
8015 }

8017 /*
8018  * qo_node_fprint () -
8019  * return:
8020  * node(in):
8021  * f(in):
8022  */
8023 void
8024 qo_node_fprint (QO_NODE * node, FILE * f)
8025 {
8026  if (QO_NODE_NAME (node))
8027  {
8028  fprintf (f, "%s", QO_NODE_NAME (node));
8029  }
8030  fprintf (f, " node[%d]", QO_NODE_IDX (node));
8031 }
8032 
8033 /*
8034  * qo_node_dump () -
8035  * return:
8036  * node(in):
8037  * f(in):
8038  */
8039 static void
8040 qo_node_dump (QO_NODE * node, FILE * f)
8041 {
8042  int i, n = 1;
8043  const char *name;
8044  PT_NODE *entity;
8045 
8046  entity = QO_NODE_ENTITY_SPEC (node);
8047 
8048  if (QO_NODE_INFO (node))
8049  {
8050  n = QO_NODE_INFO_N (node);
8051  if (n > 1)
8052  {
8053  fprintf (f, "("); /* left paren */
8054  }
8055  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
8056  {
8057  name = QO_NODE_INFO (node)->info[i].name;
8058  /* check for class OID reference spec for example: 'class x' SELECT class_meth(class x, x.i) FROM x, class x */
8059  if (i == 0)
8060  { /* the first entity */
8061  fprintf (f, (entity->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS ? "class %s" : "%s"),
8062  (name ? name : "(anon)"));
8063  }
8064  else
8065  {
8066  fprintf (f, (entity->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS ? ", class %s" : ", %s"),
8067  (name ? name : "(anon)"));
8068  }
8069  }
8070  fprintf (f, "%s ", (n > 1 ? ")" : "")); /* right paren */
8071  }
8072  name = QO_NODE_NAME (node);
8073  if (n == 1)
8074  {
8075  fprintf (f, "%s", (name ? name : "(unknown)"));
8076  }
8077  else
8078  {
8079  fprintf (f, "as %s", (name ? name : "(unknown)"));
8080  }
8081 
8082  if (entity->info.spec.range_var->alias_print)
8083  {
8084  fprintf (f, "(%s)", entity->info.spec.range_var->alias_print);
8085  }
8086 
8087  fprintf (f, "(%lu/%lu)", QO_NODE_NCARD (node), QO_NODE_TCARD (node));
8088  if (!bitset_is_empty (&(QO_NODE_SARGS (node))))
8089  {
8090  fputs (" (sargs ", f);
8091  bitset_print (&(QO_NODE_SARGS (node)), f);
8092  fputs (")", f);
8093  }
8094  if (!bitset_is_empty (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node))))
8095  {
8096  fputs (" (outer-dep-set ", f);
8097  bitset_print (&(QO_NODE_OUTER_DEP_SET (node)), f);
8098  fputs (")", f);
8099  }
8100 
8101  fprintf (f, " (loc %d)", entity->info.spec.location);
8102 }

8152 /*
8153  * qo_seg_width () -
8154  * return: size_t
8155  * seg(in): A pointer to a QO_SEGMENT
8156  *
8157  * Note: Return the estimated width (in size_t units) of the indicated
8158  * attribute. This estimate will be required to estimate the
8159  * size of intermediate results should they need to be
8160  * materialized for e.g. sorting.
8161  */
8162 int
8163 qo_seg_width (QO_SEGMENT * seg)
8164 {
8165  /*
8166  * This needs to consult the schema manager (or somebody) to
8167  * determine the type of the underlying attribute. For set-valued
8168  * attributes, this is truly an estimate, since the size of the
8169  * attribute in any result tuple will be the product of the
8170  * cardinality of that particular set and the size of the underlying
8171  * element type.
8172  */
8173  int size;
8174  DB_DOMAIN *domain;
8175 
8176  domain = pt_node_to_db_domain (QO_ENV_PARSER (QO_SEG_ENV (seg)), QO_SEG_PT_NODE (seg), NULL);
8177  if (domain)
8178  {
8179  domain = tp_domain_cache (domain);
8180  }
8181  else
8182  {
8183  /* guessing */
8184  return sizeof (int);
8185  }
8186 
8187  size = tp_domain_disk_size (domain);
8188  switch (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain))
8189  {
8190  case DB_TYPE_VARBIT:
8191  case DB_TYPE_VARCHAR:
8192  case DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
8193  /* do guessing for variable character type */
8194  size = size * (2 / 3);
8195  break;
8196  default:
8197  break;
8198  }
8199 
8200  return MAX ((int) sizeof (int), size);
8201  /* for backward compatibility, at least sizeof(long) */
8202 }
8203 
8204 /*
8205  * qo_seg_fprint () -
8206  * return:
8207  * seg(in):
8208  * f(in):
8209  */
8210 void
8211 qo_seg_fprint (QO_SEGMENT * seg, FILE * f)
8212 {
8213  fprintf (f, "%s[%d]", QO_SEG_NAME (seg), QO_NODE_IDX (QO_SEG_HEAD (seg)));
8214 }

8330 
8331 /*
8332  * qo_discover_sort_limit_nodes () - discover the subset of nodes on which
8333  * a SORT_LIMIT plan can be applied.
8334  * return : void
8335  * env (in) : env
8336  *
8337  * Note: This function discovers a subset of nodes on which a SORT_LIMIT plan
8338  * can be applied without altering the result of the query.
8339  */
8340 static void
8341 qo_discover_sort_limit_nodes (QO_ENV * env)
8342 {
8343  PT_NODE *query, *orderby, *sort_col, *select_list, *col, *save_next;
8344  int i, pos_spec, limit_max_count;
8345  QO_NODE *node;
8346  BITSET order_nodes, dep_nodes, expr_segs, tmp_bitset;
8347  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
8348 
8349  bitset_init (&order_nodes, env);
8350  bitset_init (&QO_ENV_SORT_LIMIT_NODES (env), env);
8351 
8352  query = QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env);
8353  if (!PT_IS_SELECT (query))
8354  {
8355  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8356  }
8357  if (query->info.query.all_distinct != PT_ALL || query->info.query.q.select.group_by != NULL
8358  || query->info.query.q.select.connect_by != NULL)
8359  {
8360  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8361  }
8362  if (query->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_NO_SORT_LIMIT)
8363  {
8364  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8365  }
8366 
8367  if (pt_get_query_limit_value (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), QO_ENV_PT_TREE (env), &QO_ENV_LIMIT_VALUE (env)) != NO_ERROR)
8368  {
8369  /* unusable limit */
8370  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8371  }
8372 
8373  if (env->npartitions > 1)
8374  {
8375  /* not applicable when dealing with more than one partition */
8376  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8377  }
8378 
8379  if (bitset_cardinality (&QO_PARTITION_NODES (QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, 0))) <= 1)
8380  {
8381  /* No need to apply this optimization on a single node */
8382  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8383  }
8384 
8385  orderby = query->info.query.order_by;
8386  if (orderby == NULL)
8387  {
8388  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8389  }
8390 
8391  env->use_sort_limit = QO_SL_INVALID;
8392 
8393  /* Verify that we don't have terms qualified as after join. These terms will be evaluated after the SORT-LIMIT plan
8394  * and might invalidate tuples the plan returned.
8395  */
8396  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
8397  {
8398  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (&env->terms[i]) == QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN || QO_TERM_CLASS (&env->terms[i]) == QO_TC_OTHER)
8399  {
8400  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8401  }
8402  }
8403 
8404  /* Start by assuming that evaluation of the limit clause depends on all nodes in the query. Since we only have one
8405  * partition, we can get the bitset of nodes from there.
8406  */
8407  bitset_union (&env->sort_limit_nodes, &QO_PARTITION_NODES (QO_ENV_PARTITION (env, 0)));
8408 
8409  select_list = pt_get_select_list (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), query);
8410  assert_release (select_list != NULL);
8411 
8412  /* Only consider ORDER BY expression which is evaluable during a scan. This means any expression except analytic and
8413  * aggregate functions.
8414  */
8415  for (sort_col = orderby; sort_col != NULL; sort_col = sort_col->next)
8416  {
8417  if (sort_col->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC)
8418  {
8419  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8420  }
8421 
8422  bitset_init (&expr_segs, env);
8423  bitset_init (&tmp_bitset, env);
8424 
8425  pos_spec = sort_col->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.pos_no;
8426 
8427  /* sort_col is a position specifier in select list. Have to walk the select list to find the actual node */
8428  for (i = 1, col = select_list; col != NULL && i != pos_spec; col = col->next, i++);
8429 
8430  if (col == NULL)
8431  {
8432  assert_release (col != NULL);
8433  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8434  }
8435 
8436  save_next = col->next;
8437  col->next = NULL;
8438  if (pt_has_analytic (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), col) || pt_has_aggregate (QO_ENV_PARSER (env), col))
8439  {
8440  /* abandon search because these expressions cannot be evaluated during SORT_LIMIT evaluation */
8441  col->next = save_next;
8442  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8443  }
8444 
8445  /* get segments from col */
8446  qo_expr_segs (env, col, &expr_segs);
8447  /* get nodes for segments */
8448  qo_seg_nodes (env, &expr_segs, &tmp_bitset);
8449 
8450  /* accumulate nodes to order_nodes */
8451  bitset_union (&order_nodes, &tmp_bitset);
8452 
8453  bitset_delset (&expr_segs);
8454  bitset_delset (&tmp_bitset);
8455 
8456  col->next = save_next;
8457  }
8458 
8459  for (i = bitset_iterate (&order_nodes, &bi); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&bi))
8460  {
8461  bitset_init (&dep_nodes, env);
8462  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, i);
8463 
8464  /* For each orderby node, gather nodes which are SORT_LIMIT independent on this node and remove them from
8465  * sort_limit_nodes.
8466  */
8467  qo_discover_sort_limit_join_nodes (env, node, &order_nodes, &dep_nodes);
8468  bitset_difference (&env->sort_limit_nodes, &dep_nodes);
8469 
8470  bitset_delset (&dep_nodes);
8471  }
8472 
8473  if (bitset_cardinality (&env->sort_limit_nodes) == env->Nnodes)
8474  {
8475  /* There is no subset of nodes on which we can apply SORT_LIMIT so abandon this optimization */
8476  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8477  }
8478 
8479  bitset_delset (&order_nodes);
8480 
8481  /* In order to create a SORT-LIMIT plan, the query must have a valid limit. All other conditions for creating the
8482  * plan have been met.
8483  */
8484  if (DB_IS_NULL (&QO_ENV_LIMIT_VALUE (env)))
8485  {
8486  /* Cannot make a decision at this point. Go ahead with query compilation as if this optimization does not apply.
8487  * The query will be recompiled once a valid limit is supplied. */
8488  goto sort_limit_possible;
8489  }
8490 
8491  limit_max_count = prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_SORT_LIMIT_MAX_COUNT);
8492  if (limit_max_count == 0)
8493  {
8494  /* SORT-LIMIT plans are disabled */
8495  goto abandon_stop_limit;
8496  }
8497 
8498  if ((DB_BIGINT) limit_max_count < db_get_bigint (&QO_ENV_LIMIT_VALUE (env)))
8499  {
8500  /* Limit too large to apply this optimization. Mark it as candidate but do not generate SORT-LIMIT plans at this
8501  * time.
8502  */
8503  goto sort_limit_possible;
8504  }
8505 
8506  if (bitset_cardinality (&env->sort_limit_nodes) == 1)
8507  {
8508  /* Mark this node as a sort stop candidate. We will generate a SORT-LIMIT plan over this node. */
8509  int n = bitset_first_member (&order_nodes);
8510  node = QO_ENV_NODE (env, n);
8511  QO_NODE_SORT_LIMIT_CANDIDATE (node) = true;
8512  }
8513 
8514  env->use_sort_limit = QO_SL_USE;
8515  return;
8516 
8517 sort_limit_possible:
8518  env->use_sort_limit = QO_SL_POSSIBLE;
8519  bitset_delset (&QO_ENV_SORT_LIMIT_NODES (env));
8520  return;
8521 
8522 abandon_stop_limit:
8523  bitset_delset (&order_nodes);
8524  bitset_delset (&QO_ENV_SORT_LIMIT_NODES (env));
8525  env->use_sort_limit = QO_SL_INVALID;
8526 }
8527 
8528 /*
8529  * qo_equivalence () -
8530  * return:
8531  * sega(in):
8532  * segb(in):
8533  */
8534 static void
8535 qo_equivalence (QO_SEGMENT * sega, QO_SEGMENT * segb)
8536 {
8537 
8538  while (QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (sega))
8539  {
8540  sega = QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (sega);
8541  }
8542  while (QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (segb))
8543  {
8544  segb = QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (segb);
8545  }
8546 
8547  if (sega != segb)
8548  {
8549  QO_SEG_EQ_ROOT (sega) = segb;
8550  }
8551 }
8552 
8553 /*
8554  * qo_eqclass_wrt () -
8555  * return:
8556  * eqclass(in):
8557  * nodeset(in):
8558  */
8559 static QO_SEGMENT *
8560 qo_eqclass_wrt (QO_EQCLASS * eqclass, BITSET * nodeset)
8561 {
8562  int member;
8563  BITSET_ITERATOR si;
8564  QO_SEGMENT *result = NULL;
8565 
8566  for (member = bitset_iterate (&(QO_EQCLASS_SEGS (eqclass)), &si); member != -1; member = bitset_next_member (&si))
8567  {
8568  QO_SEGMENT *seg = QO_ENV_SEG (QO_EQCLASS_ENV (eqclass), member);
8569  if (BITSET_MEMBER (*nodeset, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_SEG_HEAD (seg))))
8570  {
8571  result = seg;
8572  break;
8573  }
8574  }
8575 
8576  QO_ASSERT (eqclass->env, result != NULL);
8577  return result;
8578 }
8579 
8580 /*
8581  * qo_eqclass_fprint_wrt () -
8582  * return:
8583  * eqclass(in):
8584  * nodeset(in):
8585  * f(in):
8586  */
8587 void
8588 qo_eqclass_fprint_wrt (QO_EQCLASS * eqclass, BITSET * nodeset, FILE * f)
8589 {
8590  if (eqclass == QO_UNORDERED)
8591  {
8592  fputs ("UNORDERED", f);
8593  }
8594  else if (bitset_is_empty (&(QO_EQCLASS_SEGS (eqclass))))
8595  {
8596  /*
8597  * This is a phony eqclass created for a complex merge join.
8598  * Just fabricate some text that will let us know where it came
8599  * from...
8600  */
8601  fprintf (f, "phony (term[%d])", QO_TERM_IDX (QO_EQCLASS_TERM (eqclass)));
8602  }
8603  else
8604  {
8605  qo_seg_fprint (qo_eqclass_wrt (eqclass, nodeset), f);
8606  }
8607 }
