8609 /*
8610  * qo_term_free () -
8611  * return:
8612  * term(in):
8613  */
8614 static void
8615 qo_term_free (QO_TERM * term)
8616 {
8617  /*
8618  * Free the expr alloced by this term
8619  */
8620  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_COPY_PT_EXPR))
8621  {
8622  parser_free_tree (QO_ENV_PARSER (QO_TERM_ENV (term)), QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term));
8623  }
8624  bitset_delset (&(QO_TERM_NODES (term)));
8625  bitset_delset (&(QO_TERM_SEGS (term)));
8626  bitset_delset (&(QO_TERM_SUBQUERIES (term)));
8627 }
8628 
8629 /*
8630  * qo_term_fprint () -
8631  * return:
8632  * term(in):
8633  * f(in):
8634  */
8635 void
8636 qo_term_fprint (QO_TERM * term, FILE * f)
8637 {
8638  QO_TERMCLASS tc;
8639 
8640  if (term)
8641  {
8642  switch (tc = QO_TERM_CLASS (term))
8643  {
8644  case QO_TC_PATH:
8645  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_HEAD (term), f);
8646  if (!QO_TERM_SEG (term) || !QO_SEG_NAME (QO_TERM_SEG (term)))
8647  {
8648  fprintf (f, " () -> ");
8649  }
8650  else
8651  {
8652  fprintf (f, " %s -> ", QO_SEG_NAME (QO_TERM_SEG (term)));
8653  }
8654  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8655  break;
8656 
8657  case QO_TC_DEP_LINK:
8658  fprintf (f, "table(");
8659  bitset_print (&(QO_NODE_DEP_SET (QO_TERM_TAIL (term))), f);
8660  fprintf (f, ") -> ");
8661  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8662  break;
8663 
8664  case QO_TC_DEP_JOIN:
8665  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_HEAD (term), f);
8666  fprintf (f, " <dj> ");
8667  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8668  break;
8669 
8670  default:
8671  fprintf (f, "term[%d]", QO_TERM_IDX (term));
8672  break;
8673  }
8674  }
8675  else
8676  {
8677  fprintf (f, "none");
8678  }
8679 }
8680 
8681 /*
8682  * qo_termset_fprint () -
8683  * return:
8684  * env(in):
8685  * terms(in):
8686  * f(in):
8687  */
8688 void
8689 qo_termset_fprint (QO_ENV * env, BITSET * terms, FILE * f)
8690 {
8691  int tx;
8692  BITSET_ITERATOR si;
8693  const char *prefix = "";
8694 
8695  for (tx = bitset_iterate (terms, &si); tx != -1; tx = bitset_next_member (&si))
8696  {
8697  fputs (prefix, f);
8698  qo_term_fprint (QO_ENV_TERM (env, tx), f);
8699  prefix = " AND ";
8700  }
8701 }
8702 
8703 /*
8704  * qo_term_dump () -
8705  * return:
8706  * term(in):
8707  * f(in):
8708  */
8709 static void
8710 qo_term_dump (QO_TERM * term, FILE * f)
8711 {
8712  PT_NODE *conj, *saved_next = NULL;
8713  QO_TERMCLASS tc;
8714 
8715  conj = QO_TERM_PT_EXPR (term);
8716  if (conj)
8717  {
8718  saved_next = conj->next;
8719  conj->next = NULL;
8720  }
8721 
8722  tc = QO_TERM_CLASS (term);
8723  switch (tc)
8724  {
8725  case QO_TC_PATH:
8726  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_HEAD (term), f);
8727  if (!QO_TERM_SEG (term) || !QO_SEG_NAME (QO_TERM_SEG (term)))
8728  {
8729  fprintf (f, " () -> ");
8730  }
8731  else
8732  {
8733  fprintf (f, " %s -> ", QO_SEG_NAME (QO_TERM_SEG (term)));
8734  }
8735  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8736  break;
8737 
8738  case QO_TC_DEP_LINK:
8739  fprintf (f, "table(");
8740  bitset_print (&(QO_NODE_DEP_SET (QO_TERM_TAIL (term))), f);
8741  fprintf (f, ") -> ");
8742  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8743  break;
8744 
8745  case QO_TC_DEP_JOIN:
8746  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_HEAD (term), f);
8747  fprintf (f, " <dj> ");
8748  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8749  break;
8750 
8751  case QO_TC_DUMMY_JOIN:
8752  if (conj)
8753  { /* may be transitive dummy join term */
8754  fprintf (f, "%s", parser_print_tree (QO_ENV_PARSER (QO_TERM_ENV (term)), conj));
8755  }
8756  else
8757  {
8758  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_HEAD (term), f);
8759  fprintf (f, ", ");
8760  qo_node_fprint (QO_TERM_TAIL (term), f);
8761  }
8762  break;
8763 
8764  default:
8765  assert_release (conj != NULL);
8766  if (conj)
8767  {
8768  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser = QO_ENV_PARSER (QO_TERM_ENV (term));
8769  PT_PRINT_VALUE_FUNC saved_func = parser->print_db_value;
8770 
8771  /* in order to print auto parameterized values */
8772  parser->print_db_value = pt_print_node_value;
8773  fprintf (f, "%s", parser_print_tree (parser, conj));
8774  parser->print_db_value = saved_func;
8775  }
8776  break;
8777  }
8778  fprintf (f, " (sel %g)", QO_TERM_SELECTIVITY (term));
8779 
8780  if (QO_TERM_RANK (term) > 1)
8781  {
8782  fprintf (f, " (rank %d)", QO_TERM_RANK (term));
8783  }
8784 
8785  switch (QO_TERM_CLASS (term))
8786  {
8787  case QO_TC_PATH:
8788  fprintf (f, " (path term)");
8789  break;
8790  case QO_TC_JOIN:
8791  fprintf (f, " (join term)");
8792  break;
8793  case QO_TC_SARG:
8794  fprintf (f, " (sarg term)");
8795  break;
8796  case QO_TC_OTHER:
8797  {
8798  if (conj && conj->node_type == PT_VALUE && conj->info.value.location == 0)
8799  {
8800  /* is an always-false or always-true WHERE condition */
8801  fprintf (f, " (dummy sarg term)");
8802  }
8803  else
8804  {
8805  fprintf (f, " (other term)");
8806  }
8807  }
8808  break;
8809  case QO_TC_DEP_LINK:
8810  fprintf (f, " (dep term)");
8811  break;
8812  case QO_TC_DEP_JOIN:
8813  fprintf (f, " (dep-join term)");
8814  break;
8815  case QO_TC_DURING_JOIN:
8816  fprintf (f, " (during join term)");
8817  break;
8818  case QO_TC_AFTER_JOIN:
8819  fprintf (f, " (after join term)");
8820  break;
8821  case QO_TC_TOTALLY_AFTER_JOIN:
8822  fprintf (f, " (instnum term)");
8823  break;
8824  case QO_TC_DUMMY_JOIN:
8825  fprintf (f, " (dummy join term)");
8826  break;
8827  default:
8828  break;
8829  }
8830 
8831  if (QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_MERGEABLE_EDGE))
8832  {
8833  fputs (" (mergeable)", f);
8834  }
8835 
8836  switch (QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term))
8837  {
8838  case NO_JOIN:
8839  fputs (" (not-join eligible)", f);
8840  break;
8841 
8842  case JOIN_INNER:
8843  fputs (" (inner-join)", f);
8844  break;
8845 
8846  case JOIN_LEFT:
8847  fputs (" (left-join)", f);
8848  break;
8849 
8850  case JOIN_RIGHT:
8851  fputs (" (right-join)", f);
8852  break;
8853 
8854  case JOIN_OUTER: /* not used */
8855  fputs (" (outer-join)", f);
8856  break;
8857 
8858  default:
8859  break;
8860  }
8861 
8862  if (QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term))
8863  {
8864  int i;
8865  fputs (" (indexable", f);
8866  for (i = 0; i < QO_TERM_CAN_USE_INDEX (term); i++)
8867  {
8868  fputs (" ", f);
8869  qo_seg_fprint (QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, i), f);
8870  }
8871  fputs (")", f);
8872  }
8873 
8874  fprintf (f, " (loc %d)", QO_TERM_LOCATION (term));
8875 
8876  /* restore link */
8877  if (conj)
8878  {
8879  conj->next = saved_next;
8880  }
8881 }
8882 
8883 /*
8884  * qo_subquery_dump () -
8885  * return:
8886  * env(in):
8887  * subq(in):
8888  * f(in):
8889  */
8890 static void
8891 qo_subquery_dump (QO_ENV * env, QO_SUBQUERY * subq, FILE * f)
8892 {
8893  int i;
8894  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
8895  const char *separator;
8896 
8897  fprintf (f, "%p", (void *) subq->node);
8898 
8899  separator = NULL;
8900  fputs (" {", f);
8901  for (i = bitset_iterate (&(subq->segs), &bi); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&bi))
8902  {
8903  if (separator)
8904  {
8905  fputs (separator, f);
8906  }
8907  qo_seg_fprint (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i), f);
8908  separator = " ";
8909  }
8910  fputs ("}", f);
8911 
8912  separator = "";
8913  fputs (" {", f);
8914  for (i = bitset_iterate (&(subq->nodes), &bi); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&bi))
8915  {
8916  fprintf (f, "%snode[%d]", separator, i);
8917  separator = " ";
8918  }
8919  fputs ("}", f);
8920 
8921  fputs (" (from term(s)", f);
8922  for (i = bitset_iterate (&(subq->terms), &bi); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&bi))
8923  {
8924  fprintf (f, " %d", i);
8925  }
8926  fputs (")", f);
8927 }
8928

8940 }

9020 /*
9021  * qo_seg_nodes () - Return a bitset of node ids produced from the heads
9022  * of all of the segments in segset
9023  * return:
9024  * env(in): The environment in which these segment and node ids make sense
9025  * segset(in): A bitset of segment ids
9026  * result(out): A bitset of node ids (OUTPUT PARAMETER)
9027  */
9028 static void
9029 qo_seg_nodes (QO_ENV * env, BITSET * segset, BITSET * result)
9030 {
9031  BITSET_ITERATOR si;
9032  int i;
9033 
9034  BITSET_CLEAR (*result);
9035  for (i = bitset_iterate (segset, &si); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&si))
9036  {
9037  bitset_add (result, QO_NODE_IDX (QO_SEG_HEAD (QO_ENV_SEG (env, i))));
9038  }
9039 }
9040 
9041 /*
9042  * qo_is_prefix_index () - Find out if this is a prefix index
9043  * return:
9044  * ent(in): index entry
9045  */
9046 bool
9047 qo_is_prefix_index (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * ent)
9048 {
9049  if (ent && ent->class_ && ent->class_->smclass)
9050  {
9051  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons;
9052 
9053  cons = classobj_find_class_index (ent->class_->smclass, ent->constraints->name);
9054  if (cons)
9055  {
9056  if (cons->attrs_prefix_length && cons->attrs_prefix_length[0] != -1)
9057  {
9058  return true;
9059  }
9060  }
9061  }
9062 
9063  return false;
9064 }
9065 
9066 /*
9067  * qo_is_filter_index () - Find out if this is a filter index
9068  * return: true/false
9069  * ent(in): index entry
9070  */
9071 bool
9072 qo_is_filter_index (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * ent)
9073 {
9074  if (ent && ent->constraints)
9075  {
9076  if (ent->constraints->filter_predicate && ent->force > 0)
9077  {
9078  return true;
9079  }
9080  }
9081 
9082  return false;
9083 }
9084 
9085 /*
9086  * qo_check_coll_optimization () - Checks for attributes with collation in
9087  * index and fills the optimization structure
9088  *
9089  * return:
9090  * ent(in): index entry
9091  * collation_opt(out):
9092  *
9093  * Note : this only checks for index covering optimization.
9094  * If at least one attribute of index does not support index covering,
9095  * this option will be disabled for the entire index.
9096  */
9097 void
9098 qo_check_coll_optimization (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * ent, COLL_OPT * collation_opt)
9099 {
9100  assert (collation_opt != NULL);
9101 
9102  collation_opt->allow_index_opt = true;
9103 
9104  if (ent && ent->class_ && ent->class_->smclass)
9105  {
9106  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons;
9107  SM_ATTRIBUTE **attr;
9108  cons = classobj_find_class_index (ent->class_->smclass, ent->constraints->name);
9109  if (cons == NULL || cons->attributes == NULL)
9110  {
9111  return;
9112  }
9113 
9114  for (attr = cons->attributes; *attr != NULL; attr++)
9115  {
9116  if ((*attr)->domain != NULL && TP_TYPE_HAS_COLLATION (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE ((*attr)->domain)))
9117  {
9118  LANG_COLLATION *lang_coll = lang_get_collation (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION ((*attr)->domain));
9119 
9120  assert (lang_coll != NULL);
9121 
9122  if (!(lang_coll->options.allow_index_opt))
9123  {
9124  collation_opt->allow_index_opt = false;
9125  return;
9126  }
9127  }
9128  }
9129  }
9130 }
9131 
9132 
9133 /*
9134  * qo_check_type_index_covering () - Checks for attributes with types not able
9135  * to support index covering
9136  *
9137  * return:
9138  * ent(in): index entry
9139  * collation_opt(out):
9140  *
9141  * Note : this only checks for index covering optimization.
9142  * If at least one attribute of index does not support index covering,
9143  * this option will be disabled for the entire index.
9144  */
9145 bool
9146 qo_check_type_index_covering (QO_INDEX_ENTRY * ent)
9147 {
9148  if (ent && ent->class_ && ent->class_->smclass)
9149  {
9150  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons;
9151  SM_ATTRIBUTE **attr;
9152 
9153  cons = classobj_find_class_index (ent->class_->smclass, ent->constraints->name);
9154  if (cons == NULL || cons->attributes == NULL)
9155  {
9156  return true;
9157  }
9158 
9159  for (attr = cons->attributes; *attr != NULL; attr++)
9160  {
9161  if ((*attr)->domain != NULL && TP_TYPE_NOT_SUPPORT_COVERING (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE ((*attr)->domain)))
9162  {
9163  return false;
9164  }
9165  }
9166  }
9167 
9168  return true;
9169 }
9170 
9171 /*
9172  * qo_discover_sort_limit_join_nodes () - discover nodes which are joined to
9173  * this node and do not need to be
9174  * taken into consideration when
9175  * evaluating sort and limit operators
9176  * return : void
9177  * env (in) : environment
9178  * node (in) : node to process
9179  * order_nodes (in) : nodes on which the query will be ordered
9180  * dep_nodes (in/out) : nodes which are dependent on this one for sort and
9181  * limit evaluation
9182  *
9183  * Note: A node joined to this node is independent of the sort and limit
9184  * operator evaluation if we are not ordering results based on it and
9185  * one of the following conditions is true:
9186  * 1. Is left outer joined to to node
9187  * 2. Is inner joined to this node through a primary key->foreign key
9188  * relationship (see qo_is_pk_fk_full_join)
9189  */
9190 static void
9191 qo_discover_sort_limit_join_nodes (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * node, BITSET * order_nodes, BITSET * dep_nodes)
9192 {
9193  BITSET join_nodes;
9194  BITSET_ITERATOR bi;
9195  QO_TERM *term;
9196  int i;
9197 
9198  bitset_init (dep_nodes, env);
9199  bitset_init (&join_nodes, env);
9200 
9201  for (i = 0; i < env->nedges; i++)
9202  {
9203  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
9204  if (BITSET_MEMBER (QO_TERM_NODES (term), QO_NODE_IDX (node)))
9205  {
9206  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_JOIN
9207  && ((QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) == JOIN_LEFT && QO_TERM_HEAD (term) == node)
9208  || (QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) == JOIN_RIGHT && QO_TERM_TAIL (term) == node)))
9209  {
9210  /* Other nodes in this term are outer joined with our node. We can safely add them to dep_nodes if we're
9211  * not ordering on them */
9212  bitset_union (dep_nodes, &QO_TERM_NODES (term));
9213 
9214  /* remove nodes on which we're ordering */
9215  bitset_difference (dep_nodes, order_nodes);
9216  }
9217  else if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_PATH)
9218  {
9219  /* path edges are always independent */
9220  bitset_difference (dep_nodes, &QO_TERM_NODES (term));
9221  }
9222  else
9223  {
9224  bitset_union (&join_nodes, &QO_TERM_NODES (term));
9225  }
9226  }
9227  }
9228 
9229  /* remove nodes on which we're ordering from the list */
9230  bitset_difference (&join_nodes, order_nodes);
9231 
9232  /* process inner joins */
9233  for (i = bitset_iterate (&join_nodes, &bi); i != -1; i = bitset_next_member (&bi))
9234  {
9235  if (qo_is_pk_fk_full_join (env, node, QO_ENV_NODE (env, i)))
9236  {
9237  bitset_add (dep_nodes, i);
9238  }
9239  }
9240 }
9241 
9242 /*
9243  * qo_is_pk_fk_full_join () - verify if the join between two nodes can be
9244  * fully expressed through a foreign key->primary
9245  * key join
9246  * return : true if there is a pk->fk relationship, false otherwise
9247  * env (in) :
9248  * fk_node (in) : node which should have a foreign key
9249  * pk_node (in) : node which should have a primary key
9250  *
9251  * Note: Full PK->FK relationships guarantee that any tuple from the FK node
9252  * generates a single tuple in the PK node. This relationship allows us to
9253  * apply some optimizations (like SORT-LIMIT). This relationship exists if
9254  * the following conditions are met:
9255  * 1. PK node has only EQ predicates.
9256  * 2. All terms from PK node are join edges
9257  * 3. The segments involved in terms are a prefix of the primary key index
9258  * 4. There is a foreign key in the fk_node which references the pk_node's
9259  * primary key and the join uses the same prefix of the foreign key as
9260  * that the of the primary key.
9261  */
9262 static bool
9263 qo_is_pk_fk_full_join (QO_ENV * env, QO_NODE * fk_node, QO_NODE * pk_node)
9264 {
9265  int i, j;
9266  QO_NODE_INDEX *node_indexp;
9267  QO_INDEX_ENTRY *pk_idx = NULL, *fk_idx = NULL;
9268  QO_TERM *term;
9269  QO_SEGMENT *fk_seg, *pk_seg;
9270 
9271  node_indexp = QO_NODE_INDEXES (pk_node);
9272  if (node_indexp == NULL)
9273  {
9274  return false;
9275  }
9276 
9277  pk_idx = NULL;
9278  for (i = 0; i < QO_NI_N (node_indexp); i++)
9279  {
9280  pk_idx = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, i)->head;
9281  if (pk_idx->constraints->type == SM_CONSTRAINT_PRIMARY_KEY)
9282  {
9283  break;
9284  }
9285  pk_idx = NULL;
9286  }
9287 
9288  if (pk_idx == NULL)
9289  {
9290  /* node either does not have a primary key or it is not referenced in any way in this statement */
9291  return false;
9292  }
9293 
9294  /* find the foreign key on fk_node which references pk_node */
9295  node_indexp = QO_NODE_INDEXES (fk_node);
9296  if (node_indexp == NULL)
9297  {
9298  return false;
9299  }
9300 
9301  fk_idx = NULL;
9302  for (i = 0; i < QO_NI_N (node_indexp); i++)
9303  {
9304  fk_idx = QO_NI_ENTRY (node_indexp, i)->head;
9305  if (fk_idx->constraints->type != SM_CONSTRAINT_FOREIGN_KEY)
9306  {
9307  fk_idx = NULL;
9308  continue;
9309  }
9310  if (BTID_IS_EQUAL (&fk_idx->constraints->fk_info->ref_class_pk_btid, &pk_idx->constraints->index_btid))
9311  {
9312  /* These are the droids we're looking for */
9313  break;
9314  }
9315  fk_idx = NULL;
9316  }
9317 
9318  if (fk_idx == NULL)
9319  {
9320  /* No matching foreign key */
9321  return false;
9322  }
9323 
9324  /* Make sure we don't have gaps in the primary key columns */
9325  for (i = 0; i < pk_idx->nsegs; i++)
9326  {
9327  if (pk_idx->seg_idxs[i] == -1)
9328  {
9329  if (i == 0)
9330  {
9331  /* first col must be present */
9332  return false;
9333  }
9334  /* this has to be the last one */
9335  for (j = i + 1; j < pk_idx->nsegs; j++)
9336  {
9337  if (pk_idx->seg_idxs[j] != -1)
9338  {
9339  return false;
9340  }
9341  }
9342  break;
9343  }
9344  }
9345 
9346  if (pk_idx->nsegs > fk_idx->nsegs)
9347  {
9348  /* The number of segments from primary key should be less than those referenced in the foreign key. We can have
9349  * more segments referenced from the foreign key because we don't care about other terms from the fk node
9350  */
9351  return false;
9352  }
9353 
9354  /* Verify that all terms from pk_node reference terms from fk_node. If we find a term which only references pk_node,
9355  * we can abandon the search.
9356  */
9357  for (i = 0; i < env->nterms; i++)
9358  {
9359  term = QO_ENV_TERM (env, i);
9360 
9361  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) == QO_TC_DUMMY_JOIN)
9362  {
9363  /* skip always true dummy join terms */
9364  continue;
9365  }
9366 
9367  if (!BITSET_MEMBER (QO_TERM_NODES (term), QO_NODE_IDX (pk_node)))
9368  {
9369  continue;
9370  }
9371 
9372  if (!BITSET_MEMBER (pk_idx->terms, QO_TERM_IDX (term)))
9373  {
9374  /* Term does not use pk_idx. This means that there is a predicate on pk_node outside of the primary key */
9375  return false;
9376  }
9377 
9378  if (QO_TERM_JOIN_TYPE (term) != JOIN_INNER)
9379  {
9380  /* we're only interested in inner joins */
9381  return false;
9382  }
9383 
9384  if (!BITSET_MEMBER (QO_TERM_NODES (term), QO_NODE_IDX (fk_node)))
9385  {
9386  /* found a term belonging to pk_node which does not reference the fk_node. This means pk_node is not full
9387  * joined with fk_node
9388  */
9389  return false;
9390  }
9391 
9392  if (QO_TERM_CLASS (term) != QO_TC_JOIN || !QO_TERM_IS_FLAGED (term, QO_TERM_EQUAL_OP))
9393  {
9394  /* Not a join term, bail out */
9395  return false;
9396  }
9397 
9398  /* Iterate through segments and make sure we're joining same columns. E.g.: For PK(Pa, Pb) and FK (Fa, Fb), make
9399  * sure the terms are not Pa = Fb or Pb = Fa
9400  */
9401  if (term->can_use_index != 2)
9402  {
9403  return false;
9404  }
9405  if (QO_SEG_HEAD (QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, 0)) == fk_node)
9406  {
9407  fk_seg = QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, 0);
9408  pk_seg = QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, 1);
9409  }
9410  else
9411  {
9412  pk_seg = QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, 0);
9413  fk_seg = QO_TERM_INDEX_SEG (term, 1);
9414  }
9415 
9416  /* make sure pk_seg and fk_seg reference the same position in the two indexes */
9417  for (j = 0; j < pk_idx->nsegs; j++)
9418  {
9419  if (pk_idx->seg_idxs[j] == QO_SEG_IDX (pk_seg))
9420  {
9421  assert (j < fk_idx->nsegs);
9422  if (fk_idx->seg_idxs[j] != QO_SEG_IDX (fk_seg))
9423  {
9424  /* not joining the same column */
9425  return false;
9426  }
9427  break;
9428  }
9429  }
9430  }
9431 
9432  return true;
9433 }
9434 
9435 /*
9436  * qo_is_non_mvcc_class_with_index () - Is disabled-MVCC class with index.
9437  *
9438  * return : True/false.
9439  * class_entry_p (in) : QO class entry.
9440  */
9441 static bool
9442 qo_is_non_mvcc_class_with_index (QO_CLASS_INFO_ENTRY * class_entry_p)
9443 {
9444  /* Index scan is currently optimized for MVCC and doesn't work properly for non-MVCC classes. Disable index scan for
9445  * MVCC-disabled classes that have indexes. Index is still used to find unique object by key.
9446  */
9447  return (oid_check_cached_class_oid (OID_CACHE_SERIAL_CLASS_ID, &class_entry_p->oid)
9448  || oid_check_cached_class_oid (OID_CACHE_HA_APPLY_INFO_CLASS_ID, &class_entry_p->oid));
9449 }
